In Minneapolis, a food truck cranks out fresh lobster rolls that do double duty in a dive bar. And in Dallas, a side-of-the-road joint focuses on one thing only: burgers.

episodes.name: Crankin' Up the Classics
episodes.overview:
Broder's Cucina Italiana (Minneapolis, Minn.); Chop House Burgers (Arlington, Tex.).

This trip, Guy's checkin' out joints that are kickin' the staples up a notch. In Minneapolis, there's a family-run Italian kitchen and store crankin' out what the locals love - pizza and totally fresh pasta. And between Dallas and Fort Worth, Guy hits an Arlington fave grillin' up unexpected brisket burgers and fixin' real-deal gumbo - and meets his all-time favorite football player, legendary Houston Oiler Earl Campbell.

episodes.name: Passin' the Baton
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's hittin' the road and chowin' down on some long-standing traditions. In Ventura, Calif., one Pete passes another Pete a rockin' breakfast joint servin' up pancake burritos and fiery-hot sandwiches. And in Baltimore, check out the Greek spot where two cooking families come together to serve up age-old family recipes.

episodes.name: Big Time Flavor
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's hittin' the road looking for plates packin' a punch. In Dallas, a Neapolitan pizza place spreading bacon jam on pizza and fresh pancetta on the pasta. In Minneapolis, the Caribbean joint cranking out spicy chickpea and blazing oxtail stews. And in Austin, Texas, the tiny cafe dishing out scratch-made chicken burgers and quail.

episodes.name: Unexpected Eats
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's going for some unique chow. In Stillwater, Minn., get a pirate's take on barbecue and a sadist twist on hot wings. In Santa Rosa, Calif., Guy's own joint serves up his twist on Asian, Mexican and Italian. And in Portsmouth, Va., check out an epic hot dog joint turning its attention on chicken dumplings.

episodes.name: BBQ Road Show
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's tucking in the napkin and gettin' into some righteous barbecue. In Dallas, the barbecue stand tucked into a farmers' market, dishing out classic beef brisket and Carolina pork. And outside Las Vegas, the longtime meat market turning its knives on fresh sausage and slow-cooked ribs.

episodes.name: All Vegas, All the Time
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's going off the strip and digging into Las Vegas. There's the dive bar dishing out real deal food from Buffalo, N.Y. Then, a Bulgarian tapas joint serving up layers and layers of European comfort food. Plus, a visit to Guy's alma mater, UNLV, that has him back in class cooking with the school's newest crop of culinary talent.

episodes.name: Serious Sandwiches
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's got a line on some righteous sammies. In Austin, Texas, the gourmet sandwich shop slicin' up duck pastrami and a knuckle sandwich. In Las Vegas, the roast beef po boy done the Cajun way. And in St. Paul, Minnesota, the burger joint reborn after a tragedy, grillin' up a new series of stuffed burgers.

episodes.name: International Eats
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's got his sight set on food with international influence. In Richardson, Texas, the Lebanese joint going big when it comes to stacking the schwarma. In Las Vegas, the burger spot mixing up meat with an Asian twist. And in New York City, the Druze way of perfecting the pita.

episodes.name: Belly Up
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's getting up close to some serious gourmet grub. In Chicago, the brewhouse serving up beer to go with mussels, a mega brisket sandwich and their version of headcheese. And in Austin, Texas, the open kitchen kickin' out cheesy popovers and tasty shellfish.

episodes.name: Dynamic Dishes
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's taking on some truly unique eats. In Honolulu, there's a Jamaican joint servin' up jerk chicken wings and some wicked goat curry. In Arlington, Texas, Guy takes on the Russian spot flipping a potato pancake stuffed with beef. And in Las Vegas, check out a taco stand fillin' up tortillas with some worldly flavors.

episodes.name: Coast to Coast Chow
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's culinary quest is covering the country. In Charleston, S.C., the breakfast hangout doing a chicken fried biscuit and a shrimp BLT. In Chicago, the 40-year-old institution bustin' out traditional German specialties. And in Honolulu, a food truck cranking out chimichurri beef tacos and mango pies.

episodes.name: Unconventional Comforts
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's food radar is all over the map. On the east coast of Oahu, Hawaii, the general store crankin' out traditional Hawaiian dishes like lau lau stew. In Chicago, the real deal Italian family serving up totally scratch-made Sicilian sandwiches like the schiacciata. And in Hernando, Miss., the underground cafe going bananas with their twist on French toast.

episodes.name: Goin' the Extra Mile
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's headin' to some joints going all-in on some classic comfort foods. In Chicago, the burger joint with Asian flair proudly serving all things umami. In Memphis, a high-end chef taking low-down Southern staples to whole new level like the chorizo meatloaf with green tomato gravy. And on Oahu, Hawaii, the gas station joint fillin' up the locals with all sorts of island favorites like kalua pork and mahi mahi.

episodes.name: Savory Standouts
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's slammin' on the breaks for some enticing eats. In Chicago, the authentic Cuban joint platin' up family recipes like the fricase de pollo. In Memphis, a neighborhood gastropub serving eclectic dishes like duck fried rice and homemade popcorn. And in Annapolis, Md., the sidewalk shack worth stopping for, with dishes like chipotle habanero barbecue pork sandwiches.

episodes.name: Surf 'N' Turf Jackpot
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's hit the gold mine of surf and turf. In Horn Lake, Miss., the Memphis-style barbecue joint puttin' the championship touch on ribs, cheese fritters, and burgers with pork rinds. And in Kaneohe, Oahu, the poke palace serving up over thirty flavors of fresh fish, including tuna and octopus caught by the owner himself.

episodes.name: Massachusetts Madness
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's grubbin' from one end of Massachusetts to the other, filling up the tank with stuffed specialties. In Fall River, the Polish joint specializing in all kinds of pierogies -- like the big seller, mac and cheese. And in Boston, the gourmet sandwich shop crankin' out roast beef and pork perfection.

episodes.name: East Coast Comfort
episodes.overview:
This trip Guy's tucking in the napkin for an Italian feast. In Boston, the corner joint serving up a seafood feast straight out of Italy, and hosting the mayor to boot. And in Providence, the cornucopia of Federal Hill begins at an old school spot that's passing out meatballs and fries, and then the new school restaurant crankin' out totally fresh linguine and clams.

episode aka Italian Extravaganza

episodes.name: Flavortown Medley
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's diggin' into all kinds of fantastic flavors. In Memphis, the bar turned bistro offering low brow favorites like duck fried rice and Jack Daniels bread pudding. In Haleiwa, Hawaii, the food truck rocking out Thai short ribs and crunchy local shrimp. And in Baltimore, Guy revisits a joint firing up the grills for the signature taste of pit beef sandwiches.

episodes.name: Burgers, Noodles and Quahogs
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's on the road for some stellar food mashups. In Somerville, Mass., the burger joint putting the crowning touch on a mac and cheese burger. In Middletown, R.I., a seafood spot stuffing quahogs with chorizo and turning calamari into a Kung Pao classic. And in St. Louis, the Filipino-inspired food truck hand pulling noodles for savory dishes, and washing it all down with a two-finger punch drink.

episodes.name: Handcrafted
episodes.overview:
The Elegant Farmer (Memphis, Tenn.); Italian Corner (East Providence, R.I.).

This trip, Guy's checkin' in on tasty joints run by food fanatics. In Memphis, the chef-slash-farmer's market guru running a farm-to-table spot serving up a whole lot of classic comfort from meatloaf to sloppy joes to catfish. And in Providence, the real deal family-run Italian deli scratch-making meat tortellini in the dedicated "pasta room" and curing their own bresaola meats.

episodes.name: All Family, All the Time
episodes.overview:
3 Angels Diner (Memphis, Tenn.); Opal Thai Food (Hale'iwa, Oahu, Hawaii); Anthonino's Taverna (St. Louis, Mo.).

This trip, Guy's headed to places where families rule. In Memphis, the kid-inspired joint serving up serious fried chicken. On the North Shore of Oahu, the Thai spot where mom and pop spice up the island with pad Thai, pork larb, and their big seller: garlic fried chicken wings. And on The Hill in St. Louis, the Italian-Greek joint run by two brothers, serving up a town staple in fried ravioli and mom's recipe for dolmathes.

episodes.name: Food Done Right
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's diggin' into food made the right way. In Narragansett, R.I., the summer shack servin' up clam cakes cooked in beef fat and scratch made strawberry shortcake. In St. Louis, the neighborhood joint putting the smoke on cheesefries and delicious duck. And in East Boston, the family Mexican spot cooking up mom's chilaquiles recipe.

episodes.name: Pubs and Grub
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's grubbin' at some popular hangouts. In St. Louis, the classic British pub cooking up gourmet grilled cheese and a porchetta masterpiece. In Kill Devil Hills, N.C., the brewing station serving righteous shrimp and grits alongside craft made beers. And in Cranston, R.I., the corner spot dishin' out the pasta loaded with little neck clams.

episodes.name: Turn On Traditional
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's gettin' a taste of traditional recipes, with a kick. In Chesterfield, Mo., the Mexican joint serving up a turn on mom's pork chile verde. In Boston, a second generation lobster shack turning heads with cod cakes and lobster mac and cheese. And in Syracuse, N.Y., the real deal Irish pub stuffing the Rueben into fritters and layin' out an Irish meatloaf.

episodes.name: Authentic Eats
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's finding real deal authentic eats in unusual spots. In St. Louis, the n'awlins roadhouse serving up rice and beans, cajun potstickers and a pulled pork pasta. And in Syracuse, N.Y., the tiny Mediterranean cafe crankin' out first-class falafel and baklava.

episodes.name: Fully Focused
episodes.overview:
Pastabilities (Syracuse, N.Y.) • The Brine and Bottle (Nags Head, N.C.)

This trip, Guy's visiting restaurants with a definite direction. In Syracuse, the longtime pasta institution makin' a tomato sauce just for dipping, wicked-spicy chicken riggies, and duck and cheese pizza. And in Nags Head, the local food-focused joint using funky techniques on deep fried pickles and soft-shell crab.

episodes.name: Far Out
episodes.overview:
Funk-n-Waffles (Syracuse, N.Y.) • La Isla (Hoboken, N.J.) • Cravings (Duck, N.C.).

This trip, Guy's honing in on spots doing it different. In Syracuse, the basement joint rockin' out waffles with their fried chicken, and a full-blown Thanksgiving dinner any time of year. In Hoboken, the Cuban spot goin' deep into the repertoire with a salt cured beef dish and all kinds of classic Cuban appetizers. And in North Carolina, the gas station turned gourmet seafood stand grillin' up scallops and packin' a crab boil to-go.

episodes.name: Matches Made in Heaven
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's meeting up with credible combos. In Brooklyn, N.Y., the barbecue joint mashin' up a variety of styles for their unique wings and their big time beef ribs. And in Manteo, N.C., the husband and wife tag-teaming in the kitchen to deliver on soft shell crab quesadilla, tuna tacos, and shrimp and chorizo.

episodes.name: Savory Sensations
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's warming up with some standout specialties. In Brooklyn, N.Y., the mom and pop diner flipping a skillet apple waffle with pancetta and deep-frying breakfast empanadas. In Olympia, Wash., the brew house cranking out crab cannelloni and bangers and mash. And in Grandy, N.C., the farm to table German joint rolling out the ruebens and a cheesy baked potato soup.

episodes.name: Hometown Haunts
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's takin' a spin through the town favorites. In Chatham, N.J., the real deal Italian joint bakin' up some righteous fried chicken, arancini balls, and the decadent sacred swine sandwich. And in Olympia, Wash., the homestyle spot cranking out creole oyster benedict, a colorful winter squash and apple hash and a unique blueberry crunch roller.

episodes.name: Land to Sea
episodes.overview:
Fish Tale Brew Pub (Olympia, Wash.) • Black Pelican Seafood Company (Kitty Hawk, N.C.) • Empire Brewing Company (Syracuse, N.Y.)

This trip, Guy's samplin' from the land and sea. In Washington State, a brewpub combinin' their beer with bangers and mash and crab stuffed cannelloni. In North Carolina's Outer Banks, an ages-old summertime institution firin' up fisherman's risotto and citrus chicken. And in Upstate New York, a subterranean joint servin' up scratch-made spicy-sweet sausage fajitas.

episodes.name: Decadent Dishes
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's goin' coast to coast for decadent dishes. In Brooklyn, the southern-inspired spot crankin' out fried chicken and waffles, a spicy pulled pork sandwich and a daily donut to die for. And in Puyallup, Wash., the local's joint serving up homemade meatballs and fire grilled artichokes.

episodes.name: Eurocentric
episodes.overview:
Hey Meatball (Toronto, Ont., Canada) • Bruno's European Restaurant (Tacoma, Wash.) • Eva's European Sweets (Syracuse, N.Y.)

This trip, Guy's rollin' out for a roadtrip feast of European flavors. First up, a Toronto place only dishin' up meatballs: beef, pork, chicken, and more.  In Washington State, a German-Polish fusion simmerin' hangover soup and Frikadelle meatballs. And in Syracuse, a Polish family spot servin' potato pancakes with a heapin' side of pizzazz.

episodes.name: Hittin' the Grill
episodes.overview: Guy turns his attention to foods that are grilled, beginning with a trip to a Los Angeles joint, where he tries a hot-pork sandwich and a lamb burger. Also: kabobs and beet salad are on the menu at a pub in Tacoma, Wash.

episodes.name: Unlikely Partners
episodes.overview:
Beer Belly (Los Angeles, Calif.) • Lakeview Restaurant (Toronto, Ont., Canada)

This trip, Guy's highlightin' unique combos in funky places.  In L.A.'s Koreatown neighborhood, a craft beer spot servin' up duck confit fries and killer chicken wings with their brewskis.  And in Toronto, a 24-hour retro diner givin' big-time upgrades to grilled cheese, milkshakes, and a chicken club sandwich with a little somethin' somethin' crunch.

episodes.name: Layers of Flavor
episodes.overview: A restored diner in Toronto is celebrated for its pork belly, mac-and-cheese burger and Christmas burger. Also: Guy visits a surfer hangout in Nags Head, N.C., where Jamaican jerk chicken and Caribbean pork chops are served.

episodes.name: Real Deal Roots
episodes.overview:
Caplansky's Delicatessen (Toronto, Ont., Canada); Chomp Chomp Nation (Orange County, Calif.).

Over the border in Toronto, Guy stops by a Jewish deli with an old-school approach to smoked meat sandwiches and from-scratch, schmaltzy knishes gone wild. And somewhere in Orange County outside L.A., Guy finds the husband-and-wife duo and their food truck infusing Singaporean flavors into their chili crab cake and lamb burger.

episodes.name: Tacos and Tots
episodes.overview: Dirty Oscars Annex (Tacoma, Wash.) • Highland Tavern (Denver, Colo.).  This trip Guy's hitting the road for joints taking childhood favorites to a gourmet level. in Tacoma, the neighborhood spot turning out pork shoulder tacos, elk sliders and tater tots stuffed with parmesan cheese. And in Denver, the old-time bar going all-out homemade on the tater tots, the pork rinds and a monster pastrami sandwich.

episodes.name: Chicken, Chili and Chowder
episodes.overview:
The Stockyards Smokehouse & Larder (Toronto, Ont., Canada) • Chili John's (Burbank, Calif.) • Sidecar (Philadelphia, Pa.)

This trip Guy's hittin' the road for some scratch-made comfort food. In Toronto, the smokehouse kicking burgers and fried chicken up a notch and turning a traditional BLT on its head. In Burbank, Calif., the family-owned chili-serving spot with a name dating back a century. And in Philadelphia, the three-story gourmet bar food joint crankin' out clam chowder with gnocchi and a regional fry favorite.

episodes.name: Dynamic Duos
episodes.overview: This trip Guy's checkin' out the combos that make some local hangouts a hit. In Denver the double-duty corner bar smoking pork for its biscuits and topping pizzas with the bounty of the county. And in Scottsdale, Ariz., the husband-and-wife team fusing their Mexican and Mediterranean roots for some standout Southwest dishes, like breakfast enchiladas and french toast with red wine rosemary syrup.

episodes.name: Traditional Gone Wild
episodes.overview:
South Philadelphia Tap Room (Philadelphia, Pa.) • St. Francis (Phoenix, Ariz.)

This trip Guy's digging into some dishes like mama made, if she had a wild imagination. In Philadelphia a very special guest hits the kitchen with Guy for fried PB&Js and tacos that start with the head of a pig. In Phoenix the farm-to-table spot dishin' out a dynamite pork sammie and cooking everything from pizzas to pancakes to meatballs in its wood-fired oven.

episodes.name: Peppers, Pork and Poutine
episodes.overview: This trip triple "D" goes triple "P" with some standout veggie and meat dishes. In Phoenix the tattooed, trained chef putting her spin on chiles and a regional pork dish. And in Toronto the decades-old bohemian joint servin' up sticky Asian pork ribs and a Canadian staple.

episodes.name: Kings and Queens of 'Cue
episodes.overview: This trip Guy's meeting some masters of meat. In Compton, Calif., the Texas-inspired barbecue joint smokin' pork ribs and putting smoked turkey necks in the collard greens. In Denver the beer and pizza joint whipping up a unique bowl of mac 'n cheese and topping pizzas with beer braised brisket. And in Philadelphia a restaurant veteran serving up all kinds of fresh 'cue, from the chopped brisket sandwich to a Vietnamese-inspired pork belly sandwich.

episodes.name: A Festival of Flavor
episodes.overview:
Standard Tap (Philadelphia, Penn.) • Curry Corner (Tempe, Ariz.) • Prohibition (Denver, Colo.)

This trip Guy's pullin' over for the bounty of the county. In Philadelphia, a local joint's crankin' out chicken pie without the pot and awesome grilled octopus. In Arizona, the Pakistani spot servin' up Tandoori chicken and savory goat. And in Denver, the throwback bar goin' gangster on short rib burgers and killer apple strudel.

episodes.name: Timeless Traditions
episodes.overview: This trip Guy gets the lowdown on some longstanding traditions. In Philadelphia, the Jamaican joint going all out authentic with the jerk chicken. In Scottsdale, Ariz., the decades-old family joint servin' all kinds of sandwiches, and a time-tested sausage recipe. And in Denver, Guy's diving into some serious soul food for rabbit and chitlings.

episodes.name: From Pound Cake to Pot Pie
episodes.overview:
The Duce (Phoeniz, Ariz.) • Haggo's Organic Taco (Leucadia, Calif.) • Geechee Girl Rice Café (Mount Airy, Penn.)

This trip Guy's pullin' in for a mishmash of comfort food. In Phoenix, there's the boxing gym // restaurant servin' up mac-and-cheese muffins and chicken pot pie in glass mugs. In Leucadia, CA it's a funky joint puttin' together organic fish tacos inspired by none other than Jacques Cousteau.  And in the Mount Airy neighborhood near Philadelphia, Guy hits a spot dishin' out African-inspired Low Country cuisine including unique North African chicken and sour cream pound cake.

episodes.name: L.A. Eats
episodes.overview: This trip Guy's got visitors — a whole cast of 'em! In this comedy-filled, star-studded episode, Guy gets a visit from Adam Sandler, Chris Rock, Kevin James, and David Spade, the stars of the film Grown Ups 2, and invites them along for the Los Angeles ride. First, the Filipino barbecue joint that's got everyone going bonkers over the cornbread and the coconut beef. Then they're off to a decades-old family-run Italian joint, where they're piling up monster sandwiches and some meatball madness.

episodes.name: All San Diego, All the Time
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's heading to San Diego for some favorites, old and new. In Ocean Beach, Calif., Guy's hittin' up a legendary surfer spot for some righteous burgers with an old buddy. Just up the block, the brother-owned noodle joint with fried rice, pho, a story to tell. And in North Park, Calif., an all-time favorite pizza joint gets a second look as Guy swings by for a slice.

episodes.name: From the Heart
episodes.overview:
Shirley’s Tippy Canoe (Troutdale, Ore.) • Spirito’s Italian Diner (Carlsbad, Calif.) • Nopalito (San Francisco, Calif.)

This trip, Guy's hittin' up some spots putting their heart and soul into everything they do. In scenic Oregon, an ages-old riverside tavern crankin' out killer sloppy joes. In coastal SoCal, a family-run Italian joint stayin’ true to their original ravioli recipe. And in the City by the Bay, a Mexican spot servin' up authentic dishes like quesadillas, tortas and pozole rojo.

episodes.name: That's Fresh
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's stopping by some joints that are keepin' it fresh. In San Francisco, the Venezuelan joint servin' up a totally gluten-free menu of authentic standbys like arepas and empanadas. And in Portland, Ore., the family-run sausage spot cranking out dozens of homemade meats like Italian red wine dry cured salami and roasted garlic and rosemary bologna.

episodes.name: Neighborhood Knockouts
episodes.overview:
Crest Café (San Diego, Calif.) • Show Dogs (San Francisco, Calif.) • Industrial Café & Saloon (Portland, Ore.)

This trip, Guy's traveling up and down the West Coast in search of funky neighborhood joints. In San Diego, the "everybody knows your name" all-day breakfast café servin' up decadent crème brûlée French toast and juicy butter burgers. In San Fran, the hot dog spot holdin' the block down with unique creations like a lamb merguez dog and a killer fried chicken sandwich. And in Portland, the father-and-son team crankin' out good ole Americana with dishes like corned beef hash and creamed chipped beef.

episodes.name: Meat Lover's Paradise
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's signing up for a meat-crazed master class. In Portland, Ore., the craft-cooking family joint with a chef who butchers, cures, preserves and smokes everything in-house, from headcheese to great-grandma's fried chicken recipe. In San Carlos, Calif., the pastrami-crazed neighborhood spot crankin' out burgers, cheesesteaks and signature sammies.

episodes.name: Servin' Up San Francisco
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's cruisin' the San Francisco coast for a diverse culinary road trip. First, Guy swings by the repurposed garage in the Mission District for some southern hospitality served up in braised beef short ribs and spicy shrimp and gravy. Then he's off to the NY-style deli crankin' out old-fashioned chicken noodle with matzo ball soup and potato latkes. And the food extravaganza ends at San Fran's food truck park, where the reinvented Japanese/Korean truck hooks Guy up with a totally unique take on Asian-fusion in the pork belly and short rib kojas.

episodes.name: Cannoli, Fritters and Wings
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's rollin' out for a festival of flavors. In Portland, Ore., the Guamanian food truck serving up righteous shrimp fritters and a unique spin on chicken salad. In Wheat Ridge, Colo., the family-run comfort food joint crankin' out killer cannoli and kraut burgers. And in San Francisco, the fusion food truck combining Filipino and Latin traditions in adobo buffalo wings and grandpa's recipe for pork tacos.

episodes.name: Aces of Authenticity
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's hittin' up some joints that are authentic to the bone. In Santa Fe, N.M., the farm-raised Chimayan owner turnin' out traditional dishes like blue corn enchiladas with red chile sauce and chile en nogada. In Portland, Ore., the noodle house cranking out mom's recipes for all kinds of authentic Chinese dishes like won ton soup. And in Albuquerque, N.M., the Italian joint with a native Frenchman at the helm, serving up totally fresh pastas like beef cheek manicotti and squid ink black pasta with calamari.

episodes.name: Sammies and Stew
episodes.overview:
Bocadillo's (Albuquerque, N.M.) • Jambo Cafe (Santa Fe, N.M.).

This trip, Guy's diggin' into some super sandwiches and savory stew. First up in Albuquerque: the school lunch maven crankin' out creative sammies like turkey avocado with green apple chile chutney and a totally unique Duke City Reuben. Then on to Santa Fe, where the cafe with a native Kenyan in the kitchen serves up totally fresh fish, like island spiced banana leaf mahi mahi and a killer Caribbean goat stew.

episodes.name: All Kinds of Gobble Gobble
episodes.overview:
Golden Crown Panaderia (Albuquerque, N.M.) • Back Street Bistro (Santa Fe, N.M.) • Danny Edwards Blvd Barbecue (Kansas City, Mo.)

This trip, Guy's gettin' a variety of Thanksgiving tastes and treasures. In Albuquerque, a powerhouse father-son duo bake up a turkey-shaped specialty bread. In Santa Fe, a "blink and you'll miss it" deli serving up award-winning soup and traditional pies. And in Kansas City, smoking whole turkeys for folks who don't want to cook one themselves. This is the kind of holiday food extravaganza only a dude in a red Camaro could drum up.

episodes.name: Comfort and Soul
episodes.overview:
B.B.'s Lawnside Bar-B-Q (Kansas City, Mo.) • Tin Shed Garden Café (Portland, Ore.) • Nexus Brewery & Restaurant (Albuquerque, N.M.)

This trip, Guy's hittin' up some joints that'll warm the palate and the soul. In Kansas City, a barbecue and blues joint with a die-hard competitor dishin' up favorites like burnt ends for a local NASCAR hero. In Portland, a funky neighborhood spot crankin' out comfort vegetarian fare like a heartless artichoke sandwich that hits all the right notes. And in Albuquerque, a double-duty brewery servin' up their New Mexico twist on soul food faves like southern fried chicken and crackling cornbread..

episodes.name: Pork, Pasta and Barbecue
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's checking out some tried and true local faves. In Kansas City, Mo., the neighborhood favorite killin' it with their scratch-made standouts like pork hash with black beans. Down the road in Kansas City, right on the Missouri/Kansas border, the former chef to the President of Italy dishing up authentic homemade pastas straight out of the family recipe book. And in Albuquerque, N.M., the southern pride joint situated on Route 66, serving up a smorgasbord of dishes from smoked barbecue chicken to specialty hot dogs.

episodes.name: South of the Border
episodes.overview: Guy travels to Cabo San Lucas, Mexico, and visits a taco joint that serves octopus and Guadalajara-style sauces. Also: stuffed fish with lobster sauce and a unique take on French toast; taquito trifecta and a Mexican twist on sushi.

episodes.name: Tennessee Holiday Traditions
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's digging into the unique holiday traditions in Tennessee. In Hendersonville, the barbecue joint with a storied past serving up the traditional shoulder pull and a holiday ham with a fiery finish. And in Nashville, the tiny taco joint wrappin' up traditional Mexican tamales and unique quinoa sweet potato tacos.

episodes.name: Family Time
episodes.overview: Guy visits several family-owned restaurants. Included: A husband and wife in Nashville run a gourmet food truck specializing in grilled cheese; and a nearby Italian spot serves grandma's recipes for lasagna and lamb shanks. Also: Siblings in Kansas City embrace their Chinese heritage by making firebird chicken and chili pepper wontons.

episodes.name: Soup, Salad and Seafood
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's diving into all kinds of classic comfort foods. In Kansas City, Mo., the real deal chef serving up his dressed-up version of comfort food with dishes like chicken pot pie and steamed mussels. In Franklin, Tenn., the southern spot crankin' out comfort food favorites like jambalaya, chargrilled oysters and the regional favorite hot chicken. And near the airport in Nashville, the food truck turned deli keepin' it funky with all kinds of homemade soups, salads and even some graffiti.

episodes.name: Guy's Hometown Tour
episodes.overview:
Hotel Ivanhoe • Ferndale Meat Co. • The Awesome Pretzel Co. • Clendenen's Cider Works (Fortuna, Calif.) • Loleta Cheese Factory (Loleta, Calif.) • Humboldt Sweets Bakery and Cafe

On this special, hourlong trip, Guy's taking us on a tour of Ferndale, Calif., which is not only his hometown, but one of many small towns in Humboldt County with righteous food and a whole lotta flair. There's the generations-old apple orchard with a special place in Guy's heart, to the local's watering hole where Guy first experienced work life in the kitchen; the old-school butcher and the artisan cheese maker. This is a super chef's hometown tour you won't wanna miss!

episodes.name: All Things New York
episodes.overview:
Queen's Comfort (Astoria, Queens, N.Y.) • Black Tree (Manhattan, N.Y.) • Paul's Live from New York (Eureka, Calif.).

This trip, Guy's gettin' a taste of New York in and out of the Big Apple. In Queens, there's the filmmaker-turned-chef kickin' out killer dishes like spicy atomic fireballs and making his dreams come true with a life-changing question.  On New York's Lower East Side, the farm to table spot taking fresh and local to a whole new level, servin' up standout seasonal sammies like the winter pig.  And in Eureka, the Bronx-bred pizza maker bringing unique Neapolitan-style pies to northern California.

episodes.name: Big Time Bites
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's rolling up to some joints pullin' out all the stops. In New York's East Village, the neighborhood spot plating up a standout burger worthy of a four star review. In Eureka, Calif., the popular hangout servin' up all kinds of local favorites fired up in the righteous oven, from roasted oysters to wild mushroom cobbler. And in Ridgewood, N.Y., the rocking Vietnamese joint in an obscure industrial park kickin' out authentic dishes like banh xeo and suon nuong xa.

episodes.name: Keepin' It Real
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's gettin' into the heart of some long-standing traditions. In Miami, Fla., the Asian fusion spot delivering the bomb dot com Brussels sprouts and going all out ducky on the sous vide sammie. In Eureka, Calif., the soul food spot takin' a page out of grandma's cookbook with down home favorites like jerk fried chicken and shrimp and crawfish etouffee. And in midtown New York, the Italian pizza maker schooling Guy and Iron Chef Geoffrey Zakarian on the authentic Neapolitan technique behind standout pizzas like pistacchio e salsiccia and montanara starita.

episodes.name: Dynamite Duos
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's checking out some spots keepin' it all in the family. In New York's Lower East Side, the sibling spot starting at the very beginning — pickling, smoking, curing and fermenting, everything from the goat necks to chicken wings to pig ears. In Eureka, California the husband and wife team cranking out Mediterranean favorites like the lamb plate alongside bar standards like the pulled pork po' boy. And in Miami, Fla., the Southern-bred brother/sister duo servin' up grandma's lowcountry recipes with unique touches on favorites like whole fried snapper and beer braised baby back ribs.

episodes.name: Kickin' It in Key West
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's checking out some of the awesome eats of the island — Key West, Fla., that is. From a funky little shack servin' up New England seafood with coastal twists to a husband/wife team dishing up standout fish tacos just down the street. And a trip to this eclectic oasis wouldn't be complete without a stop to the teeny tiny food cart crankin' out hundreds of Asian/Caribbean fusion dishes a day.

episodes.name: From Meatballs to Lollipops
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's getting into a festival of flavorful faves. In Miami, Fla., the local watering hole puttin' a unique spin on standard bar food with the loaded chimi burrito and lobster lollipops. In Sandy, Utah, the mountain town favorite scratch-makin' everything from breads to smoked meats and a creative combos like Canadian bacon and potato croquettes and white bean and steak pizza. And in Salt Lake City, the New Jersey native serving up authentic Italian family recipes like the larger than life ten ounce meatball.

episodes.name: Cross Country Comfort Food
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's got the goods on stick-to-your-ribs knockouts from the ski slopes to the sea. In Miami, Fla., the law student who switched out his suit for a chef coat is killing it with all kinds of comfort food like spicy oxtail and big ragu. In Park City, Utah, the local boy serving low brow gourmet grub like the signature chivito club and chicken bowl with rice, and the mom and pop ski lodge keepin' the snow bunnies fed on flavorful favorites like pork osso buco, vegetarian mushroom stroganoff and crispy pork belly.

episodes.name: International Family Style
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's taking his place at the family table. In Holladay, Utah, the sibling-run Vietnamese joint serving up mom's legendary recipes for authentic dishes like pho and bahn mi, plus the wildly flavorful honey glazed pork vermicelli noodle buns. In Kailua, Hawaii, the brothers dedicating their lives to fulfilling dad's lifelong dream of having his own restaurant, and crankin' out island favorites like Hawaiian-style kalbi ribs and mochiko chicken. And in Salt Lake City, the Greek joint drawing inspiration from the family playbook and sourcing fresh ingredients straight from Greece for dishes like grilled octopus and righteous lamb tacos.

episodes.name: Island Flavor
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's cruisin' through Hawaii for an authentic taste of Oahu. In Waipahu, the family-run Filipino joint serving up scratch-made favorites straight outta mama's cookbook like the lechon special and pork adobo fried rice. In Aiea, the double-duty bowling alley/restaurant is keeping it funky with one of DDD's best-ever oxtail soups and the flavorful grilled turkey sandwich. And on the windward side of the island, in Kaneohe, the tiny authentic Hawaiian drive-in where a world-class chef is crankin' out crazy fresh fish like pan-fried ono and signature ahi cakes.

episodes.name: Grillin', Chillin' and Huli Huli Chicken
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's steppin' up to unique grills on the mainland and beyond. In Miami, Fla., the husband/wife duo serving up classic Americana with a 21st century twist like the smoky fried chicken and Buffalo-style pig wings. In Long Beach, Calif., the anything-but-average taco truck grilling steaks for the drunken torta and deep frying green chicken chilaquiles. And on Oahu, Hawaii, Guy's favorite rotisserie chicken joint cranking out the island's signature huli huli chicken.

episodes.name: Righteous Bites
episodes.overview:
Fat Sal's Deli (Los Angeles, Calif.) • Loulou's Griddle in the Middle (Monterey, Calif.) • The Alley Restaurant (Aiea, Oahu, Hawaii).

In the Westwood Village section of L.A., three New York buddies are crankin' out the kind of food they want to eat, including a monster "Fat Jerry" hero.  In Monterey, Calif., a former bait shop turned seafood grill dishin' up the bounty of this seaside county: fresh abalone sliders and a Dungeness crab feast. And in Aiea, Hawaii, a bowling alley spot with a gourmet twist servin' its famous oxtail soup.

episodes.name: California Cruisin'
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's cruisin' the west coast for a taste of California. In Culver City, Gene Simmons from Kiss makes a surprise visit to the neighborhood hangout dishing out real deal Hawaiian. Nearby in Garden Grove, the family-run Mexican joint serving up standout tamales and traditional beef chamorro. And up the coast in Monterey, the funky fish house grillin' up fresh-caught oysters and a full-flavored pasta-seafood medley.

episodes.name: Stuffed and Twisted
episodes.overview:
Sidewinders American Grill & Tavern (Jackson, Wyo.) • Rosine's Restaurant (Monterey, Calif.) • Blunch (Boston, Mass.)

This trip, Guy's checkin' out all kinds of funky foods from coast to coast. In  Wyoming, it's a spot where an ex-Marine's bringin' Americana to town with dishes like chicken pot pie and homemade soups and pretzels. In Monterey, there's the second-generation Italian joint servin' mom's time-tested recipes like meaty lasagna and real-deal minestrone. And in Boston, Guy hits a funky little sandwich shop pressin' panini to satisfy both meat and veggie lovers.

episodes.name: Old Standards, New Styles
episodes.overview:
Pinky G's Pizzeria (Jackson, Wyo.) • Starling Diner (Long Beach, Calif.) • Cannery Row Brewing Company (Monterey, Calif.).

This trip, Guy's hittin' up some spots serving comfort food kicked up a notch. In Wyoming, it's a pizza joint slicin' up mouthwatering pies topped with everything from pesto and chicken to spicy sausage and marinara. In the Belmont Heights neighborhood of Long Beach, there's the old-school diner with a new-school chef cookin' up home-style favorites like pot roast. And in Monterey, Guy's visitin' the brewhouse crankin' out big-time bar food like Parmesan pretzels and short rib grilled cheese.

episodes.name: From Standards to Standouts
episodes.overview:
Pèpe's Little Napoli (Carmel-by-the-Sea, Calif.) • Pica's Mexican Taqueria (Jackson, Wyo.) • The Factory Gastrobar (Long Beach, Calif.).

This trip, Guy's hitting up all kinds of killer joints, from classic Italian to modern Americana. In Carmel, a Cooking Channel host is along for the ride at an authentic Italian joint dishin' out tri-color cannelloni and fresh seafood cioppino. In Wyoming, a California chef brings his brand of legit Mexican to the mountains, like savory chicken sopes and one of Guy's favorite dishes, pozole. And in Long Beach, it's a Bixby Knolls neighborhood spot where a chef with artistic flair is servin' up some of her signature veggie sammies.

episodes.name: All Day Dining
episodes.overview:
Nora's Fish Creek Inn (Wilson, Wyo.) • Tavern on 2 (Long Beach, Calif.) • The Wild Plum Café & Bakery (Monterey, Calif.).

This trip, Guy's getting a taste of every meal from dawn to dusk. Just west of Jackson Hole, there's the Wilson, Wyoming log cabin-turned-restaurant cookin' up a banana bread French toast mash-up and classic beef stroganoff.  In the Belmont Shore area of Long Beach, the hidden-gem gastropub marryin' pork belly with octopus and servin' up slam-dunk short ribs. And in Monterey, the Old Town neighborhood spot keepin' it local, sustainable, and scratch-made with apple pancakes, three-pork porchetta, and more.

episodes.name: Legends of Texas
episodes.overview: In this one-hour special, Guy's cruising the Lone Star State for a big bite of Texas-style Triple D. From gumbo to Greek, pizza to burgers and tasty twists from Dallas to Houston. We're reuniting with some familiar faces along the way, cooking killer chicken casserole with Matthew McConaughey and chowing down with football legend Earl Campbell. Plus, we're opening the vault to head back to a classic from the first DDD episode ever.

episodes.name: Roadtrippin' in Beantown
episodes.overview:
Lone Star Taco Bar (Allston, Mass.) • Deep Ellum (Allston, Mass.) • Cafe Polonia (South Boston, Mass.).

This trip, Guy's parking the Camaro in Beantown for an all-Boston smorgasbord. Just outside the city in the Allston suburbs, two restaurants sharin' one kitchen cookin’ up totally different menus: Mexican street food on one side and gastropub standouts, like killer gravlax and dynamite chicken sausage on the other. Then in the Polish Triangle in South Boston, Guy’s joined by Anthony Shriver, founder of Best Buddies International, and former NFL player Dan Koppen at an authentic old-country spot dishin’ out righteous pierogi and a fried pork favorite.

episodes.name: Seriously Saucy
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's toppin' off some righteous dishes with all kinds of sauce. In Cincinnati, the funky cafe putting their creative spin on barbecue chicken and vegan chili. In Boston, the neighborhood spot spicing up everything from lemongrass chicken to sloppy Joe's with some killer specialty sauces. And in Jackson, Wyo., the century-old log cabin housing an eclectic menu of totally homemade standouts, like scratch-made ramen and pork ragu.

episodes.name: Cross-Country Classics
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's roadtrippin' all over the country for some home-style cooking. In Boston, the funky neighborhood joint cranking out Southern staples, like chicken and waffles and off-the-hook tots. In Carmel, Calif., Robert Irvine's riding shotgun to check out the cool cafe centered around scratch-made classics, like amped-up biscuits and gravy and brisket chili. And in Superior, Wis., the sports bar scoring with classics like house-cured meat pizza and a super special chicken sandwich.

episodes.name: Worldwide Flavorfest
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's getting a taste of global flavor. In Cincinnati, the Jamaican joint firing up their trademark jerk chicken and spicy snapper. In Boston, the lunch-only spot serving a full plate of authentic Italian, like porcini cascioni and rosettes. And in Duluth, the flavorful border dweller dishin' out a taste of Thailand with dishes like the Bangkok burrito and a killer lamb curry.

episodes.name: Small Town Standouts
episodes.overview:
The Kounty Quarthouse (Parkland, Wis.) • Lotus Cafe (Jackson, Wyo.) • Junkyard Extreme Burger & Brats (Lancaster, Ore.)

This trip, Guy's rollin' out to some small towns with big flavor. In rural Wisconsin, a roadside bar servin' sandwiches stuffed with the bomb brisket and crispy pork belly. In Wyoming ski country, an organic spot dishin' out ethnic-inspired eats, like an Asian bison bowl and Thai curry soup. And in rural Oregon, a farmland favorite firin' up monster burgers and their unique twist on pizza.

episodes.name: One Street Wonders
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's headed to Cincinnati to three righteous restaurants all sitting pretty on one street. First, the funky pub where a husband/wife duo's dishing out all kinds of creative hot dogs and sammies. Then, a real deal Belgian spot cooking up legit waffles and beer cheese pretzels. And, the Southwestern spot servin' up short rib tacos and a killer chicken torta.

episodes.name: Old School Joints
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's getting a taste of yesteryear. In Duluth, the Italian market/restaurant stacking up hearty homemade lasagna and a monster muffaletta. In Eugene, Ore., DDD's first all-vegan spot serving their signature tofu sammy and frozen peanut butter pie. And in Delta, Wis., the real deal retro diner dishing out righteous red-eye gravy and a surprising spin on the pancake, where he's joined by Jimmy John Liautaud and his family.

episodes.name: Meat in the Middle
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's grabbing dishes stacked and stuffed with off-the-hook goodness. In Baltimore, the cozy pasta bar rolling out righteous ravioli and topping things off with killer clams. In Eugene, Ore., the sandwich food truck creating a meaty, cheesy masterpiece and a double dose of pork. And in Cable, Wis., the small town favorite charging up their barbecue with espresso and firing up creme brulee French toast.

episodes.name: Soup-Centric
episodes.overview:
Sláinte (Baltimore, Md.) • Soup Nation (Eugene, Ore.) •  Phở Lang Thang (Cincinnati, Ohio)

This trip, Guy's fillin' up on some serious soup. In Baltimore, an authentic Irish pub servin' up seafood gumbo and a corned beef and cabbage twist. In Oregon, a college-town joint dishin' out 80 kinds of soup, from Middle Eastern lamb to Peruvian pork and quinoa. And in Cincinnati, a Vietnamese spot in the Findlay Market crankin' out phenomenal phở and turnin' bánh mì on its head.

episodes.name: All Baltimore, All the Time
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's hitting the pavement for a tasty tour of Baltimore. First, just off Dundalk Ave, the local legend cranking out all kinds of crab plates. Then in the Hamilton neighborhood, the farm-to-table spot cooking up bacon-wrapped meatloaf and Asian braised pork. And in the Upper Fells Point neighborhood, the funky pizza joint firing up some outta bounds pies and savory risotto balls.

episodes.name: Chicken Chowfest
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's filling up on winner winner chicken dinners. In Baltimore, the local landmark dishing out wicked wings alongside a killer steak wrap. In Eugene, Ore., the soul food joint smoking the bomb barbecue bird and slinging their signature burger. And in Des Moines, the Southern spot serving up legit fried chicken and decadent red velvet waffles.

episodes.name: Fresh Fish & Funky Chicken
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's hittin' the road for some outrageous seafood and tasty bird. In Des Moines, the trophy-winning barbecue joint smokin' up all kinds of unique wings and dishing out an out-of-bounds apple dumpling dessert. Across town in West Des Moines, a real deal Ecuadorian spot cookin' up authentic specialties like chicken with rice and pork with hominy. And in Eugene, Ore., the seafood market serving up totally fresh caught Dungeness crab and a legit Cajun crawfish pie.

episodes.name: Oldies But Goodies
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's hitting up some legit local landmarks. In Des Moines, the historic drive-in famous for their nearly century-old chili recipe. In Leeds Point, N.J., the scenic seaside joint serving up fresh catch since the 1930s. And in Brigantine, N.J., the old-school butcher shop cranking out righteous homemade sausage and real deal jerky.

episodes.name: Fish, Fries and Feet
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's tackling everything from land to sea. In Des Moines, the funky fusion joint serving up unique burritos alongside off-the-chain bulgogi masa fries. Across town in the Beaverdale area of Des Moines, the Southern spot cooking up all the classics, from ribs and red beans and rice to catfish cakes and collards. And in Atlantic City, the husband-wife duo dishing out soul food standouts like turkey chops and pig feet.

episodes.name: Cruisin' the Italian Countryside
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's taking a tasty tour through Tuscany, Italy. In Montecatini Alto, the hillside seafood spot serving up a squid ink specialty and a Mediterranean prawn-artichoke mashup. To the west in Collodi, Guy swings through the "birthplace of Pinocchio" to reunite with an old buddy dishing out legit spaghetti and outrageous lamb. Then, Guy's headed south for a bucket list experience of truffle hunting in the mountains of San Miniato. And finally to Lucca for one last stop, at a true Tuscan joint cooking up all kinds of totally fresh pasta with mussels and an out of bounds oxtail tortelli.

episodes.name: Fillin' up in Florence
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's hitting up totally traditional Italian spots in Florence, Italy. First, the 50-year-old landmark serving up their legendary spaghetti specialty and some crazy good chicken. Then, the second generation spot reeling in the awards and cranking out all kinds of totally fresh pasta. And finally, the popular pizza place sharing their Italian dough-making secrets and cooking up a legit salami-cheese calzone.

episodes.name: Arizona All-Stars
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's heading southwest for a flavor-filled tour of sunny Arizona. First, the real deal Italian market making an authentic beef specialty straight from the mother country. Also in Scottsdale, a pitstop at the funky gas station/barbecue cafe dishin' out the bomb brisket alongside a host of handcrafted fuel — yes, fuel. And in Phoenix, the out-of-the-box burger joint serving up all kinds of crazy culinary creations.

episodes.name: Roadtrippin’
episodes.overview:
The Anchorage (Somers Point, N.J.) • Sal’s Gilbert Pizza (Gilbert, Ariz.) • Salty’s BBQ & Catering (Bakersfield, Calif.)

This trip, Guy's headin’ coast to coast and north to south. In New Jersey, a legendary spot dishin' out righteous crab-stuffed flounder and a legit spin on cannelloni. In Arizona, a mom and pop pizza place tossin’ pies topped with everything from baked ziti to chicken marsala. And in Bakersfield, a joint dishin’ out sunshine and down-home specialties, like tri tip and grilled chicken worthy of a road trip.

episodes.name: From Atlantic to Pacific
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's gettin' a far out taste of both coasts. In Bakersfield, Calif., the 75-year-old steakhouse firing up savory stuffed pork chops and legit lobster mac 'n cheese. Across town, the Latin-American fusion joint cranking out chicken and tri-tip with a south-of-the-border spin. And in Somers Point, N.J., the sandwich spot serving up all kinds of crazy combos, like a killer crab melt and the bomb pork belly reuben.

episodes.name: Globe Tasting
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's getting an authentic taste of all ends of the earth. In Bakersfield, Calif., the firehouse-turned-restaurant firing up Latin-fusion favorites like basque lamb tacos and popcorn pork with a side of zing. In Northfield, N.J., an Italian spot servin' all kinds of authentic specialties like grandma's pizza and homemade pappardelle pasta. And in Phoenix, the funky Thai joint dishing out off-the-hook dumplings and coconut Asian pork.

episodes.name: Sweet, Savory and Saucy
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's taste buds are in for a culinary adventure. In Bakersfield, Calif., the classic cafe dishing out meaty Texas chili and decadent pumpkin pancakes. Across town, the hidden gem piling up a peanut butter burger alongside all kinds of delicious desserts, like homemade "Bacon Love" ice cream. And in Phoenix, the gourmet taco spot mixing up a mean mole.

episodes.name: To Bakersfield and Beyond
episodes.overview:
Athena's Greek Cafe and Bakery (Bakersfield, Calif.) • Pyrenees Café (Bakersfield, Calif.) • Asian Experience (Taft, Calif.)

This trip, Guy's givin' some love to a little town with a lot of flavor. In Bakersfield's Rosedale neighborhood, a Greek place cookin' up authentic comfort foods like cabbage dolmades and braised beef over pasta. Across town, a landmark Basque joint servin' garlic fried chicken and a four-course meal with outrageous oxtail.  And west of town in Taft, the funky Asian joint dishin' out killer pad Thai and a favorite called tom yum kung.

episodes.name: Racing Through Charlotte
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's checkin' out high octane joints in Charlotte, N.C., with NASCAR driver Clint Bowyer. First, the relocated Triple-D alum dishing out dynamite burgers and a unique spin on shrimp. Then, the go-kart track serving revved-up sandwiches like steak with fig preserves and smoking hot chicken. And parked at the Charlotte Speedway, the funky food truck firing up tasty flavors like chana masala tacos and buffalo cauliflower sliders.

episodes.name: Indulgent Dishes
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's indulging himself in righteous, rich recipes. In Charlotte, N.C., the crazy seafood spot reeling in off-the-hook gumbo and a spicy mahi mahi specialty. Across town, the mother-daughter team serving up savory lamb ragout and a decadent ice cream sandwich. And in Los Angeles, the Korean-German combo firing up drunken chicken and a killer burger, where he's joined by NFL player Julian Edelman.

episodes.name: Griddles and Vittles
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's headed west for barbecue and beyond. In Los Angeles, the food court gem grilling up homemade chorizo and a Yucatan turkey special. Then, in Las Vegas, two funky joints firing up the grill and slinging dishes that'll have you licking your chops ... and your fingers.

episodes.name: Intercontinental Flavorfest
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's hittin' up world flavors tucked away in the USA. In L.A.'s Chinatown, a New Orleans-inspired joint cookin' up Big Easy po' boys and legit crawfish mac & cheese. In nearby East L.A., a Korean-Mexican mashup servin' short rib tacos and spicy pork chimichangas. And in Charlotte, a Serbian pizza place dishin' out Eastern European-style calzones and a stuffed cabbage delicacy.

episodes.name: A Bowlful of Soul
episodes.overview:
Tubs Fine Chili & Fancy Fixin's (Culver City, Calif.) • Crêpe Expectations (Las Vegas, Nev.) • Mert's Heart and Soul (Charlotte, N.C.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's going all in for some comfort and soul. In Culver City outside LA., Marc Summers and "Law and Order: SVU" star Dann Florek join Guy at the mom and pop shop firing up tasty turkey chili and dynamite dogs on cornbread buns. In Vegas, the standout strip mall spot stuffin' crêpes with everything from carne asada to sweet caramel apples.  And in Charlotte, the down-home hangout dishin' out low country favorites, like killer collard greens and standout shrimp and grits.

episodes.name: Taste of Asia
episodes.overview:
Osaka Japanese Bistro (Las Vegas, Nev.) • Fat Choy Asian American Fare (Las Vegas, Nev.) • Dae Gee Korean BBQ (Denver, Colo.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's gettin' a big taste of the Far East. First up, the original Vegas Japanese spot rollin' out serious sushi and traditional udon. Next, the Vegas winner dealin' out righteous pork belly bao and an Asian spin on grilled cheese. And  in Denver, the Korean barbecue joint firin' up the grill for a meaty all-you-can eat flavorfest.

episodes.name: Tri-Continent Cuisine
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's checking out killer cuisine spanning three different continents. In Denver, the unique quick service spot dishing out a creative take on Indian curry. Then in northwest Denver, the Brazilian bistro cooking up the bomb croquettes and an abundant seafood specialty. And in Atlanta, the folksy joint stacking mega meat into serious sandwiches.

episodes.name: From Biscuits to Brisket
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's digging in to stick-to-your-ribs comfort food. In Atlanta, the down-home joint cooking up righteous chicken and biscuits and house-cured lox, where he's joined by former NFL player Jamal Lewis. Across town, the twin-brother team firing up Southern grub like brisket burger and chicken-fried ribs, where he meets up with TV host Rutledge Wood. And in Fort Collins, Colo., the funky cafe serving up vegetarian specialties like tomatillo and chickpea pizza and a savory cauliflower steak.

episodes.name: Homeland Favorites
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's celebrating homeland favorites from all kinds of diverse cultures. In Richfield, Minn., the Mexican restaurant-market combo dishing out real-deal tacos al pastor and carnitas tamales. In Denver, the Greek joint cooking up lights-out lamb ribs and a unique dessert specialty. And in Atlanta, the Southern spot serving up their spin on shrimp and grits, plus legit biscuits and gravy.

episodes.name: Name That Kitchen
episodes.overview:
The Lodge Sasquatch Kitchen (Fort Collins, Colo.) • Pickle Jar Kitchen (Falmouth, Mass.) • Dana’s Kitchen (Falmouth, Mass.)

This trip, Guy's checkin' out righteous spots that say a lot in the name. In the Colorado mountains, an NFL pro and a Triple-D alum are teamin’ up on gangster green chili and mile-high burgers. In Falmouth, Mass., a quaint breakfast-lunch café puttin’ out perfect pickle chips and savory scone sandwiches. And just north of Falmouth, a family-owned culinary oasis servin’ local soft-shell crab and hearty kale soup.

episodes.name: Beef It Up
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's divin' into menus boasting the bomb beef. In Minneapolis, the neighborhood gastropub serving up serious sandwiches piled with steak and braised beef. In Atlanta, the Jewish deli putting out a fish specialty alongside killer pastrami hash, where he's joined by his chef friend G. Garvin. And in Plymouth, Mass., the funky cafe dishin' out unique cheesesteak pretzels and a twist on traditional shepherd's pie.

episodes.name: By Hand and By Fork
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's digging into dynamite dishes and grabbin' some outrageous grub. In Denver, the Argentinian joint stuffing the bomb beef empanadas and a veggie tarta specialty. In Bayport, Minn., the family-run barbecue joint pilin' brisket into sandwiches and pulled pork onto plates. And in Falmouth, Mass., the homestyle spot dishing out a righteous Tex-Mex breakfast and loaded chicken sandwich.

episodes.name: Finger Lickin' Food
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri is eating up grub that doesn't require a knife and fork! In Atlanta, a funky old house turned brew pub cookin' up cheddarwurst corn dogs along with a knockout pastrami sandwich. In Minneapolis, an English-Filipino mashup serving the bomb banh mi and bacon onion dip. Then, in Woods Hole, Mass., a seafood spot dishing out mussels and lobster-stuffed cod.

episodes.name: Bite of Britain
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's livin' it up in London, digging into a real-deal regional feast. First, a couple of British buddies smoking up true blue American 'cue. Then, a hip hangout giving classic fish-n-chips a modern makeover. And Guy finds a taste of legit English fare at a locals' favorite, serving standout shepherd's pie, braised ox cheek, and righteous rhubarb cheesecake.

episodes.name: Piggin' Out
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's going big on the pig. In Colorado Springs, a funky food truck serving their pork fusion on loaded platters and Colombian arepas. In Minneapolis, an Asian joint tucked away in a grocery store dishing out barbecued pork and pork belly ramen. And across town, a smokehouse firin' up killer wings and a hearty porchetta sandwich.

episodes.name: Ultimate Turkey Fest
episodes.overview:
Mike's City Diner (Boston, Mass.) • Alpine Steak House (Sarasota, Fla.) • Funk-n-Waffles (Syracuse, N.Y.) • Golden Crown Panaderia (Albuquerque, N.M.) • Sammy's Food Service & Deli (New Orleans, La.) • Supino Pizzeria (Detroit, Mich.) • The Comet Cafe (Milwaukee, Wisc.) • Bocadillos (Albuquerque, N.M.) • The Pitts Again (Glendale, Ariz.)

This trip, Guy's revisitin' joints servin' up Thanksgiving feasts. In Boston, the diner roastin' stand-up turkeys. In Sarasota, a Thanksgiving legend: Turducken. Near Syracuse U. a basement dive crankin' out stuffing waffles. In Albuquerque, bakin' up a turkey-shaped bread. In the Big Easy, a Cajun-style Thanksgiving dinner complete with oyster stuffing. In the heart of Detroit, the City Wing Thing pizza featurin' smoked, pulled turkey legs. On Milwaukee's east side, complete-but-compact turkey dinners. Back in Albuquerque, a North Valley community favorite: a turkey avocado sammie. And a Glendale BBQ champion smokin' whole turkeys low and slow.

episodes.name: Isle-talian
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's cruisin' from east to west for a taste of Asian and Americana. In Washington D.C., a funky underground joint serving knockout dumplings and the bomb ramen. In Ocean City, New Jersey, a pizza parlor firin' up cheeseburger and chicken vodka pies. And in Colorado Springs, a comfort food cafe going big with their Rocky Mountain roast beef and king-sized cinnamon rolls.

episodes.name: Holiday Hoopla
episodes.overview: In this special hour-long episode, Guy's celebrating the holidays with dishes perfect for the Christmas and Hanukkah seasons. In Nashville, killer tamales and a sugar-glazed knockout. Then, from Florida to California totally-legit matzo balls, latkes, cabbage and knishes.  And in North Pole Alaska, traditional turkey with a sweet chaser.

episodes.name: East-West Flavorfest
episodes.overview: Guy's crusin' from the Atlantic to the Rocky Mountains for an East-West flavorfest of Asian and American cuisine. In Washington, DC, an underground joint turning ramen in to an art form. In Ocean City, New Jersey, a red-hot Italian spot firing up pizza with a twist. And in Colorado Springs, it's go big or go home... cookin'!

episodes.name: All Kinds of Meat
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy's digging into a meat lover's paradise. In Colorado Springs, a Jamaican joint dishing out killer curry goat and jammin' jerk chicken. In Baltimore, a funky beer bar serving up wild boar sliders and outrageous pork belly mac and cheese fries. And in Washington D.C., an uber-deli carvin' up homemade pastrami and rolling out a meat-filled Moroccan specialty.

episodes.name: Family Legacies
episodes.overview:
Front Range Barbeque & Home Style Meals (Colorado Springs, Colo.) • Sam's Rialto Grill (Pleasantville, N.J.) • Miss Shirley's Cafe (Baltimore, Md.)

This trip, Guy's visiting spots keepin' up with their family ties. In Colorado Springs, southern family recipes mark a barbecue spot piling up a "sloppy pig" sandwich and scratch-made meatloaf. In Pleasantville, N.J., a wife carries on her husband's legacy with his down-home chicken and waffles and righteous ribs. And in Baltimore, an inherited breakfast-lunch joint still servin' up noteworthy coconut cream French toast and crab cake po' boys.

episodes.name: Between the Bread
episodes.overview:
Bub and Pop's (Washington, D.C.) • Skirted Heifer (Colorado Springs, Colo.) • Vagabond Kitchen & Tap House (Atlantic City, N.J.)

This trip, Guy's grabbin' grub piled high on bread and buns. In D.C., The '68 Camaro stops by a family-run sandwich shop servin' up a killer corned beef hoagie and lights-out porchetta. In Colorado Springs, it's a funky joint going scratch-made and local with a Pueblo chili burger and a hangover specialty. And in Atlantic City, there's a neighborhood pub pullin' off knockout grub like a pork and brisket sandwich and savory tequila shrimp.

episodes.name: Smoke and Seafood
episodes.overview:
The Fish House (Key Largo, Fla.) • The Smoking Swine (Baltimore, Md.) • Islamorada Shrimp Shack (Islamorada, Fla.)

This trip, Guy's firin' up the smoker and divin' into seafood. First up: a Key Largo market and restaurant smokin' up fantastic fish dip and puttin' out their own savory seafood specialties. In Baltimore, a food truck dishin' out killer barbecued pulled pork and righteous ribs. Then back to Florida where an Islamorada seaside shack is servin' standout shrimp fritters and doctorin' up Guy's own fresh catch.

episodes.name: International Appeal
episodes.overview:
Green Papaya Food Truck (Stockton, Calif.) • El Nuevo Frutilandia (San Francisco, Calif.) • DiGiorgio's Café Largo (Key Largo, Fla.)

This trip, Guy's goin' on a nationwide international flavor-fest. In Stockton, Calif., a funky food truck dishin' out a taste of Southeast Asia with homemade rice noodle soup. Down the road in San Fran, a neighborhood legend servin' up Puerto Rican and Cuban favorites. Then it's cross-country to Key Largo, where a real-deal Italian joint is cookin' up outrageous veal and hearty truffle mac and cheese.

episodes.name: Tacos, Turtles and Tri-Tip
episodes.overview:
Cosecha Cafe (Oakland, Calif.) • Green Turtle Inn (Islamorada, Fla.) • Midtown Creperie (Stockton, Calif.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's crossin' the country eatin' up an eclectic mix. In Oakland, a real-deal Mexican joint piling up pork belly tacos and carne adovada in a high-energy marketplace. In the Florida Keys, an Islamorada landmark that's been dishin' out their trademark turtle soup for decades. And in Stockton, Calif., a New Orleans-inspired spot serving savory crêpes and a saucy twist on traditional beignets.

episodes.name: Succulent Sandwiches
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diggin' into succulent sandwiches! In Oakland, a real-deal butchery stacking up killer cheesesteak and off-the-chain chicken. In Modesto, Calif., a funky food truck putting pastrami on pretzel bread and cooking pulled pork in root beer. And in Key Largo, Fla., a seafood staple servin' up a sandwich that's become a local legend.

episodes.name: Hot Meat and Cool Veg
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's firing up meaty meals and veggie specialties. In Modesto, Calif., a funky spot servin' up Portuguese sausage and a lights-out lamb burger. In Oakland, a vegan joint with outrageous okra gumbo and a meatless spin on succulent sandwiches. And in Islamorada, Fla., a carnivore's paradise dishin' out wicked wings and righteous pork rinds.

episodes.name: South Beach Sizzle
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri is hitting culinary hot spots in South Beach, Fla. First, a real-deal taqueria servin' up scratch-made tortillas and grasshopper tacos. Then, an authentic German joint cooking up standout sauerbraten and killer currywurst, where he's joined by chef friend Carl Ruiz. Plus, a poolside oasis dishin' out legit paella and homemade linguine.

episodes.name: Smoked, Grilled and Fried
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diggin' into all kinds of meat: out of the smoker, on the grill, and into the fryer. In Miami, a legit charcuterie dishing up wild boar sausage and house-cured bacon, where he's joined by former Major Leaguer Charles Johnson. In Modesto, Calif., a funky joint making monster tacos and a sweet and savory waffle. And in Stockton, Calif., an ex-NFL player slingin' wings that score with the sauce.

episodes.name: Cruisin' in Cuba
episodes.overview:
El Figaro (Old Havana, Cuba) • Nazdarovie (El Malecón, Havana, Cuba) • Fonda la Paila (El Vedado, Havana, Cuba)

This trip, Guy Fieri's is cruisin' the food scene in Cuba. First, a spot that payin' homage to Cuba's most famous chef - Gilberto Smith Duquesne - by cookin' up his trademark lobster in coffee sauce and pork Camagüeyano. Then, a Soviet joint servin' authentic Russian ravioli and rich chicken Kiev. And an outdoor "paladar" grillin' up righteous ribs and lamb-stuffed plantains.

episodes.name: Havana Hot Spots
episodes.overview:
Al Carbon (Havana, Cuba) • La Catedral (El Vedado, Havana, Cuba) • Casa Abel (Esquare San Nicolas, Havana, Cuba)

This trip, Guy Fieri's hittin' up the hot spots in Havana, Cuba. First, a neighborhood joint cookin' up house-cured lamb and freshly-caught snapper. Next, a house-turned-restaurant dishin' out savory goat stew and Chinese fried rice. And a cigar-lovers' haven servin' specialties like "drunk chicken" and pork with plantains.

episodes.name: Great Gear
episodes.overview:
Gian's Deli (Stockton, Calif.) • CatHead's BBQ (San Francisco, Calif.) • The Outrigger Pizza Company (Kihei, Maui, Hawaii)

This trip, Guy Fieri is grabbing grub cooked up with some great gear. First up: in Stockton, Calif., a multi-generational Italian deli makin' ravioli on an amazing century-old machine. Then in San Fran, a place firin' up lights-out lamb and huge pork biscuits in some of the city's last indoor smokers.  And on Maui, a mobile pizza oven puttin' out island twists on meaty pies.

episodes.name: Pizza Party
episodes.overview: From classic Italian in Anaheim to elk sausage in Idaho, Guy rounds up the ultimate pizza party all over the nation, in this special pie-palooza of pizza joints

episodes.name: Soakin' Up Maui
episodes.overview:
Da Kitchen Café (Kahului, Maui, Hawaii) • Fat Daddy's Smokehouse (Kihei, Maui, Hawaii) • Like Poke? (Kahului, Maui, Hawaii)

This trip, Guy Fieri's cruisin' the Valley Isle with buddy Chef Reno Henriques. First up: on the Haha Highway near the airport, a real-deal taste of regional favorites like loco moco and kalbi ribs. Then in Kihei, a legit barbecue joint smokin' up St. Louis-style ribs and "the bomb" burnt ends. And a Kahului food truck on the road to Haleakala dishin' out the freshest catch served raw, baked and even deep-fried.

episodes.name: Asia, Africa and India
episodes.overview:
Belly & Snout (Los Angeles, Calif.) • Radio Africa & Kitchen (San Francisco, Calif.) • Gandhi Mahal (Minneapolis, Minn.)

This trip, Guy's goin’ international with flavors from Asia, Africa and India. In L.A.’s Koreatown, a funky fast Filipino joint spicin' up hot dogs and pilin’ pork adobo on grilled cheese. In San Fran, a Triple-G competitor addin’ Ethiopian flair to jambalaya and today’s fresh catch. And in Minneapolis, a lights-out Indian joint killin' it with classics like tikka masala and naan.

episodes.name: Creole, Cold Cuts and Crepes
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's cookin' up everything from creole to cold cuts to crazy Asian crepes. First, a multi-generational joint bringing New Orleans to Los Angeles with off-the-hook gumbo and etouffee. In Minneapolis, a unique deli stacking sandwiches with vegan turkey, vegan cheese and Italian meat-free "meats." And in Maui, Hawaii, a noodle spot dishin' out righteous ramen and off-the-chain Vietnamese crepes.

episodes.name: Chew and Brew
episodes.overview:
The Local (Coral Gables, Fla.) • Surley Brewing Company (Minneapolis, Minn.) • Delancey Pizzeria & Bar (Hollywood, Calif.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's grabbin' grub cooked up at brew pubs! In Coral Gables, Guy's joined by "K.C." Casey from KC and the Sunshine Band at a craft drink and beer joint servin' southern favorites like hen and dumplings. In Minneapolis, a big-time brewery is cookin' up dishes like righteous pulled pork and a killer brisket sandwich.  And in Hollywood, an Italian spot is dishin' out mega-meat pizza and wild boar gnocchi.

episodes.name: Global Greats
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's going global with international flavors. In Maui, Hawaii, a funky sushi joint serving up righteous rolls and ice cream made with a local favorite. In Los Angeles, a 70-year-old Italian spot servin' up their legendary spins on pizza and lasagna.

episodes.name: Sausage, Seafood and Shawarma
episodes.overview:
Red Wagon Pizza Company (Minneapolis, Minn.) • STREET Eat Drink 360° (Portsmouth, N.H.) • Ivan's Cookhouse (North Miami Beach, Fla.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's taking an eclectic, global-infused tour of Flavortown. In Minneapolis, a neighborhood Italian spot carryin' on family pizza-makin' traditions with a bit of fun. Then, in New Hampshire, a funky joint puttin' their own spin on street food from around the world. And in Miami, a champion chef cookin' Haitian classics like griot, snapper and octopus.

episodes.name: Cosmopolitan Comfort
episodes.overview:
Prairie Dogs (Minneapolis, Minn.) • Moxy (Portsmouth, N.H.) • Azla Ethiopian Vegan (Los Angeles, Calif.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's grabbing all kinds of cosmopolitan comfort food.  In Minneapolis, an over-the-top hot dog spot loadin' up with beef, sausage and even lamb poutine. In New Hampshire, a righteous joint puttin' a New England spin on corned beef and cabbage, plus a fresh take on stroganoff. And in L.A., a mother-daughter team dishin' out authentic Ethiopian specialties.

episodes.name: Burgers, Buns and Bagels
episodes.overview:
Bagel Street Grill (Plainsboro Township, N.J.) • The Bun Shop (Los Angeles, Calif.) • The Kitchen (Portsmouth, N.H.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's pickin' up everything from burgers to buns to bagels. Near Princeton, a world-class bagel shop spicin' up their specialty and toppin' things off with Jersey's famous pork roll. In L.A., a Koreatown favorite loadin' up Asian buns and a unique bacon-corn bar dish. And in New Hampshire, an amped-up deli servin' lights-out lamb burgers and righteous ribs.

episodes.name: Big Food, Small Towns
episodes.overview:
Tuckaway Tavern & Butchery (Raymond, N.H.) • Vincentown Diner (Vincentown, N.J.) • Rocky Hill Inn (Rocky Hill, N.J.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's stopping in small towns to dig in to big-time eats. In New Hampshire, a blow-your-mind butchery loadin' up burgers and crankin' out scratch-made corn dogs. In Vincentown, N.J., a multi-generational diner makin' mile-high meatloaf and killer French toast. And stayin' in Jersey, a 1700s-era inn-turned-gastropub near Princeton dishin' out a twist on burgers and a funky spin on fries.

episodes.name: From Port to Port
episodes.overview:
Vida Cantina (Portsmouth, N.H.) • P's & Q's Market (Portland, Ore.) • Ataula (Portland, Ore.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's going coast-to-coast for righteous flavor. In New Hampshire, a modern cantina puttin' out the pork - from belly tacos to a pig's head platter. In Portland, a Woodlawn Park neighborhood market cookin' up grandma's take on biscuits and gravy, plus a funky polenta sandwich.  And in northwest Portland, a husband-and-wife relivin' the Spanish food he grew up with, servin' outrageous octopus and other creative tapas.

episodes.name: Turkey-giving
episodes.overview:
Jammin' Crêpes (Princeton, N.J.) • Forty Five Market Street Bakery & Cafe (Somersworth, N.H.) • The Table Cafe (Louisville, Ky.,)

This trip, Guy Fieri is dishin' out the spirit of Thanksgiving! In Princeton, Rev Run jumps in at a crêpe place servin' their take on a turkey club and a 20-layer cake. In New Hampshire, a hometown spot cookin' up terrific turkey meatloaf and killer haddock sandwiches. And in Louisville, a spot dishin' out rockstar food to the community, with a "pay-what-you-can" mission.

episodes.name: Brunch, Bologna and Burgers
episodes.overview:
Gralehaus (Lexington, Ky.) • Grind Burger Kitchen (Louisville, Ky.) • The Original Dinerant (Portland, Ore.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's grabbin' everything from brunch to burgers! In Lexington's Highlands neighborhood, an old-house-turned-bed-and-breakfast-lunch-spot crankin' out southern comfort, like fried bologna sandos. Then on to Lexington's NuLu area, where an eclectic joint's cookin' up pork belly Cubans and killer veggie burgers. And in Portland, a diner/restaurant mashup dishin' out chicken and waffles with a kick and decadent donut sliders.

episodes.name: Carnivore Creations
episodes.overview:
Tails & Trotters (Portland, Ore.) • Momma's Mustard, Pickles & BBQ (Louisville, Ky.) • Jersey Girl Café (Hamilton Township, N.J.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's gettin' right to the meat of the matter with some carnivore creations. In Portland, a bomb butchery puttin' out porchetta and a unique style of prosciutto. Next in Louisville, a righteous barbecue joint rubbin' down wings and ribs. And in suburban Jersey, a café dishin' their take on steak sandwiches and chicken panini.

episodes.name: Belly Up to Barcelona
episodes.overview:
Can Conesa (Plaça de Sant Jaume, Barcelona, Spain) • Pulpería A Gudiña (Eixample, Barcelona, Spain) • Cal Boter (Gràcia, Barcelona, Spain)

Guy Fieri crosses the Atlantic to dive into the many different cuisines of Barcelona. In Saint James Square, a bocadillo shop makin' all sorts of tasty Catalan sandwich specialties. In the Eixample district, an authentic Galician spot craftin' octopus tapas and other comfort food from northwest Spain. And in the Gràcia district, a mom-and-pop joint servin' up old-school Catalan cooking, including snails just like mom used to make.

episodes.name: A Sampling of Spain
episodes.overview:
El Pacífico (Barceloneta, Barcelona, Spain) • Can Vilaró (Sant Antoni, Barcelona, Spain) • Bar Morryssom (Eixample, Barcelona, Spain)

Guy Fieri travels to Barcelona, Spain, and digs into everything from top-notch tapas to traditional Catalan specialties.  In Little Barcelona, a beach-side joint servin' killer paellas with a twist. Then, across from the famous Sant Antoni Market, a family-run spot dishin' up authentic Catalan dishes including Cap i Pota — veal-head stew. And in l'Eixample de Gràcia, a family-owned bar is crankin' out tapas like quail in vinaigrette and chickpeas with prawns.

episodes.name: Mega Mouthfuls
episodes.overview:
Dolce & Clemente's (Robbinsville Township, N.J.) • The Seafood Lady (Louisville, Ky.) • Matt's BBQ (Portland, Ore.)

Guy unhinges his jaw for some mega-mouthful meals. In New Jersey, a real-deal Italian market cookin' up prosciutto bread and their multi-meat "boss of the sauce." In Louisville, a funky seafood spot pilin' their specialties on top of waffles. And in Portland, a killer barbecue food truck stackin' a fully-loaded "shabamwich."

episodes.name: Swiss, Sandwiches and Sausage
episodes.overview:
JJ's Red Hots (Charlotte, N.C.) • Swiss Hibiscus (Portland, Ore.) • Papi Queso Food Truck (Charlotte, N.C.)

Guy stops in Charlotte and Portland to sample grilled cheese sandwiches with a twist, made-from-scratch sausages and specialties straight out of Switzerland.

episodes.name: Beef, Lamb and Pig
episodes.overview:
Irish Rover (Louisville, Ky.) • Bang Bang Burgers (Charlotte, N.C.) • The Improper Pig (Charlotte, N.C.)

Guy Fieri hunts down all kinds of meaty favorites, starting in Louisville with an Irish pub's cottage pie. Then on to two very different stops in the Queen City: a burger joint addin' toppings like Southern-fave pimento cheese, and a funky Asian-barbecue fusion spot crankin' out spicy pulled pork and Asian slaw for "Chow Bao" tacos.

episodes.name: Kickin' It in Cancún
episodes.overview:
El Rincon de los Antojos (Nichupté, Cancún, Q.R., Mexico) • Mora Mora (El Centro, Cancún, Q.R., Mexico) • Guy Fieri's Kitchen + Bar (Playa del Carmen, Q.R., Mexico)

Guy heads south of the border to dig into local Mexican cuisine. First up, an authentic, family-owned spot where Grandma is cookin' up rellenos and killer chicharrón gorditas. Then, an eclectic downtown oasis servin' global mashups like an Asian-influenced pork belly burger and tuna tartare topped with Mayan xcat'ic chles - but you need a password to get in! Plus, get an inside look at a joint near and dear to Guy himself.

episodes.name: Not Your Typical Joints
episodes.overview:
Fu̅d at Salud Deli (Charlotte, N.C.) • Q-Shi (Spring, Tex.) • El Fish Fritanga (Zona Hoteliara, Cancún, Q.R., Mexico)

This trip, Guy's goin' off the beaten path to check out funky finds. In Charlotte, an eatery inside a beer store spinnin' up crazy waffle creations. North of Houston, a not-your-everyday fusion joint mashin' up barbecue with sushi. And Guy's headed back to Cancún, where they're dishin' out regional specialties fresh from the sea at a funky-cool hideout on Boulevard Kukulkan.

episodes.name: From North to South America
episodes.overview:
Pinchez Tacos (Avenida las Torres, Cancún, Q.R., Mexico) • Heist Brewery (Charlotte, N.C.) • The Original Marini's Empanada House (Houston, Tex.)

This trip, Guy's diggin' into flavors spannin' the Americas!  In Cancún, a joint with swagger is wood firin' street tacos with attitude. In the Queen City, a NoDa neighborhood brewery servin' up some bomb bacon jam burger sliders. And in Houston's West Chase section, a mom-and-pop shop crimpin' more than 80 different varieties of Argentinian empanada.

episodes.name: Goin' International
episodes.overview:
Cafe Lili Lebanese Grill (Houston, Tex.) • Cool Runnings Jamaican Grill (Houston, Tex.) • The Surfin' Burrito (Zona Hotelera, Cancún, Q.R., Mexico)

This trip, Guy Fieri grabs gangster global grub from a Jamaican joint in Houston and a 24-hour burrito hot spot in Cancun, Mexico.

episodes.name: Wonder Women
episodes.overview:
Irma's Original (Houston, Tex.) • Se7en Bites Bakeshop (Orlando, Fla.) • The Meatball Stoppe (Orlando, Fla.)

This trip, Guy Fieri visits all-female lineups that are rockin' the house. In midtown Houston, a long-time Mexican spot cookin' roast pork tamales to feed hungry Astros fans. In Orlando's Milk District, a bakery lookin' to fill your pie hole with scratch-made sweet and savory dishes.
