And staying in Orlando, an Italian joint servin' up Nonna's recipes for all kinds of meatballs.

episodes.name: Multicultural Cooking
episodes.overview:
Willie's Pinchos (Orlando, Fla.) • The Pastrami Project (Orlando, Fla.) • Cuchara Restaurant (Houston, Tex.)

This trip, Guy Fieri digs into the traditions of many different cultures including a Mexican joint in Houston and a Jewish deli-on-wheels in Orlando, Florida.

episodes.name: Turkeys, Taters and Dogs
episodes.overview:
Sherman's Deli & Bakery (Palm Springs, Calif.) • Mrs. Potato Restaurant (Orlando, Fla.) • Fat One's Hot Dogs and Italian Ice (Orlando, Fla.)

Guy digs into a righteous mashup of flavors across the country.  First up, a dynamite deli showcasin' real-deal latkes and turkey pastrami. Then in Orlando, a dishin' out hearty potato-centric Brazilian specialties including a carne seca rosti. And an Orlando destination in The Florida Mall keepin N'Sync with legit hot dog vibes.

episodes.name: Burgers, Beef and Barbecue
episodes.overview:
HoBo's BBQ (Temecula, Calif.) • Saigon Noodle and Grill (Orlando, Fla.) • Grill-a-Burger (Palm Desert, Calif.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's diving into the bomb beef and barbecue. In Orlando, Fla., an authentic Vietnamese spot serving phenomenal pho and a beefy specialty, where Guy is joined by Justin Warner. In Palm Springs, Calif., a not-your-typical burger joint dishing out their "Buddha Burger" and "Devil's Revenge." And in Temecula, Calif., a smokin' barbecue stop where they're even putting their 'cue into lasagna.

episodes.name: Chicken Trifecta
episodes.overview:
Fleetwood's on Front Street (Lahaina, Maui, Hawaii) • Thai Mee Up (Kahului, Maui, Hawaii) • Frank in Bun (South Palm Springs, Calif.).

This trip, Guy hits the road lookin' for the best chicken dinners. In Lahaina, Maui, rocker Mick Fleetwood's joint servin' up his mom's favorite chicken. Near the Maui airport, a Hawaiian-Thai food truck stuffin' their wings and fryin' their ribs. And in Palm Springs, a hot dog spot goin' meatless with their chili dog and puttin' a twist on chicken and waffles.

episodes.name: From Spicy to Icy
episodes.overview:
The Dirty Buffalo (Norfolk, Va.) • Down the Hatch (Lahaina, Maui, Hawaii) • Zobö & Meester's (Cathedral City, Calif.)

Guy heats up with spice and cools off with ice. In Norfolk, an Upstate New York transplant is dishin' out food he grew up with, like their namesake wings. Then on to paradise at a Maui spot chillin' out with tropical faves and fruity shave ice.  And outside Palm Springs, a Cathedral City joint servin' smoke and fire with sandwiches and other specialties.

episodes.name: Island and Desert
episodes.overview:
Wilma & Frieda (Palm Desert, Calif.) • Maui Brick Oven (Kihei, Maui, Hawaii) • Carib Shack (Virginia Beach, Va.)

Guy Fieri hunts down desert treasure and island flavor, starting with a breakfast-lunch cafe in Palm Desert, CA. Then he heads to a funky gluten-free spot in Maui, HI, and a crazy Caribbean joint in Virginia Beach, VA.

episodes.name: Sandwiches, Spaetzle and Sticky Wings
episodes.overview:
Pendulum Fine Meats (Norfolk, Va.) • Alkaline (Norfolk, Va.) • Brigit & Bernard's Garden Cafe (Kahului, Maui, Hawaii)

This trip Guy's spannin' the nation for outrageous dishes. In Norfolk Guy finds a two-for-one spot stackin' sandwiches in their market by day and firin' up ramen and sticky wings at night. And on Maui, a German-Swiss joint servin' Old World specialties like rouladen and apple strudel.

episodes.name: Flavor Adventure
episodes.overview:
Maui Fresh Streatery (Kahului, Maui, Hawaii) • Jessy's Tienda y Taqueria (Norfolk, Va.) • ediBOL (Los Angeles, Calif.)

Guy takes a culinary trip filled with adventurous flavor.  On Maui, a farm-to-table truck servin up global treats and Hawaiian eats. Then in Norfolk, a sibling-run market dishin' Mexican specialities. And a funky L.A. spot in the Arts District fillin' bowls with eclectic Asian-fusion yumminess.

episodes.name: Barbecue, Batter and Beer Can Chicken
episodes.overview:
Three's Bar and Grill (Kihei, Maui, Hawaii) • BatterFish (Los Angeles, Calif.) • Horse Thief BBQ (Los Angeles, Calif.)

This trip, Guy's all over the map lookin' for outrageous bites. On Maui a funky joint is fusin' Hawaiian, Pacific Rim, and Southwest cuisines for ridiculous ramen and the bomb beer can chicken. Then, a food truck parked in Santa Monica fryin' up off-the-hook fish and chips. And stayin' in L.A., a smokin' barbecue spot at Grand Central Market makin' killer fried chicken sandwiches.

episodes.name: Fun in the Sun
episodes.overview:
Big Wave Shrimp Truck (Haleiwa, Oahu, Hawaii) • Tiki Bar (Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico) • Chomp Chomp Nation (Orange County, Calif.) • Salty's BBQ & Catering (Bakersfield, Calif.) • Cravings (Duck, N.C.) • Curry Corner (Tempe, Ariz.) • Ted Peters Famous Smoked Fish (South Pasadena, Fla.)

On this extra-long trip, Guy soaks in the sunshine, grabbin' grub at outdoor hot spots and food trucks across the Americas.  First up: a North Shore Hawaiian shrimp truck and a classic Florida fish house.

episodes.name: Mex to the Max
episodes.overview:
Andale Taquería y Mercado (Richfield, Minn.) • Chichén Itzá Restaurant (Los Angeles, Calif.) • Los Taquitos Mexican Food Grill (Phoenix, Ariz.) • Lito's Take Out (Santa Barbara, Calif.) • Taco Bus (Tampa, Fla.) • Lone Star Taquería (Salt Lake City, Utah) • Espinos Mexican Bar & Grill (Chesterfield, Mo.) • California Tacos & More (Omaha, Neb.)

Guy Fieri's crossing the states to get some south of the border flavor. From Florida to California, he's diving into everything from tacos to tamales and tortas to pozole.

episodes.name: Ocean Coasts and Great Lakes
episodes.overview:
Meat Southern BBQ & Carnivore Cuisine (Lansing, Mich.) • La Tostadería Seafood (Los Angeles, Calif.) • The Grilled Cheese Bistro (Norfolk, Va.)

Guy goes from coast-to-coast and to the Great Lakes to dig up some dynamite dishes. In Michigan, an old-school heavy metal rocker smokin' meats for killer combinations. In L.A.'s Grand Central Market, a Mexican counter spot cookin' outrageous octopus tostadas. And in Norfolk, a downtown spot thinkin' up gourmet sandwiches like a lobster mac-and-cheese grilled cheese mashup.

episodes.name: A Passport of Flavor
episodes.overview:
Zaytoon Mediterranean (Lansing, Mich.) • La Panadería (San Antonio, Tex.) • Capital City BBQ (Lansing, Mich.)

Guy's cruisin' from Michigan to Texas for killer cuisine with international flair. On the west side of Lansing, a joint celebratin' their Middle Eastern heritage with amazin' shawarma and lamb-stuffed grape leaves. In downtown San Antonio, a Mexican bakery down the street from the Alamo bakin' artisan old-school sourdough loaves and tequila-almond croissants. And back in Lansing, a cell phone store with a Vietnamese-BBQ sit-down crankin' out brisket banh mi and humungous pork and shrimp spring rolls.

episodes.name: Amazing Asian
episodes.overview:
bún-ker Vietnamese (Ridgewood, Queens, N.Y.) • Blue Koi Noodles & Dumplings (Kansas City, Mo.) • Pok Pok (Portland, Ore.) • Oh Mai Vietnamese Sandwich Kitchen (Holladay, Utah) • HRD Coffee Shop (San Francisco, Calif.) • Wild Thaiger (Phoenix, Ariz.)

Guy takes a journey across the Pacific without ever leaving the States diving into Asian classics from Korean coffee in San Francisco to Vietnamese staples in New York.

episodes.name: Old Faces, New Places
episodes.overview:
Blackbrick Chinese & Dim Sum (Miami, Fla) • Fat Olives (Flagstaff, Ariz.) • Sunset Pointe (Fair Hope, Ala.)

This trip, Guy visits familiar Triple D faces to check out their new places. First, a funky Miami joint fusin' Sichuan and Hunan cuisines for Dan Dan noodles and bao buns. Then an Arizona primo pizza shop slingin' true Neapolitan pies.  And in Alabama, it's Panini Pete's killer new seafood spot dishin' up crazy dishes like grilled snapper throat.

episodes.name: From Pied to Fried
episodes.overview:
Bourrée Cajun Smokehouse (New Orleans, La.) • bu̅ya Izakaya | Ramen (St. Petersburg, Fla.) • Eastside Fish Fry & Grill (East Lansing, Mich.)

Guy Fieri digs into some righteous savory pie treats and deep-fried eats. In the Big Easy, an off-the-beaten-path joint smokin' spicy favorites like hot sausage meat pie and spicy shrimp boudin. In St. Petersburg, a Japanese-inspired gastropub servin' duck confit ramen charred shishito peppers. And in Michigan, a funky joint fryin' up frog legs and chicken gizzards.

episodes.name: All in the Family
episodes.overview:
Mike's Chili Parlor (Seattle, Wash.) • Tomahawk Barbeque (Vancouver, B.C., Canada) • Tufano's Vernon Park Tap (Chicago, Ill.) •  Brownstone Diner & Pancake Factory (Jersey City, N.J.) • Tune-Up Café (Santa Fe, N.M.) • Burger Bar (Roy, Utah)

On this extra-long trip, Guy's headin' to spots keepin' the business all in the family.  First up, a Seattle joint servin' great chili for generations. Over the border, the oldest family-run Vancouver spot dishin' out classics like roast beef with Yorkshire pudding. Back in the States, a Chicago neighborhood bar where a family's cookin' lemon chicken and other Italian faves. In New Jersey, a diner crankin' out killer pancakes and Greek classics straight from the heart. In Santa Fe, a husband-and-wife destination infusin' Salvadoran vibes into Southwest specials like chiles relleno. And west of Salt Lake, a '50s-era shack makin' drive-in classics like their signature Big Ben burger stacked high and onion rings with Utah's famous Fry Sauce.

episodes.name: Sammies and Spice
episodes.overview:
Loops (Columbus, Ohio) • Jitlada (Los Angeles, Calif.) • The Roost (Longmont, Colo.)

This roadtrip Guy's grabbin' standout sandwiches from savory to heat.  In Columbus, a brother-run joint bringing a taste of the Windy City to Ohio like Italian Beef.  In L.A.'s Thai Town, some Triple-G regulars showin' the way to southern Thai fire with green curry chicken. And in Colorado, two buddies are givin' profits back to the community while servin' up Bangin' Cauliflower and primo pork burgers

episodes.name: College-Town Champs
episodes.overview:
Pierogi Mountain at Café Bourbon Street (Columbus, Ohio) • Ray Ray's Hog Pit (Columbus, Ohio) • Aloy Thai Cuisine (Boulder, Colo.)

This trip, Guy's rollin' into college towns lookin' for A+ cuisine. In Columbus, an Ohio State punk bar with a hidden-gem pierogi paradise. Then, a Columbus-fave food truck crankin' out a monster brat burger from their self-raised premier swine. And a Boulder joint wowin' Colorado students with knockout Thai noodle dishes.

episodes.name: Breakfast, Brisket and Belly
episodes.overview:
Sweet Carrot (Columbus, Ohio) • Nighthawk Breakfast Bar (Venice Beach, Calif.) • Bootleggers Modern America Smokehouse (Scottsdale, Ariz.)

This trip, Guy digs into a meatapalooza. In Columbus' Grandview Heights neighborhood a funky joint servin' creative combos like Asian-flair chicken meatballs and a brisket corncake. In California, the late-night hangout all about breakfast dishin' out pork belly biscuit bao and drunken French toast. And in Arizona an old-town Scottsdale spot smokin' pork belly for killer dumplings.

episodes.name: Poutine, Pizza and Pork
episodes.overview:
SAMPLES Restaurant (Longmont, Colo.) • Slanted Rice Vietnamese Bistro (Scottsdale, Ariz.) • Tutta's Pizza (Dallas, Tex.)

This trip, Guy's divin into meaty masterpieces. In Colorado, a craft beer joint crankin' out poutine burgers and a Korean BBQ sandwich. In Scottsdale, a Triple-G alum steers Guy to a Vietnamese bistro mixin' up killer clay-pot chicken.  And in downtown Dallas, a warehouse hangout doin' a Texas Two Step mashin' up BBQ and pizza, including The Chipper - a roasted chicken and potato chip pie.

episodes.name: Mom's Kitchen
episodes.overview:
Republica Empanada (Mesa, Ariz.) • Zoe Ma Ma (Boulder, Colo.) • Ena's Caribbean Kitchen (Columbus, Ohio)

This trip, Guy Fieri's hitting the road and grabbing grub straight out of Mom's kitchen.  In Arizona, a family spot cookin' lights-out Latin cuisine, from Cubano empanadas to arroz con pollo. In Colorado, a mother-son team servin' up Chinese street food specialties like dan dan noodles and steamed buns. And in Columbus, a Jamaican joint grillin' up jerk chicken and other island favorites.

episodes.name: Delicious Discoveries
episodes.overview:
Mo Mo Ghar (Columbus, Ohio) • Nora Restaurant and Bar (Dallas, Tex.) • Tacos Mariachi (Dallas, Tex.)

This trip, Guy Fieri uncovers some surprising culinary discoveries. In Columbus, a hidden gem tucked away in a grocery store servin' out-of-bounds Nepalese-Tibetan specialties. Then in Dallas, a joint cookin' up lights-out dishes straight from Afghanistan. And stayin' in Dallas, a Mexican late-night spot dishin' up standout Tijuana seafood tacos and unique mole fries.

episodes.name: By Land and Sea
episodes.overview:
Grilled Cheese & Crab Cake Co. (Somers Point, N.J.) • Pinky's Westside Grill (Charlotte, N.C.) • Bizzarro Italian Cafe (Seattle, Wash.) • El Figaro (Old Havana, Cuba) • Northern Waters Smokehaus (Duluth, Minn.) • Darwell's Cafe (Long Beach, Miss.)

From bison pastrami and smoked white fish in Duluth, Minnesota, to clam linguine and elk ravioli in Seattle, Guy Fieri dives into joints servin' up spectacular surf and tasty turf.

episodes.name: Bird and Beef
episodes.overview:
Tacos Chiwas (Phoenix, Ariz.) • One90 Smoked Meats (Dallas, Tex.) • The Post Chicken & Beer (Longmont, Colo.).

This trip, Guy digs in to awesome bird and beef dishes. In Phoenix, a couple cookin' the flavors of Chihuahua including beef cheek barbacoa tacos. In East Dallas, a spot smokin' duck and pilin' on the spicy brisket. And in Colorado, a fried chicken emporium dishin' up their pressure-fried specialty with unique chicharrónes.

episodes.name: All Kinds of Comfort
episodes.overview:
Audrey Jane's Pizza Garage (Boulder, Colo.) • Whistle Britches (Dallas, Tex.) • Grubstak (Gilbert, Ariz.)

Guy Fieri dives in to all kinds of comfort cooking. In Phoenix, he visits a funky joint that's stacking up barbecue fries and putting a new spin on chilaquiles. In Colorado, he stops by a pizza place that's loading up the pies.

episodes.name: Pub Grub
episodes.overview:
Standard Tap (Philadelphia, Pa.) • Blackthorn Restaurant & Pub (Buffalo, N.Y.) • Johnny Rad's Pizzeria Tavern (Baltimore, Md.) • Highway 61 Roadhouse and Kitchen (St. Louis, Mo.) • Starlite Lounge (Blawnox, Pa.) • Brick (Kansas City, Mo.)

Guy's grabbin' all kinds of pub grub from chicken pie in Philadelphia and pizza in Baltimore to pierogis in Pennsylvania and an over-the-top dog in Kansas City, MO.

episodes.name: Rollin' in the Dough
episodes.overview:
Aloha Kitchen (Mesa, Ariz.) • Renee's Organic Oven (Tucson, Ariz.) • Mojo Donuts & Fried Chicken (Miami, Fla.)

Guy Fieri's diggin' into dishes featuring some dynamite dough from a legit Hawaiian joint in Arizona serving a meaty bun to a funky shop in Miami making artisan doughnuts.

episodes.name: International Intrigue
episodes.overview:
Zemam's (Tuscon, Ariz.) - crushcraft Thai Street Eats (Dallas, Tex.) - Milly's Empanada Factory (Miami, Fla.)

Guy crisscrosses the nation to grab some international grub from a funky Thai joint serving up noodles, curry and green papaya salad in Uptown Dallas to a family-run Venezuelan place dealing in empanadas in Miami.

episodes.name: West Coast Cookin'
episodes.overview:
Cosecha (Oakland, Calif.) • Little Napoli (Carmel-by-the-Sea, Calif.) • Loulou's Griddle in the Middle (Monterey, Calif.) • The Golden Bear (Sacramento, Calif.) • Cafe Rolle (Sacramento, Calif.) • The Front Porch (San Francisco, Calif.) • Putah Creek Cafe (Winters, Calif.)

On this trip, Guy Fieri's sticking to the West Coast and making all kinds of funky stops. From northern to southern Cali, he's diggin' into a mouth-watering variety of killer cuisine that's sure to please any palate.

episodes.name: Lights-out Latin
episodes.overview:
Ceviche's (Wilmington, N.C.) • Mr. & Mrs. Bun (Miami, Fla.) • Tumerico Cafe (Tuscon, Ariz.)

Guy Fieri dives into all kinds of amazing Latin specialties from Panamanian flavors in North Carolina and primo Peruvian sandwiches in Miami and a joint in Tucson putting a funky-fresh vegetarian spin on tacos and carne asada.

episodes.name: Pizza, Pork and Peru
episodes.overview:
The Copper Penny (Wilmington, N.C.) • The Cosmos (Lansing, Mich.) • Inca's Peruvian Cuisine (Tucson, Ariz.)

This trip, Guy Fieri digs into standout Philly sandwiches in North Carolina, out-of-this-world pizza with a surprise in Michigan, and real deal Peruvian specialties in Tucson.

episodes.name: All-American All-Stars
episodes.overview:
Shirley's Tippy Canoe (Troutdale, Ore.) • From Scratch Restaurant (Carmel-by-the-Sea, Calif.) • Dell Rhea's Chicken Basket (Willowbrook, Ill.)  • Lankford Grocery (Houston, Tex.) • Nora's Fish Creek Inn (Wilson, Wy.)• Whitner's Barbecue (Virginia Beach, Va.) • G & A Restaurant (White Marsh, Md.)

Guy Fieri is cruisin' the country and fillin' up on all-American all-stars, from East Coast Coney dogs to elevated mountain grub in the Rockies. He also gets a spicy taste of Texas and samples a hidden Northwestern gem.

episodes.name: Seafood and Savory
episodes.overview:
The Purple Carrot (Okemos, Mich.) •Chef Alisah's Restaurant (Tucson, Ariz.) • Something Fishy Seafood Restaurant (Wilmington, N.C.)

Guy grabs some off-the-hook seafood and savory sensations, from a Bosnian restaurant in Tucson, AZ, serving up Eastern European specialties to a down-home Southern spot frying up favorites in Wilmington, NC.

episodes.name: Grab and Grub
episodes.overview:
Rocco's Little Chicago (Tucson, Ariz.) • Doce Provisions (Miami, Fla.) • Fork N Cork (Wilmington, N.C.)

Guy Fieri's grabbing all kinds of grub, starting with a Chicago-style spot in Tucson firin' up deep-dish pie. In Miami, an NFL coaching legend is ridin' shotgun with Guy to a place with out-of-the-box Cuban.

episodes.name: Primetime Pork
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy's piling plates high with all kinds of pork. He's diggin' into everything from barbecue and chops to sausage and sandwiches. Get ready to pig out on nationwide porkapalooza.

episodes.name: BBQ Bites and Southern Flavor
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's grabbing some barbecue and Southern comfort. He visits a Seattle barbecue joint smokin' up ribs and dishin' out brisket chili and a real-deal Southern spot in California that's serious about fried chicken and collards.

episodes.name: East Coast, West Coast
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri hits both coasts for delicious dishes. In California, he grabs spicy pork in Palo Alto and plantains in Oakland. Then, he stops at a bakery-restaurant serving up meatloaf and French toast in Wilmington, North Carolina.

episodes.name: Italian, Hawaiian and More
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's digging into a multicultural flavorfest, from a poke place in Hawaii knocking it out of the park with island specialties to a crazy Italian spot putting tasty twists on their homemade pasta in San Carlos, California.

episodes.name: Playin' Chicken
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's playing a tasty game of chicken all over the country. He finds it Nashville hot-style in California and French-style at a pizza-pasta place in Seattle. In Hawaii, it's stuffed with Southern comfort and island flair.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Poke, Pork, and Chicken Parm
episodes.overview:
Big & Little's (Chicago, Ill.) • Pam's Kitchen (Seattle, Wash.) • The Shanty (Wadsworth, Ill.) • Atomic Cowboy (Denver, Colo.)

This trip, Guy's headin' back to some of his favorite joints still servin' up a bite for any time of the day. In Chicago, things have changed a lot for a shop still dishin' up poke. Up in Seattle, DDD's returnin' to its first and only Trinidadian joint where they've got a new spin on their classic fry bread. In Illinois, Guy's reminiscin' with the owner on how Triple-D changed his life and his menu. And in Denver, it's a second helpin' of a triple threat bar-biscuit-pizza joint where they're servin' up new late-night options.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Global Goodies
episodes.overview:
Taste of Peru (Chicago, Ill.) • Mike's Chili Parlor (Seattle, Wash.)  • Pok Pok (Portland, Ore.)

This trip, Guy's takin' a walk down memory lane to check on some of his favorite DDD finds. Up first in Chicago, he gets a second helping at his first Peruvian place. In Seattle, tradition's been standin' firm since 1922 at an old-school chili parlor. And back to Portland for a walk-up still servin' their killer wings.

episodes.name: On the Hook and In the Bun
episodes.overview:
Rebel Kitchen (Kealakekua, Hawaii) • Grand Harbor (San Francisco, Calif.) • The Red Door (Seattle, Wash.)

This trip, Guy's reelin' in off-the-hook seafood and diggin' into serious sandwiches.  First up, celebratin' flavors of the world with a fresh poke burger on the big island of Hawaii. Then in San Fran, a Chinese emporium cooking up lobster, pork buns and even dim sum chicken feet. And in Seattle, a beer-lover's spot serving fantastic fish and chips and the bomb beef dip.

episodes.name: Fusion of Flavors
episodes.overview: Guy digs into a variety of flavor fusions from a Latin-Asian mashup in Chicago and a Nashville hot chicken joint in Seattle to a Hawaiian spot that mixes the island with the mainland.

episodes.name: Tasty Traditions
episodes.overview:
Manny's Cafeteria & Delicatessen (Chicago, Ill.) • Kanaka Kava (Kona, Hawaii) • Piroshki on 3rd (Seattle, Wash.)

Guy Fieri dives into dishes steeped in tasty tradition. First, an old-school Jewish deli in Chicago's South Loop curin' and slicin' 40,000 pounds of homemade pastrami and corned beef a month. Then, on the Big Island, a tucked-away Kona spot servin' up authentic Hawaiian culture and cuisine. And in Seattle, a funky spot makin' their name with scratch-made Russian piroshki.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Sammies, Snacks and Seafood
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri pops into one of his favorite Seattle spots from the first season of DDD to see what's new for breakfast and lunch. In Minneapolis, Cuban cuisine has really taken off since DDD came to visit.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Surf and Turf
episodes.overview: It's a mix of land and sea as Guy Fieri pops into a few favorite spots. A Portland, OR, chef is still serving up seafood for breakfast, lunch and dinner, and Guy taste-tests new pizzas in Jackson, WY.

episodes.name: Food Truck Flavorfest
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's grabbin' some of the best meals on four wheels thanks to some full-throttle food trucks. In Nashville, a joint transforming the classic grilled cheese into gourmet goodness. In Key West, Fla., a welcoming wagon goin' gangbusters with their burgers and puttin' out the bomb bulgogi tacos. And in San Francisco, a tricked-out truck cooking up amazing Asian street eats.

episodes.name: Far East Flavorfest
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri cruises the states to check out some Far-East flavors from funky chicken with an Asian spin in Seattle and righteous Thai in Hawaii to modern Korean wings in Chicago.

episodes.name: Culinary Journey
episodes.overview:
MFK (Chicago, Ill.) • Broke Da Mouth Grindz (Kailua-Kona, Hawaii) • Blue Toba (Ashland, Ore.)

This trip, Guy's hittin' the road on an off-the-chain culinary journey. In Chicago, a Spanish-style spot servin' off-the-hook coastal cuisine. On the Big Island of Hawaii, a Filipino-Hawaiian mashup makin' a name by leavin' diners speechless. And in Oregon, a husband-and-wife Indonesian joint stir-fryin' Balinese curries that are a fave of someone Guy knows well - his mom Penny!

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Meat Lovers
episodes.overview:
Sakaya (Miami, Fla.) • Blackbrick (Miami, Fla.) • Frank's Noodle House (Portland, Ore.) • Waddell's Brewpub & Grille (Spokane, Wash.)

It's meat any way you like it when Guy's headin' back to favorite spots to see what they've been up to. In Miami, a long-time buddy craftin' magical dishes with chicken and duck at his second joint.  In Portland, a noodle shop expandin' to crank out thousands of dumplings a week these days. And in Spokane, ridiculous burgers and chicken wings have never been so explosive at their gigantic new location.

episodes.name: From Pork to Pasta
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's diggin' into everything from pork to pasta on this trip. In Chicago, a real-deal Italian spot with righteous ravioli and dynamite deep dish. Plus, an authentic Hong Kong barbecue experience served alongside all the classics. And in Spokane, Wash., a local joint with killer culinary, like carnitas fries and a twist on gnocchi.

episodes.name: Sandwiches, Southern and South of the Border
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diving into sandwiches, Southern eats and south-of-the-border specialties. In Spokane, Wash., a lights-out food truck smokin' up real-deal barbecue. In Ashland, Ore., a Mexican joint putting a tasty twist on tamales and crushin' their carnitas torta. And in Bozeman, Mont., a fried chicken haven serving up the bomb bird on the bone and in the bun.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Around the World
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's digging into everything from pretzels to paella. In Bozeman, Mont., a five-star take on breakfast with a Mexican pork masterpiece and a French toast Monte Cristo. In Little Rock, Ark., a microbrewery servin' up elevated pub grub like scratch pretzels and a gumbo-cheese fry mashup. Plus, a Mediterranean-inspired restaurant serving up Spanish specialties like on-point paella.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Wings 'n' Things
episodes.overview: This trip, it ain't no thing but a chicken wing in Coeur d'Alene, Idaho, when Guy Fieri stops by to taste a couple of new eats they've added. A Nashville barbecue spot has a new take on the old standard wings, and a joint in Miami is keepin' it real with a variety of new dishes, including drumsticks and duck.

episodes.name: Pretzels, Pork, and Paella
episodes.overview:
Storm Castle Cafe (Bozeman, Mont.) • Flyway Brewing Company (North Little Rock, Ark.) • La Terraza Rum & Lounge (Little Rock, Ark.)

This trip, Guy's diggin' into all kinds of outrageous creations. In Montana, a husband-and-wife breakfast spot bumpin' farm-to-table up a notch with a carnitas chimichanga and a Monte Cristo that eats like a meal. In North Little Rock, a buddy-owned joint crankin' out classic soft pretzels with plenty of dippin' sauce options to pair with their brews.  And across the river in LIttle Rock, a Venezuelan chef mashin' up his heritage with Spanish, French, and Italian for authentic comfort dishes like paella.

episodes.name: From Big Burgers to Little Italy
episodes.overview:
Zoftig Eatery (Santa Rosa, Calif.) • Bruno's Little Italy (Little Rock, Ark.) • North Bar (Little Rock, Ark.)

Guy Fieri's trying everything from the bomb burgers to a taste of Italy. He grabs craft brew and food pairings in Arkansas, homemade lasagna made by two brothers and righteous sandwiches in Santa Rosa, CA.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Between the Bread
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's always down for a good sandwich, so he's stopping in to check out some of the Triple D Nation's latest creations in Nashville, Denver and Miami. He also shares a Fieri family tradition.

episodes.name: Meaty Mashup
episodes.overview:
Simply Viêtnam Express (Santa Rosa, Calif.) • Cochon Volant BBQ (Sonoma, Calif.) • The Fold (Little Rock, Ark.)

Guy Fieri is digging into all kinds of carnivore creations. First up, a Fieri family Vietnamese  favorite in Santa Rosa ladlin’ up phenomonal phở. In the heart of California Wine Country, an old-school stickburnin’ joint rocking’ the best Southern ‘cue with a NorCal twist. And in Little Rock, a retro gas station servin’ up righteous Mexi-fusion comfort combos like bison burritos and pork and waffles.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Brisket to Bison
episodes.overview: It's all about the meat as Guy Fieri crosses the country to stop at some of his favorite haunts. In Denver, a Native American eatery has a new way to serve bison, and a Nashville diner is taking lamb to the next level.

episodes.name: Burgers, Bacon and BBQ
episodes.overview:
The Root Cafe (Little Rock, Ark.) • Eight Noodle Shop (Napa, Calif.) • Smoke Shack (San Antonio, Tex.)

Guy Fieri's diving into meaty, savory goodness, from a funky farm-to-table spot piling up a pimento cheese burger in Little Rock, AR, to an amazing Asian joint cooking up kimchi fried rice and prime-time pork ramen in Napa, CA.

episodes.name: From Sandwiches to Stroganoff
episodes.overview:
Wrigleyville (San Antonio, Tex.) • Fat Tummy (San Antonio, Tex.) • Zazu Kitchen + Farm (Sebastopol, Calif.)

Guy Fieri is digging into all kinds of hearty meals, from smoked meat sensations and killer empanadas in San Antonio, TX, to a farm-to-table spot putting their spin on stroganoff in Sebastopol, CA.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Stuffed Stuff
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri knows it's what's on the inside that counts, and these top spots in the Triple D Nation really know how to stuff the good stuff in, from stuffed calamari in CA to the Empress of Empanadas in CO.

episodes.name: Regional Recipes
episodes.overview:
Taquería Molcajetes (Santa Rosa, Calif.) • Ma Harper's Creole Kitchen (San Antonio, Tex.) • Dignowity Meats (San Antonio, Tex.)

Guy Fieri's diving into dishes with righteous regional flavor. In California, he finds a real-deal Mexican spot dishing out Michoacan specialties. And in San Antonio, a pair of joints: one cookin' creole classics, and deli mashin' up East Coast and Texas flavors.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Fried and Smoked
episodes.overview: Sometimes it's not what you're cookin' but how you're cookin' it. This trip, outside San Antonio, Guy's checkin' in on the O.G. Triple D and she's blowin' his mind with her new fried food. In Miami, things are smokin' with a fish dip appetizer and chicken wings. In Omaha, it's soul food all-around. And in West Des Moines they're servin' up barbeque and Southern twists with smoked duck.

episodes.name: Piling on the Pork
episodes.overview:
Marjie's Grill (New Orleans, La.) • Turkey and the Wolf (New Orleans, La.) • Luna Rosa Puerto Rican Grill y Tapas (San Antonio, Tex.)

Guy Fieri digs in and pigs out at a gangster grill in New Orleans serving up pork knuckles, a funky Big Easy joint making not-your-everyday pork tacos, and a Puerto Rican spot in San Antonio with a monster chop.

episodes.name: Cultural Twist
episodes.overview:
Red's Chinese (New Orleans, La.) • Finn's Cafe (Salt Lake City, Utah) • Curry Pizza (West Valley City, Utah)

Guy dives into cultural cuisine with a twist including scratch-made Scandinavian specialties, an Indian take on pizza and a funky Chinese-American mashup.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From the Sea
episodes.overview: Guy's headed back to see what the Triple D Nation is cookin' up from under the sea starting with an oyster shuckin' shack in the Big Easy and ending with a legit Mexican joint in Phoenix.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: International Affair
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is circling the globe starting in Salt Lake City where a Vietnamese sandwich shop has exploded with six -- count 'em -- SIX locations around town. In San Antonio, Texas, a Greek chef is whippin' up real-deal Mexican for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Finally, a haus in Glendale, Arizona, that hasn't missed a beat in their quest for true German flavor.

episodes.name: Handy Helpings
episodes.overview:
Proper Brewing Co. (Salt Lake City, Utah) • Hruska's Kolaches (Salt Lake City, Utah) • Rreal Taco (Atlanta, Ga.)

Guy grabs a fistful of righteous hand-held delights.  In Salt Lake City, a burger joint ampin' it up with beer in the beef.  Also in Salt Lake, the sibling-run Czech spot specializin' in sweet and savory breakfast treats.  And a funky spot in Atlanta where a chef with a serious culinary résumé is crankin' our real-deal tacos.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Steak, Sausage and Salami
episodes.overview: It's meat mayhem and Guy Fieri is checking out a joint known for cheesesteaks and meatballs that have taken over Salt Lake City. Then, a father-son team stays true to their Italian roots in -- of all places -- Glendale, Arizona. And in Omaha, a Triple-D chef's son pays tribute to his father by carrying on his legacy and his recipes.

episodes.name: 'Round the World Roundup
episodes.overview:
OneTaco (Austin, Tex.) • Yakitori Jinbei (Smyrna, Ga.) • Laziz Kitchen (Salt Lake City, Utah)

Guy digs into a world of flavors all over the United States from amazing Asian in Georgia and tasty tacos in Texas to lights-out Lebanese in Utah.

episodes.name: Whole Lotta Comfort
episodes.overview:
Twisted Soul Cookhouse & Pours (Atlanta, Ga.) • Purgatory (Salt Lake City, Utah) • Valentina's (Austin, Tex.)

Guy dives into hearty helpings of comfort from soul food in Atlanta and American-Asian mashups in Utah to spot-on barbecue in Austin, Texas.

episodes.name: Sandwich Showcase
episodes.overview:
Holy Roller (Austin, Tex.) • SLAB BBQ & Beer (Austin, Tex.) • Vinny's Bakery (Pasco, Wash.)

This trip, Guys grabbin' serious sandwiches from an Austin rock-n-roll brunch bar, a Texas joint goin' slow, low, and bangin' with '90s hip hop in their stacked up specialties, and a bakery in Washington State servin' up a killer Cuban and off-the-chain chicken.

episodes.name: Eating Up New Orleans
episodes.overview:
Piece of Meat (New Orleans, La.) • Seither's Seafood (New Orleans, La.) • Avery's on Tulane (New Orleans, La.)

This trip, Guy's takin' a tasty tour of The Big Easy. He rolls into a legit butcher shop with a funky take on comfort food flavors, checks out a creative seafood spot, and digs into a real deal po' boy joint saucing up their oysters.

episodes.name: Southern to South American
episodes.overview:
Greens & Gravy (Atlanta, Ga.) • Boteco (Austin, Tex.) • Porter's Real Barbecue (Richland, Wash.)

This trip, Guy Fieri digs into Southern comfort food and South American specialties. In Atlanta, a real-deal soul food spot dishing out collard green lasagna and a twist on fried chicken. In Austin, a food truck putting out Brazilian flavors that has some A-list fans. And in Richland, Washington, a joint going big with their legit barbecue.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Where's the Beef?
episodes.overview: It's all about the beef on this trip as Guy Fieri pops into a classic diner in Marietta, Georgia, for a taste of what's topping the charts these days. Next, it's on to San Antonio where a carwash-laundromat-kitchen combo is crankin' out killer burgers. And in Gilbert, Arizona, there's a joint pullin' all their ingredients from their own backyard and giving new meaning to the phrase, "farm to table."

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: A Taste of Italy
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri hits up his favorite Italian joints from over the years. In Scottsdale, Arizona, a real-deal Italian grocer crankin' out scratch-made staples like gnocchi and prosciutto that bring a tear to Guy's eye. And a San Antonio pizzeria serving authentic Neapolitan pie -- and they have the papers to prove it. Plus--BONUS! Guy pops into a by-the-slice stand in Austin, Texas, that the Nation has never seen before.

episodes.name: Mega Meat and Sweet Treats
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri goes to a Korean-taqueria mashing up unique flavors in their chicken tacos and bulgogi fries, a pizza joint putting out killer pastrami and outrageous scratch-made caramel rolls and serious strombolis.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Beef, Barbecue and Bar Food
episodes.overview:
Louie Mueller Barbecue (Taylor, Tex.) • Forte European Tapas Bar & Bistro (Las Vegas, Nev.) • The Highlander Diner (Atlanta, Ga.)

Guy Fieri's trip is all about the three B's: beef, barbecue and bar food. First, he stops in Taylor, Texas, at one of the first DDD barbecue joints to pay homage to an old friend whose son is carrying on his legacy. Then, it's on to Las Vegas, where Bulgarian bites and the ultimate Triple D prank reigned supreme. Finally, in Atlanta, a punk rock bar is still flippin' the script on bar food.

episodes.name: Belly, Beef and Bratwurst
episodes.overview: Fable Diner (Vancouver, B.C., Canada) • Pijiu Belly (Atlanta, Ga.) •  This trip, Guy's spannin' the continent to find the best in meaty treats.  In Vancouver, an elevated diner is dishin' out duck pancakes. In Atlanta, siblings at a funky Asian spot are puttin' out primetime pork belly and wok-fried chicken. And in Washington State, a brewpub is pairin' their pints with house-made sausages.

episodes.name: Coming Together in Cali
episodes.overview:
The Banshee (Chico, Calif.) • Upper Crust Bakery & Café (Chico, Calif.) • Grana Wood Fired Foods (Chico, Calif.)

This trip, Guy zeroes in on Chico, California, celebratin' the food scene as residents and restaurant owners recover from the 2018 Camp Fire that devastated the area. First up, a Boston-born chef rockin' Asian inspired fare like a «Phở-rench Dip» sandwich and bánh mi tacos.  Then, a local icon where a husband-wife team are makin' hometown-faves like chili and Korean pork salad. And a legit Italian joint crankin' out farm-to-table pasta and pizza specialties in their imported oven.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Pancakes, Potatoes and Pizza
episodes.overview:
Red Wagon (Vancouver, B.C., Canada) • The Green Mesquite BBQ (Austin, Tex.) • Pizzeria Lola (Minneapolis, Minn.)

On this trip, Guy Fieri crosses the border to Vancouver to check in on an elevated eatery serving the ultimate in diner food, from confit duck to pancakes. In Austin, Texas, a barbecue joint whose claim to fame — and its name — is all in the wood. And in Minneapolis, a Korean-inspired, French-oven-baked pizza parlor knockin' out killer creations and pilin' 'em on their perfect pies.

episodes.name: Burger and Breakfast
episodes.overview:
Sin of Cortez (Chico, Calif.) • Ethos Bakery & Café (Richland, Wash.) • The Pie Hole (Vancouver, B.C., Canada)

Guy Fieri's going from breakfast to burgers, stopping at a morning hot spot in Cali pumpin' up French toast. In southeast Washington State, a made-from-scratch joint makin' gangsta gravlax and a burger topped with an indulgent twist. And in Vancouver, a north-of-the-border pastry joint with fillin's goin' from savory meat to crazy sweet.

episodes.name: Not Your Everyday Eats
episodes.overview:
Momona (Chico, Calif.) • Frost Me Sweet (Richland, Wash.) • tuc (Vancouver, B.C., Canada)

Guy Fieri hits the road from Cali to Canada for out-of-the-ordinary eats. Like a crunchy mochico-crusted chicken bao and outrageous ramen in down the street from Cal State - Chico. Then, a southeastern Washington bakery-gone-savory firin' up duck confit banh mi and sweet potato lasagna. And over the border in historic Vancouver, cookin' up global inspirations for lamb-in-a-hole skillet pie and bite-sized pork belly crackling.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Chili Three Ways
episodes.overview:
Peaceful Restaurant (Vancouver, B.C., Canada) • Fox Bros. Bar-B0Q (Atlanta, Ga.) • Los Taquitos Comida Mexicana (Phoenix, Ariz.)

Guy Fieri crosses the border to Vancouver, British Columbia, to check in on an authentic Chinese place and see if their Thousand Chili Chicken is as spicy as it sounds. Then he heads south to Atlanta, where a couple of Texan twins are makin' out-of-bounds brisket chili and expanding all over the ATL. Finally, a sibling-run taquería in Phoenix is churning out Mom's famous green chili and taking over the town.

episodes.name: A World of Barbecue
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's firing up an entire world of barbecue, from smokin' chicken salad in Delaware to Argentinian flavor in San Diego and a traditional Hawaiian pig roast down in the ground in Kauai.

episodes.name: Sausage, Shawarma and Scaloppini
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's grabbing all kinds of grub, from arancini and veal scaloppini in Delaware to shawarma and first-rate falafel in San Diego, not to mention pizza topped with lamb sausage and pig cheeks in Vancouver, British Columbia.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Pork to Pot Pie
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri brings the whole family to his favorite jerk joint in Ocho Rios, Jamaica. Then it's back to the States, where a Georgia cafeteria sticks to Southern staples and a barbecue hot spot is seriously smokin' in Salt Lake City.

episodes.name: British, Hawaiian and Mexican
episodes.overview: Guy's getting international flavors in the States from a British pub in Delaware to a real-deal Mexican spot in San Diego.

episodes.name: Standout Seafood
episodes.overview: Guy hits Vancouver, Hawaii and California to reel in all kinds of standout seafood from salmon fish and chips to prime-time poke.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Guy's Going Home
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's hittin' up some of his favorite hometown haunts. He pops into a Mexican joint in Santa Rosa, CA, for pozole, grabs New York-style pizza in Eureka, CA, and visits a college hangout in Las Vegas for strombolis.

episodes.name: Crazy Chicken and Twisted Burgers
episodes.overview: Guy's digging into crazy twists on chicken and burgers including doctored-up chicken skins in Delaware, shawarma-stuffed sausages in San Diego and hearty walnut burgers in Vancouver.

episodes.name: International Infusion
episodes.overview: Guy grabs grub infused with international flavors from Thai sausage in Delaware and real-deal Hawaiian in Kauai to authentic Lebanese in San Diego.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Flavortown Favorites
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri revisits some of the best of Flavortown, from a noodle house in San Diego to a bigger-and-better neighborhood bistro in New Orleans.

episodes.name: Beef Bonanza
episodes.overview: Guy dives into a serious beef bonanza with scratch-made meaty ravioli in Delaware, an elevated spin on the French dip in San Diego and beefed-up Middle-Eastern fare in El Paso, Texas.

episodes.name: Spinning the Globe
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's checking out joints with global flavors, from saimin in Kauai, Hawaii, to outrageous tacos in Kansas City, Missouri, and meatless Mexican from a funky food truck in El Paso, Texas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Burgers, Burritos and Biscuits
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's checking out all kinds of food across Flavortown. In Boulder City, Nevada, a chili-churning diner is keeping it all in the family, and a taqueria in Salt Lake City is still cranking out burritos as big as your head.

episodes.name: From Australian to Asian
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's hitting the road and grabbing all kinds of worldwide flavor. In Kauai, Hawaii, a Japanese-Hawaiian spot putting a quick spin on fish, burgers and burritos. In Kansas City, Mo., an Australian bakery cookin' up Down Under comfort food like meat pies and sausage rolls, and in El Paso, Texas, a funky joint servin' international mashups like Pasta Chihuahua and an oxtail tostada.

episodes.name: Loaded, Stuffed and Fried
episodes.overview:
Arable (Santa Fe, N.M.) • Jarocho (Kansas City, Kan.) • Desert Oak Barbecue (El Paso, Tex.)

Guy Fieri's digging into joints loadin' it, stuffin' it and fryin' it, from bison-gravy fries and a lamb sandwich in Santa Fe, to outrageous stuffed oysters in KC, and fully loaded potatoes in El Paso.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: A Family Affair
episodes.overview:
Elena's (Waipahu, Oahu, Hawaii) • El Indio (San Diego, Calif.) • Blue Koi (Kansas City, Mo.).

This trip, Guy's checkin' back on some family-run favorites. On Oahu, siblings with a brick-and-mortar spot now rollin' out their mom's Filipino food all over the island. In San Diego, a taquería scratch- makin' taquitos the same way for three generations. And a brother-sister team in KC still dishin' out off-the-hook, Asian-inspired eats.

episodes.name: Full of Surprises
episodes.overview:
Extra Virgin (Kansas City, Mo.) • DELIght (El Paso, Tex.) • Joseph's Culinary Pub (Santa Fe, N.M.).

Guy Fieri's digging into some surprising ingredients, from duck tongue tacos in KC MO to lamb neck in Santa Fe.

episodes.name: Far-Flung Flavor
episodes.overview:
Krokstrom (Kansas City, Mo.) • The Beestro (Santa Fe, N.M.) • La Colonial Tortilla Factory (El Paso, Tex.)

Guy Fieri's heading out to grab flavor from far and wide, starting in KCMO with fantastic Scandinavian specialties including a chicken-banana-chili-cream concoction known as "Flying Jacob". In Santa Fe, an out-of-the-way spot dishin' upscale steak shawarma pitas and salmon souvlaki bowls. And in El Paso, a family-run operation crankin' out tortillas, tostadas, and tamales by the thousands.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Coastal Cuisine
episodes.overview:
Fresh Catch (Honolulu, Oahu, Hawaii) • Blue Water Seafood Market & Grill (San Diego, Calif.) • Privateer's Cove (Kona, Hawaii).

The sun is out and the surf is high as Guy Fieri hits up some ultimate DDD spots by the shore. First, he's in Honolulu to say aloha to an old buddy who's reelin' in fresh poke and smokin' pork by the filing cabinet-full! Then it's on to San Diego where two brothers who learned the fish biz before they could drive are dishin' out the freshest catch. And finally, Guy is back on the Big Island where a modern-day pirate is serving up craft dishes from around the world.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Something Sweet
episodes.overview:
Succotash (Kansas City, Mo.) • Twisted Root Burger Company (Dallas, Tex.) • Monte Carlo Liquor & Steakhouse (Albuquerque, N.M.).

It's Diners, Drive-Ins, Dives and decadence … as Guy revisits Triple D spots with plenty of sweet to go along with the savory! First up, Guy's in Kansas City, where a brunch spot is serving up a vegan treat rich enough for any meat eater. Then, a burger joint in Dallas is stirring things up with their mouthwatering milkshakes. Finally, a hidden steakhouse in Albuquerque, N.M., is keeping Mama's Greek classics -- and confections -- coming out of the kitchen.

episodes.name: Pizza Plus
episodes.overview:
Dirty Water Dough Co. (Boston, Mass.) • Dr. Field Goods Kitchen (Santa Fe, N.M.) • Noble Pie Parlor (Reno, Nev.).

Guy Fieri is divin' into the pie, starting in Boston at a joint putting beer into the crust. Then, a hard-rock hangout in Santa Fe, NM, is servin' up carne adovada pizza, and a funky spot in Reno, NV, gives new meaning to apple pie.

episodes.name: Bagels, Biscuit and Boar
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is diggin' into all kinds of flavor, starting in Santa Fe, NM, at a pub serving comfort grub like chicken and biscuits. Then, it's on to Reno, NV, for wild boar spaetzle, and Cambridge, MA, for some bagel sandwiches.

episodes.name: Unique Eats
episodes.overview:
Veggie Galaxy Diner & Vegan Bakery (Cambridge, Mass.) • Paper Dosa (Santa Fe, N.M.) • Yo̅sh's Unique Deli (Reno, Nev.)

This trip, Guy's crusin' for unique eats, starting at a vegetarian spot near M.I.T. whippin' up mac-and-cheese waffles. In Santa Fe, he's samplin' Indian delicacies like lamb curry and giant crêpes known as dosa. And in Reno, a joint temptin' taste buds with a pork belly bánh mì.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Fried, Baked and Barbecued
episodes.overview: Things are cookin' all kinds of ways when Guy Fieri visits a San Diego diner where law enforcement hones their skills and stuffs their gills. Then, a French-trained-chef-turned-barbecue-expert teaches Guy a thing or two about smoking sausage in Mission, Kan. And finally, in Phoenix, a Triple D legend serves up a Mexican-Asian mashup that has never been matched.

episodes.name: Eating Alaska
episodes.overview:
V's Cellar Door (Juneau, Alaska) - Pucker Wilson's (Juneau, Alaska) - Forno Rosso (Juneau, Alaska)

This trip Guy's headin' north, takin' in culinary goodies in Alaska's capital.  First up, divin' into some Latin-Asian fusion in a funky basement spot . Then a food truck servin' meaty, savory cowboy sundaes. And a family-affair Italian food truck slicin' up reindeer pie from their authentic wood-fired oven.

episodes.name: Northern Southern
episodes.overview:
Zerelda's Bistro (Juneau, Alaska) - Highland Fried (Cambridge, Mass.) - Carolina Kitchen and Barbeque Co. (Sparks, Nev.)

This trip, Guy's grabbin' Southern flavor all over the place. In the 49th state, they're smokin' honey-bourbon ribs. In Massachusetts cookin' up Nashville hot chicken and gumbo. And in the Silver State, it's low-and-slow wagyu brisket and wing nachos.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Trotting Out the Turkey
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is checkin' out Flavortown's all-time turkey-centric spots. At a Boston diner, Guy reminisces about the Thanksgiving plate he had in 2007. Then, in New Orleans, traditional turkey gets the French Quarter flair with some seafood stuffing you won't see coming. Finally, a chef in Albuquerque is still puttin' a New Mexico spin on her turkey -- not to mention the pork and corned beef.

episodes.name: Cruisin' Capital Cities
episodes.overview:
Perly's Restaurant and Delicatessen (Richmond, Va.) - In Bocca al Lupo (Juneau, Alaska) - Jax (Ottawa, Ont., Canada)

This trip, Guy's checkin' out cuisine in capital cities, like pappardelle with king crab in Juneau, duck pierogis in Richmond, and a bison burger and banana French toast in Ottawa.

episodes.name: Guy's All-Star Guests
episodes.overview:
In a Pickle Restaurant (Waltham, Mass.) • Pigwich (Kansas City, Mo.)  • Pauli's (Boston, Mass.)

This trip, Guy's rollin' out on an All-Star trip through Flavortown. West of Boston, hangin' with a Red Rocker at a spot crankin' out crazy burgers and French toast. Then in KC, tacklin' pigskin with an NFL coachin' legend at a joint meticulous about their meat. And back in Boston, meetin' up with a local chef to check out wicked-fresh, unbelievable lobster rolls.

episodes.name: Family Meals
episodes.overview:
Butcher's Kitchen Char-B-Que (Reno, Nev.) • Pop's Market on Grace (Richmond, Va.) • Pelican Seafood Market & Grill (Ottawa, Ont., Canada)

This trip, Guy's all about keepin' it all in the family. In Reno, father and son meat masters firin' up killer grilled barbeque with their whole family. In Virginia, a mother-son tribute servin' up deli faves and elevated spins on classic fare. And north of the border, an Ottawa spot carryin' on multi-generational, decades-long seafood traditions.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Cultural Cookin'
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is getting culture shock, starting with a French-inspired Hawaiian hot spot. Then, he checks in with a Lebanese joint outside Dallas, and in Santa Fe, NM, a Salvadoran chef is whipping up classics from his home country.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Slurpin' Soup
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri grabs a spoon for slurpin', starting in Honolulu at a diner known for oxtail soup. Then, people are flocking to a family-run restaurant in Baltimore, and a New Mexico chef is spicing her soup with a Santa Fe staple.

episodes.name: Creative Creations
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is divin' into inventive eats, from a funky joint cooking up mac and cheese pancakes in Burlington, VT, to an artistic eatery in Ottawa, Canada, firin' up spaghetti pizza and putting a colorful spin on the cronut.

episodes.name: Off the Beaten Path
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri takes a detour to find some not-your-everyday eats. In Richmond, VA, a Jamaican joint is serving oxtail and fried chicken with island flavor, and in Reno, NV, a sandwich spot puts a unique twist on the breakfast burrito.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: A Little Lighter
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is going lighter, starting at a Boston diner that's serving up egg-white omelets. Then, a Cuban joint in Los Angeles is trading in bread for plantains, and jackfruit tacos in Park City, Utah, are perfect after a ski day.

episodes.name: Meat Sampler
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri digs into all kinds of different meats on this trip. In Ottawa, Canada, a carnivore haven is stacking sandwiches with dynamite duck and a pork trifecta, and a Richmond, VA, taco joint is loading up out-of-bounds oxtail.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Meat Mashup
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is reliving his most meat-tastic memories, starting in Kansas City, Mo., at an award-winning BBQ joint. Then, a Dallas taqueria is still flipping the Tex-Mex script, and a sub shop is winning over Washington, D.C.

episodes.name: Smokin' Hot BBQ
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's diving into all kinds of 'cue on this trip. In Ottawa, Canada, a funky chicken joint is cranking the rotisserie and firing up the ribs, and a Burlington, VT, place is smoking wings and mashing up their BBQ with ramen.

episodes.name: Savory with a Side of Sweet
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is jumping into some sweet and savory dishes. In Burlington, VT, a vegan joint is gettin' crazy with a coconut-banana French toast, and a gas station-turned-restaurant in Logan, UT, is flipping grilled cheese inside-out.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Layered, Stuffed and Stacked
episodes.overview: It's a feeding frenzy, as Guy Fieri stops in Kansas City, MO, for a not-so-secret menu of sandwiches. Then, a Baltimore taqueria is now three locations deep, and a Greek joint in Cambridge, MA, has the moussaka market cornered.

episodes.name: Lots of Latin
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is loading up on all kinds of Latin on this trip. In Logan, Utah, a Salvadoran spot is puttin' out pupusas, and a funky food truck in Denver is dishing out prime-time Puerto Rican specialties.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Italian, Thai and Pie
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri has a righteous time revisiting joints offering everything from Thai to pie. In Honolulu, a family spot serves up specialties straight out of Thailand, and a funky spot in Dallas draws crowds for pizza and pasta.

episodes.name: Mom and Dad
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's hanging out at mom-and-pop spots, like a family-run Indian joint hooked up to a gas station in Logan, UT. He stops at a dumpling house in Vermont and a Denver landmark where Mom's cookin' up Caribbean-soul favorites.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Near to Far
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's taking a trip around the world without leaving the U.S. An Italian eatery in Boston is still serving up real-deal dishes from the homeland, and just down the street, a popular place is making major-league burgers and poppin' up all over the city. There's a first time for everything when Guy decides to revisit a ramen spot in El Paso, Texas, that he just discovered for dinner the night before!

episodes.name: Down-Home Flavor
episodes.overview:
Florence's Restaurant (Oklahoma City, Okla.) • The Pie Dump (Garland, Utah) • Just Be Kitchen (Denver, Colo.)

Guy Fieri hits the road and digs into some down-home cooking. In OKC, it's the country-cookin' joint fryin' up pork ribs and crankin' out yam-fried chicken. In Utah, an almost hundred-year-old Garland institution servin' up legendary breads, sammies, and sweet treats. And a Denver joint puttin' a healthy, paleo spin on classic comfort food dishes.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Savory Seafood and Square Pie
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's thinking outside the box. He and his son, Hunter, check on an Italian spot in Boston dishing out double portions of their authentic eats, and a Baltimore pizza joint is serving up not-your-average-shaped pies.

episodes.name: From Beef to Bao
episodes.overview:
Bun Daddy (Juneau, Alaska) • il porcellino salumi (Denver, Colo.) • Sabores International Cuisine (Logan, Utah)

This trip, Guy's diggin' into dishes from buns to cured meats to funky burgers. In Juneau, a husband and wife duo makin' funky bao in their tiny trailer. In Denver, an artisanal charcuterie emporium curin' and dryin' dozens of salumi for their killer deli sandwiches. And in Utah, an international success story servin' up flavors from around the world - includin' a funky peanut butter burger.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Italian Inspired
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri gets in touch with his Italian roots as he pops into a Baltimore market where the arancini and eggplant lasagna are both off-the-hook. Then, in Park City, Utah, the apres-ski crowd is clamoring for this seafood cioppino.

episodes.name: Hometown Inspiration
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri meets chefs putting their roots into their menus, like a Utah joint serving Louisiana specialties including blackened chicken pasta. He also finds vegan Israeli flavors in Portland, OR, and Detroit-style pizza in Denver.

episodes.name: Takeout: Flavortown Comes Home
episodes.overview: With restaurant takeout and delivery at an all-time high, on this trip, Guy Fieri is hosting a virtual Triple-D family reunion and bringing Flavortown to his own kitchen. Guy checks in with four DDD alums via video chat. All the chefs have sent Guy ingredients for their newest signature dishes, and they guide him through four knockout recipes so he can taste the out-of-bounds flavors. For this menu, Guy is cooking up chicken tamales from Arizona, Alabama paella fritters, European dumplings outta Vegas and a Kansas City burnt-end Philly cheesesteak.

episodes.name: Takeout: Home Delivery
episodes.overview: Four DDD alums connect with Guy Fieri via video chat and walk him through cooking their top sellers. On the menu are primo pork from New Hampshire, California chicken Parm, Minneapolis pizza and tuna all the way from Hawaii.

episodes.name: Takeout: Tastier at Home
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri brings Flavortown to his own kitchen by connecting with four DDD alums via video chat. All the chefs have sent Guy ingredients for their newest signature dishes, and they guide him through making a French dip, arancini and more.

episodes.name: Takeout: Dinner and Dessert That Delivers
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri and his son, Hunter, video chat with four DDD alums to cook some off-the-hook recipes at home. On the menu are Boston pasta, real-deal New York Neapolitan pie, mole enchiladas from Cleveland and an apple-pie funnel cake from Orlando for dessert.

episodes.name: Takeout: Funky Finds in 'da House
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri video chats with four DDD alums who guide him on a trip to Flavortown. The off-the-hook recipes include a funky waffle from Syracuse, gourmet mac 'n' cheese from Cleveland and pork with an island twist straight out of Charlotte, NC.

episodes.name: Takeout: Cross-Country Delivery
episodes.overview: It's Triple-D style takeout as Guy Fieri chats via video with four DDD alums who send ingredients to make their most off-the-hook recipes, including a wild West Virginia weenie, a Miami Asian-barbecue mashup and a righteous baloney sandwich from Atlanta.

episodes.name: Takeout: Bold Bites Brought Home
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri and his son, Hunter, do takeout in Flavortown style as DDD alums send ingredients for their most-dynamite recipes, including a Chinese-Mexican mix from Phoenix, Florida alligator fritters and a creole meatloaf straight from a California beach.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: BBQ, Burgers and Beyond
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is biting into burgers and barbecue. First up, he heads back to an O.G. Triple D barbecue joint in Oklahoma City to see what they're smokin' these days. Then, a burger biz in Roy, Utah, is flippin' patties for a third generation, and they've added some exotic meats. Finally, in Virginia Beach, Va., it's brisket and burnt ends like you wouldn't believe.

episodes.name: Sicilian and Seafood
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's in Oklahoma City, where a funky food truck turns out wood-fired pizza and Grandma's Sicilian meatball recipe. In Fort Lauderdale, FL, he chills with Vanilla Ice at a pirate-inspired joint serving up Brazilian and Caribbean seafood specialties.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: East Coast Eatin'
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri checks in on some favorite East Coast eats. First stop is a neighborhood joint that's dishin' out diner classics from a cramped kitchen, and in Baltimore, third time is the charm with this out-of-bounds pit beef stand.

episodes.name: Flavortown International
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is going global with flavors from all over the world. He checks out samosas and chicken kebab in Oklahoma and real-deal Mexican tortas in Oregon. Plus, he tries some legit Indonesian specialties in Florida.

episodes.name: Takeout: Culinary All-Stars
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri does takeout with a twist and calls on five all-star chefs via video chat to help cook the recipes. The menu includes Maneet Chauhan's tandoori chicken poutine, arancini and empanadas from Antonia Lofaso and Michael Voltaggio's crab-cake crepes.

episodes.name: Takeout: Celebrity Chefs
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri calls on five celebrity chefs via video chat to combine great restaurant food with cooking at home. The menu includes killer cavatelli from Alex Guarnaschelli, sticky rice from Beau MacMillan and Buddy Valastro's famous lobster tail pastries.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Breakfast, Lunch and Brunch
episodes.overview: On this road trip revisit, Guy Fieri pops by an Oklahoma City diner known for their onion burgers. Then, a Baltimore brunch spot is stepping up their grit game, and a quirky joint in Los Angeles is still putting a spin on their diner dishes.

episodes.name: Takeout: Worldwide Delivery
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri and his family love cooking at home and great restaurant food, so they combine the best of both worlds with some Triple-D style takeout. Four DDD alum send ingredients for their most off-the-hook recipes, then join Guy and Hunter via video chat to cook up all that flavor. On this menu, there's Roman-style pizza from Arizona, a wicked-hot burger from Boston, Hawaiian surf and turf and Trinidadian specialties out of Seattle.

episodes.name: Filling Up on Philly
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is filling up on a taste of Philadelphia, including a funky malt house serving the bomb Buffalo wings and a twist on the cheesesteak. A longtime tavern is making mama's Italian recipes, and a mother-daughter trio cooks up Indonesian specialties.

episodes.name: Takeout: Bringing Comfort Home
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri does takeout Triple-D style, combining cooking at home with great restaurant food. Four DDD alums send ingredients for their most off-the-hook recipes, then join Guy and Hunter via video chat to cook up all that flavor. On this menu, there's gourmet grilled cheese from Nashville, primo pizza from Boulder, Colo., Memphis fried chicken and Greek kebabs out of Houston, Texas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Smothered and Covered
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is covering all things smothered, starting with some mole sauce masters in Salt Lake City. Then, in Florida, a diner is dishing out down-home comfort food like biscuits and gravy, and a joint in Reno, NV, is servin' up sweetbreads in style.

episodes.name: Takeout: Global Comes Local
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's family combines great restaurant food and cooking at home with some Triple-D style takeout. Four DDD alums send ingredients for some real-deal recipes, then join Guy and his son Hunter over video chat to cook up all that flavor. On this menu, there's authentic Mexican from Phoenix, kolaches from Salt Lake City, Baltimore pit beef and pork belly all the way from Maui.

episodes.name: Chicken and Pie
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is checking out some chicken and diving into some pie on this trip. In Portland, Ore., a Southern transplant is servin' up a killer chicken sandwich and hush puppies, and three sisters in Oklahoma City are puttin' their own funky spin on pizza.

episodes.name: Takeout: Ordering All Kinds of Flavor
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri combines cooking at home and great restaurant food in some Triple-D style takeout. Four DDD alums send ingredients and join Guy and his son Hunter via video chat to cook their most off-the-hook recipes. There's real deal Italian from Scottsdale, Ariz., American Indian fare from Denver, gourmet grub out of a Massachusetts lounge, and short ribs all the way from Hawaii.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Finger Lickin' Chicken
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is chickening out across the country, starting at a sandwich shop outside Boston that has customers begging for more with their once-a-month Super Cluckin' sandwich. In Los Angeles, a Filipino favorite is keepin' it real with their coconut beef, cornbread and candy-coated chicken. Plus, a grilled cheese joint in Cleveland brings Guy's catchphrase to life with the Winner Winner Chicken Dinner.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Pork to Po' Boys
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri takes a drive down memory lane and revisits a German joint in Brighton, Colo., known for their killer kraut and signature sausage specials. Then, at a stop in the Midwest, a mod-Mex menu is now showcasing mole smothered pork chops, and a New Orleans native in Los Angeles is still slinging po' boys and boudin in Old Chinatown.

episodes.name: From Vikings to Wings
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is digging into a Scandinavian, Persian and Asian spin on wings. A vintage food truck in Portland, Ore., rollin' out wraps stuffed with Norwegian specialties, and, in Sunrise, Fla., authentic Iranian cuisine like chicken pomegranate stew. Plus, in Oklahoma City, a joint goin' wild with wings -- like Buffalo sriracha, bourbon teriyaki and Szechuan garlic parmesan.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Farm-to-Table Fresh
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is grabbin' straight from the garden. In Portland, Ore., he checks in on restaurant vets who closed down their original nose-to-tail eatery and opened a farm-to-table vegan joint. In Cleveland, a cafe is still sourcing local staples and making everything from scratch, and finally, a brunch spot in Virginia Beach, Va., literally bought the farm to grow their own ingredients for their take on potato pancakes.

episodes.name: From Authentic to Inventive
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is divin' into dishes from real deal to really creative. In Portland, Ore., a 70-year-old icon serving up authentic recipes straight from the chef's Chinese hometown, and a jammin' joint in Oklahoma City getting groovy with chicken and biscuits and a funky signature specialty. Plus, in Philadelphia, a legit sandwich shop putting their own twist on the Philly cheesesteak.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Diners, Drive-Ins and Delis
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is going to diners, drive-ins ... and delis. First up, Guy revisits a hoagie shop in Florida where the numbering system has him scratchin' his head. Then, in Denver, a Jewish deli is getting creative with their knishes, and, in Norfolk, VA, the inventor of the ice cream cone is still serving sandwiches and sweet treats over a century later.

episodes.name: Chicken and Briskets
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's digging into everything from chicken to brisket. In Fargo, N.D., a funky place piling barbecue onto mac and throwin' heat into wings. A Mexican joint in Parkland, Fla., pumping out righteous recipes inside a gas station, and, in Philadelphia, a scratch-made spot servin' up hearty home cooking with a healthy spin.

episodes.name: Pierogis, Pork and Pizza
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is diving into all kinds of off-the-hook flavors on this trip. In Hollywood, Fla., a sandwich shop servin' up a terrific taste of Peru. A pierogi palace in Philadelphia giving a fresh take on Polish specialties, and, in Fargo, N.D., a wood-fired pizza spot puttin' their own spin on pies and a Mediterranean twist into their meatballs.

episodes.name: America's Favorites: Cross-Country Culinary Cred
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri and son Hunter are on the first of a four-week road trip across America, picking the most creative and endearing videos to win $1,000 and be featured on the show. This time, they go from carne asada in Omaha to toaster tarts in Palm Desert, Calif. Plus, there's Philly cheesesteaks in North Carolina and Kansas City, Mo., all served up with a soundtrack.

episodes.name: America's Favorites: Fantastic Flavortown Finds
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri and son Hunter asked, and America answered -- more lucky winners are grabbing $1,000 and a spot on DDD. On this trip, there's monster meatballs and top-notch tostadas in Florida, pit beef in Baltimore that'll make you bust-a-rhyme and sentimental stories from these trying times all over the Triple D Nation.

episodes.name: America's Favorites: Top-Notch Tastes
episodes.overview: Viewers vouched for their favorite Triple-D joints, and Guy Fieri and son Hunter picked the most creative to be featured and get a cool $1,000 in their hand. The duo crisscrosses the country from California to Colorado and Phoenix to Florida for bomb burgers, excellent empanadas … and breakfast worth waking up for.

episodes.name: America's Favorites: Global Greats
episodes.overview: The final six winners from Guy Fieri and son Hunter's search for America's favorite DDD joints get their day in the sun and $1,000 in their pocket. Viewers from Alaska to Atlanta and Syracuse, N.Y., to San Diego submitted their No. 1 neighborhood spots. And this time, it's an international affair with killer Korean, incredible Italian and Middle Eastern that'll make your mouth water.

episodes.name: South Dakota Smorgasbord
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is hitting Triple-D's 50th state as he crosses into South Dakota. In Sioux Falls, a spot takin' a true regional specialty called chislic to the next level. Plus, real-deal dishes at the state's first Ethiopian joint, and in Garretson, a Midwest-Southern mashup puttin' their own stamp on comfort cooking.

episodes.name: Spicin' Things Up
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's grabbin' sandwiches, spice and everything nice on this trip. In Fargo, N.D., an incredible Indian joint firing up shrimp with a kick and lights-out lamb. In Sioux Falls, S.D., a funky spot loadin' up hand-held flavor bombs, and in Fairbanks, Alaska, a wild pizza place takin' pies from a sour specialty to spicy sweet.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Sausage to Saltfish
episodes.overview: This time, Guy Fieri's heading back to a century-old sausage maker in Portland, Ore., for a taste of pepperoni and a trip down memory lane. Then, in Oklahoma City, a meat-and-three is still dishin' out fried ribs and oxtail just like Mama used to make. And a Jamaican joint in Miami with the same cast of characters is servin' up everything from saltfish to spicy hot hand pies.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Hearty Helpings
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's plate is full of hearty, heaping helpings. First up, he stops by a neighborhood joint in Pittsburgh that's still servin' local staples and family favorites. Then, a Florida diner with inspiration from up North is spreading out all over the South, and in Oklahoma, the second generation is churning out award-winning chili on all kinds of creations.

episodes.name: Savory Meat and a Little Sweet
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is digging into both meat and sweet, starting in Sioux Falls, S.D., a market-butcher eatery servin' up a full culinary extravaganza. In Fairbanks, an off-the-hook Indian spot heatin' up Alaska with their hearty, real-deal specialties. And in Fargo, N.D., a bakery cafe scratch-making sticky pecan rolls and a savory French pastry dish.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Authentic International Eats
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's trip around the U.S. is a culinary spin around the globe. First up in Alaska, Guy's headed to Santa's hometown, North Pole, where Chinese staples like Dragon Chicken are favorites all year 'round. Then, in Portland, Ore., meat is still king at a family-run German sausage joint, and a Ukrainian market is feeding the Minneapolis crowd authentic eats like cabbage rolls and bigos stew.

episodes.name: Rib-Stickers
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's diggin' into dishes that'll stick to your ribs. In Sioux Falls, S.D., a funky joint cleaning up familiar favorites, like burgers and mac and cheese. In Fairbanks, Alaska, a place cookin' up elevated comfort like a lollipop pork chop and 25-ingredient meatloaf. And in Moorehead, Minn., a spot serving Midwest mashups like their take on bibimbap and a chicken fried sandwich.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: California Comfort
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's cruisin' around Cali, and his first stop is a Fieri favorite from the pilot episode that's still slayin' with their killer prime rib sandwich. Then, the Camaro's heading south to a neighborhood eatery in Eagle Rock where chicken and pork sandwiches are still supreme. Finally in Los Angeles, a chef from Yucatan is branching out with his Mexican menu.

episodes.name: Alaskan Adventure
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri heads to Fairbanks for an Alaskan culinary adventure. There's authentic German specialties at a super funky food truck, a joint rockin' a food-and-music jamfest featuring lights-out Cuban favorites and a local hot spot servin' up comfort like a meatball sub and their spin on a chicken pot pie.

episodes.name: Takeout: Goin' Big and Bringin' Home
episodes.overview: The Fieri family loves both cooking at home and great restaurant food, so they're combining the best of both worlds with some Triple D-style takeout -- cooking up recipes sent by DDD alums who join Guy and Hunter via video chat. On this menu, there's New Zealand red deer comin' from Texas, a stromboli from Jackson, Wyoming, seafood stew from a classic Georgia diner and sinful cinnamon rolls out of Colorado.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: BBQ, Pubs and Local Grub
episodes.overview: Guy revisits a few spots for barbecue, breakfast and brewpub favorites.

episodes.name: Takeout: Carnivore Delivery
episodes.overview: Guy and Hunter connect with DDD alums to make monster beef ribs and pizza.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Snacks, Apps and Twisted Mac
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri revisits an old favorite he's been going to for years in San Francisco, but nowadays it's his buddy who's on the line serving up cod rillettes and chowder with a surprise ingredient. In St. Paul, the Godfather of pasta is still servin' scratchmade everything, including a twist on mac and cheese, and in Superior, Wis., a neighborhood hot spot has added some new appetizers with influence from up north.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Italy to Africa
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is making Triple D history in San Francisco with a GGG-turned-DDD star who's bringing his Ethiopian-style flank steak and sauteed prawns to the Triple D Nation. In Minneapolis, an Italian joint is still scratch-making their pasta and prosciutto. Then, a Duluth diner is gathering ingredients straight from their planters and putting them right on your plate.

episodes.name: Takeout: Comin' From All Over the Map
episodes.overview: Guy and Hunter Fieri love cooking at home and great restaurant food, so they combine the two by cooking up recipes sent by Triple-D alums who join them via video chat. On this menu, there's gangster gorditas comin' from Phoenix, Korean chicken wings out of Denver and a steak specialty from a classic Jewish deli in Houston, Texas. Plus, pizza and meatballs sent by an old-school spot in Knoxville, Tenn.

episodes.name: Takeout: Sendin' the Surf & Turf
episodes.overview:
Takeout from: Pier 23 (San Francisco, Calif.) ● Super Duper Weenie (Fairfield, Conn.) ● Flying Mango (Des Moines, Iowa) ● Jitlada Restaurant (Los Angeles, Calif).

Guy and Hunter Fieri combine their love of cooking at home and great restaurant food by making recipes sent by DDD alums who join them via video chat. On this menu, there are fish tacos and crab cakes outta San Fran, a deluxe hot dog from a Connecticut wiener shop, a Cajun shrimp creation comin' from Des Moines and sensational spicy Thai straight out of L.A.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Nostalgic Neighborhood Nosh
episodes.overview:
Rocco's Cafe (San Francisco, Calif.) ● The Wienery (Minneapolis, Minn.) ● The Dining Car (Philadelphia, Penn.)

This time, Guy Fieri is cruising the neighborhood to revisit local hangs he can't get enough of. First up, a San Francisco Italian joint that keeps crankin' out favorites like chicken Marsala and eggplant Parmesan. Then it's back to the downtown Minneapolis dive that's added even more Chicago-style staples to their menu, including a hot dog topped with giardiniera. And finally, on to Philly, where an old-school, family-run diner is still offerin' up scrapple, crèpes and apple walnut French toast any hour of the day.

episodes.name: Pasta Potatoes and Pescatarian
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is tasting everything from pasta to potatoes, and he's got some grub for his pescatarian friends. First up, Vanilla Ice takes Guy to his favorite Ecuadorian joint in West Palm Beach, Fla., for standout ceviche. Then, in Moorhead, Minn., a former DJ mixes it up with his take on scratch-made pasta and poutine, and, in the Florida Keys, a local landmark is poundin' out hits like their chicken and smash.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From the Seas and Lots of Cheese
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is diving into all sorts of off-the-hook flavors. First up, in the Florida Keys, Guy and Hunter are hittin' up a local landmark that's new to DDD -- but their deconstructed ceviche is the talk of the town. In St. Paul, the stuffed burgers and spicy apps at a neighborhood hot spot called us back for a third time, and, in Philly, classic comfort food is made with unexpected ingredients.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: New Faces and Old Places
episodes.overview: This time, Guy Fieri is checking out a mix of familiar places and new faces. In Miami, Guy and a couple buddies hit up a Haitian place for the first time, and the fried pork and pikliz do not disappoint. Then, in Oakland, a vegan version of Creole classics like gator bites and jambalaya, and, in Blawnox, Pa., an old school dive still dishin' out heaping helpings of hearty home cooking.

episodes.name: Takeout: Best of the West Roundup
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri and Hunter are joined by DDD alums via video chat to make some Triple-D style takeout. On this menu, there's a crazy burger creation comin' from Phoenix and handmade sausages out of Portland, Ore. Plus, a couple California spots are sending spicy Mexican shrimp and the bomb barbecue.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Mobile Meals
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri is chasing down dynamite dishes on the move. First up, in Kihei, Hawaii, Guy, Hunter and Jules stumble onto a pizza cart that Guy first found on the beach in 2016 -- and the pie is still legit. Then, in Cloquet, Minn., an old-school carhop's delivering double cheeseburgers and real-deal Coneys right to your car, and a food truck traveling throughout San Francisco opened a permanent spot for their Asian-Mexican mashups.

episodes.name: Takeout: All Over the Menu
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's family loves both cooking at home and great restaurant food, so they combine the two with some Triple-D style takeout. Guy and Hunter are joined by DDD alums via video chat to cook up a menu of chicken and biscuits out of Brooklyn and off-the-hook Jamaican oxtail and wings from Cincinnati. Plus, octopus and pasta comin' from Chicago and a whole new kind of crab cake straight out of Baltimore.

episodes.name: Takeout: Real Deal Delivery
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri combines a love of great restaurant food and cooking at home by making recipes sent by DDD alums who join Guy and Hunter via video chat. On this menu, there's real deal barbecue from Los Angeles, wild Thai dishes out of Phoenix, a monster lasagna from Minneapolis and old-school steak hoagies straight out of Hollywood, Fla.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: All Sorts of Seafood
episodes.overview: This time, Guy Fieri is diving into all sorts of seafood sensations.
