In Kailua-Kona, Hawaii, a poke place had to change their address to handle the DDD crowds, but they brought their ahi and oysters with them. Then, in San Francisco, a quaint spot is still servin' Southern staples with a twist -- like their crawfish pot pie. Plus, a clam shack in Key West, Fla., got creative with conch.

episodes.name: Takeout: Shipped, Sweet & Savory
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri loves cooking at home and great restaurant food, so he combines the best of both worlds by making some Triple-D style takeout with DDD alums who join Guy and Hunter via video chat. On this menu, there’s killer Cajun comin’ from Los Angeles, sweet and savory crepes out of Las Vegas, empanadas sent from Denver, and legit barbecue straight out of Taylor, Texas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Pork and Poke
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri hits the road to Houston, where he checks out the rotisserie pork at a Greek diner; a poke place in Kahului, Hawaii, is dishin' out fresh fish and turning up the heat on tako, and a Mexican joint in San Francisco makes it all from scratch.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Cookin' Across the Country
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri travels from sea to shining sea, starting in Key West, FL, where a food cart has increased its footprint to churn out more kimchi and Kogi dogs. In College Station, TX, an early stop on the road trip is still making classic diner staples.

episodes.name: Pig's Feet, Mojo and Chow-Chow
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri dives into not-your-everyday recipes, starting in Palm Beach, FL, where a hidden gem is serving up seafood and chow-chow. Plus, a funky Filipino joint in Hawaii is firing up their spin on pig's feet.

episodes.name: Taste of the Tropics
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is loading up on tropical flavour, starting in a Florida spot serving up lobster enchiladas and lionfish rolls.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Intercontinental Cuisine
episodes.overview: In Lahaina, Hawaii, the Fieri family revisits a funky noodle joint; in Chicago, an Italian eatery cranks out calamari and a Korean-American burger joint goes crazy with kimchi.

episodes.name: Mouthwatering Meat
episodes.overview: Brisket and burgers at a butcher shop-restaurant in Palm Beach, Fla.; Latin-style pork belly and Caribbean oxtails in Houston, Texas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Chicken
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri starts off revisiting a spot on Maui for smoked chicken and killer cornbread; there's a breakfast of sweet potato hash with chorizo at a Wisconsin diner and jumbo wings in soy ginger sauce at a Chicago BBQ joint.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Papaya, Panelle and Pork
episodes.overview: In Kihei, Hawaii, Guy Fieri finds a pairing of papaya and pork belly; an Italian eatery and market in Norridge, Ill., creates authentic Sicilian recipes like pane and panelle; a Chicago BBQ spot is dishing up pulled pork.

episodes.name: Cookin' from Scratch
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's diving into scratch-made specialities. In Houston, TX, there's real-deal Italian pasta, plus a funky joint is putting out pizza topped with a surprising combo. Then, a scenic spot in Hawaii is cooking up a comforting chicken pot pie.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Fresh from Flavortown
episodes.overview: On this trip, it's Flavortown at its freshest. In Hawaii, Guy Fieri stops by a food truck for fresh hamachi on chilled soba noodles. Then, Guy checks in on an empanada empire in Houston, TX, and a Chicago hot spot known for their homemade chorizo.

episodes.name: Domestic and Abroad
episodes.overview:
Matteo's Osteria (Wailea, Maui, Hawaii) • Dick's Northwest Sausage & Deli (Centralia, Wash.) • Be More Pacific (Houston, Tex.)

On this trip, Guy's digging into all-American and foreign favorites. On Maui, the husband-and-wife Italian joint puttin' five layers of love in its homemade lasagna and lamb osso bucco. In Centralia, Wash., a real-deal meat market is stackin' up serious sandwiches, including their killer pastrami. And in Houston, a funky spot firin' up Filipino flavor with a Texan twist.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Diner Eats and a Fieri Treat
episodes.overview: On Maui, Guy Fieri and his family stop by musician Mick Fleetwood's restaurant to whip up lamb with mint pesto; Guy returns to a diner in Wisconsin and savours the burgers and specials at a joint in Houston.

episodes.name: Regional Flavors
episodes.overview:
The Toasted Coconut (Houston, Tex.) • Zydeco (Bend, Ore.) • Mackinaw's Restaurant (Chehalis, Wash.)

Guy Fieri digs into righteous regional flavors where you may not expect to find them. There's the tiki oasis in Houston servin' up elevated dumplings and honey butter chicken biscuits. A husband-and-wife duo slingin' Cajun jambalaya in Bend, Oregon. And a Washington State spot where a chef runs two restaurants with a shared kitchen kickin' up a phenomenal Pakistani oxtail curry.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Chicken to Chowder
episodes.overview: This time, Guy Fieri's got all kinds of chicken and a chowder that can't be missed! First up in Florence, Ore., a never-been-seen seafood shack is makin' a must-have crab chowder, and Guy's creating a crab toast for their menu! Then, a Cuban spot in Chicago is cooking pollo and vaca frita the authentic way, and in Houston, a Jamaican joint's still adding their wet jerk seasoning to just about everything.

episodes.name: Meat and Heat
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri hits the road to dig into the meat and catch some heat. There's a tucked-away panini paradise in Chehalis, Wash., and a funky Korean spot in Brentwood, Tenn., gettin' spicy with their chicken and bulgogi. Plus, in Houston, a barbecue joint throwin' some Tex-Mex into the mix with their brisket tacos and jalapeno sausage.

episodes.name: Sandwiches and Spice
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's grabbing serious sandwiches and a side of spice. In Bend, Ore., there's a bagel shop loadin' up pastrami and throwing in some jalapeno heat. In Salt Lake City, a Venezuelan spot making amazing arepas and a plantain patacon. Plus, a Nashville joint following in their DDD-alum mother's footsteps while puttin' their own twist on Jamaican specialties.

episodes.name: Traditional Twists
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's digging into a world of flavor with some special flair. In Bend, Ore., a funky spot stuffin' their buns with all kinds of unexpected flavors. A Puerto Rican oasis in West Jordan, Utah, cooking up specialties like real deal mofongo. Plus, in Nashville, an Italian joint servin' grandma's meatball recipe and righteous coal-fired pizza.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Creative Comfort
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's gettin' creative with comfort food. His first stop is a Jewish deli in Houston, Texas, where he tackles a towering take on chicken and waffles. Then, in Portland, Ore., Texas-style barbecue is pulling inspiration from south of the border with their smoked chicken enchiladas. And, in Nashville, a "meat and three" is still serving their Southern staples, but now you can get 'em after-hours.

episodes.name: Tacos, Tots, and Chops
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's enjoying a fun, filling fiesta. In Grand Junction, Colo., there's a legit pub serving scratch-made comfort, like elevated hash and a real deal Reuben. In Salt Lake City, a funky spot takin' tacos to a whole new level, and, in Nashville, Middle Eastern specialties that are as outrageous as the group cookin' them up.

episodes.name: Classic and Comfort
episodes.overview: This trip is a classic, comfort-filled joy ride for Guy Fieri. In Leavenworth, Wash., a quintessential retro diner shines with their scratch-made mozzarella sticks and gravy fries. In Draper, Utah, a stellar Southern spot puttin' out homestyle fried chicken and grits. Plus, in Nashville, a vegan spot knockin' it out of the park with their club sandwich spin and meatless chorizo.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Eats Abroad
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri is packing his passport because he's eating abroad! First up in Houston, Texas, Guy stops into a Mexican joint makin' mole and guisada just like grandma. An Italian eatery in Nashville is loadin' up the lasagna, and a Polish place in Hamtramck, Mich., is still pinchin' perogies and wrappin' beef rolls the old-fashioned way.

episodes.name: Chicken 'Cross the Globe
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri is trackin' down off-the-chain chicken from all across the globe. In Salt Lake City, there's a unique curry-chicken mashup, and in Albuquerque, N.M, the chicken is down-home fried alongside a sweet take on waffles. Plus, in Grand Junction, Col., it's nested in tacos at a spot also puttin' an outrageous culinary spin on guacamole.

episodes.name: From Europe to Asia
episodes.overview:
Red Rock Deli (Albuquerque, N.M.) • Il Bistro Italiano (Grand Junction, Colo.) • Kobe (Mill Creek, Utah)

This trip, Guy Fieri has a culinary lineup crossing both the Atlantic and the Pacific. In Albuquerque, a real-deal Eastern European emporium servin' legit stuffed cabbage and schnitzel. In Western Colorado, an authentic Italian spot makin' artichoke Parmesan soup and their "Rosetta" specialty from scratch, And just outside Salt Lake City, a Japanese joint dishin' up righteous ramen -- both hot and cold.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Fish, Fries and Frog Legs
episodes.overview:
Jamaicaway Restaurant (Nashville, Tenn.) • 55 South (Franklin, Tenn.) • Eastside Fish Fry & Grill (East Lansing, Mich.)

On this trip, Guy Fieri's fuelin' up for visits back to a few Flavortown favorites. First up: a Jamaican joint in the Nashville Farmer's Market dishin' out oxtail and red snapper escovitch straight from the island. Then just a bit south in Franklin, a joint is servin' loaded fries and messy shrimp. And outside Detroit, the East Lansing market preppin' more batches of fried wings, frog legs, and chicken gizzards.

episodes.name: Asian and American
episodes.overview:
Seoul Casa (Anchorage, Alaksa) • Hickory House Ribs (Aspen, Colo.) • Kitsune (Albuquerque, N.M.)

On this trip, Guy Fieri's got Asian flavors, an American classic and some mashups in between. In Anchorage, there's a Korean-Mexican joint rollin' out kimchi burritos and wild wings. In Aspen, it's a smokehouse run by a former dentist puttin' his own twist on ribs, and in Old Town Albuquerque, a funky fusion food truck-turned-brick-n-mortar spot heads off the charts with a flavorful veggie specialty and the bomb pork belly.

episodes.name: Meaty, Cheesy and Sweet
episodes.overview:
Highlands Alehouse (Aspen, Colo.) • Waffles and Whatnot (Anchorage, Alaska) • Guava Tree Café (Albuquerque, N.M.)

On this trip, Guy Fieri's finding things meaty, cheesy and a little sweet. In Aspen Highlands, a ski hot spot elevatin' their slopeside menu with loaded carnitas nachos and sizzlin' steak tacos. In Anchorage, there's a wild waffle house pilin' up both sweet and savory masterpieces. Plus, in Albuquerque, a lights-out Latin joint goin' big with their amazing arepas and prime-time pork paninis.

episodes.name: From Appetizers to Dessert
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's digging into appetizers, dessert and everything in-between. In Laramie, Wyo., an old-school cafe is loadin' up the bomb green-chili burritos and serving stellar scratch-made pie. In Albuquerque, N.M., a vegetarian joint is packin' flavor into their no-meat loaf and cauliflower "wings." And, in Anchorage, Alaska, a funky spot is going next level with their blackened chicken gnocchi and a sweet-and-savory focaccia starter.

episodes.name: Gettin' Funky in Flavortown
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's grabbing all kinds of funky flavor. In Laramie, Wyo., a righteous restaurant-bar is pilin' up their nachos and putting a special pop in their burgers. Plus, a longtime spot is cookin' up a vegetarian spin on both meatloaf and a banh mi sandwich. Then, in Anchorage, Alaska, a Mexican joint is serving dynamite duck tacos and off-the-chain chorizo.

episodes.name: From Italian to Asian
episodes.overview:
Originale Caffè & Deli (Anchorage, Alaska) • Coda Bakery Vietnamese Deli & Tofu House (Albuquerque, N.M.) • The Crowbar & Grill (Laramie, Wyo.)

Guy Fieri's diving into global flavors, starting at a real-deal Italian deli in Anchorage servin' up magical and devilish sandwiches. Then on to an Albuquerque spot rockin' an out-of-bounds Duc Biet banh mi. Plus, the Triple-D-inspired Wyoming joint meldin' cultures with Bulgogi fries and their Billhook lamb-feta-tzatziki pizza.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Poultry, Lamb and Jam
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's got breakfast, lunch, dinner and drinks, starting in Columbus, Ohio, where he loads up on a meatball sub; Guy turns his attention to creative cocktails and a jammin' turkey burger in Edison, N.J., and shawarma in Lansing, Mich.

episodes.name: Pickin' Up and Chowin' Down
episodes.overview:
Rowley Inn (Cleveland, Ohio) • Alibi Wood Fire Pizzaria and Bakery (Laramie, Wyo.) • Ray's Place (Anchorage, Alaska)

This trip, Guy's rollin' out to places perfect for pickin' up and chowin' down. In Cleveland, a funky bar across the street from a Christmas classic makin' monster tots and a Hawaiian-Polish mashup. In Wyoming, a powerhouse pizza-bakery firin' up barbecue pie and standout sandwiches.  And in Anchorage, a Vietnamese spot cookin' up amazing crepes and flavor-bomb chicken.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Out of Bounds Burgers
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's got a mouth full of the best burgers, starting with a Cali-inspired chorizo burger in Blue Ash, OH. There's a strawberry jam-packed double patty in Nashville, and a burger joint in Ann Arbor, MI, is making 'em a million different ways.

episodes.name: Food Network Super Chefs
episodes.overview:
Mabel's BBQ (Cleveland, Ohio) • Chaatable (Nashville, Tenn.)

Guy Fieri's hitting up joints owned by Food Network super chefs. Like Michael Symon's barbeque spot in Cleveland, where he's firin' up pork belly and brisket. Then on to Nashville, where Maneet Chauhan is servin' up her creative spin on Indian recipes.

episodes.name: Plating Up Puerto Rico
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's travelling with Antonia Lofaso on a culinary journey through Puerto Rico. In Old San Juan, they're diggin' into a chicken-trifongo combo; a spot in Juncos is servin' up plantain-picadillo lasagna and a stew made with pig's feet.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Old Friends, New Flavors
episodes.overview:
Kesté Pizza & Vino (Manhattan, N.Y.) • Joe's Gizzard City Café (Potterville, Mich.) • Taste of Belgium (Cincinnati, Ohio)

On this trip, old friends are whippin' up new flavors.  In Manhattan's Financial District, Guy follows a Triple D alum to his new place to check out old-school pizza and a new level of lasagna. Then, it's back to the south-central Michigan place known for its gizzards - where they're frying everything from burgers to breakfast sandwiches. Plus the Belgian bistro in Cincinnati still servin' waffles every which way.

episodes.name: Chicken, Steak and Cake
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's doubling up with sweet and savory, both hot and cold. In San Juan, Puerto Rico, a Venezuelan food stand is serving up amazing arepas with off-the-chain chicken and stellar steak. In Laramie, Wyo., a funky food truck is scoring with winning wings, including a star NFL quarterback's favorite. And in Cleveland, a two-for-one spot is making an outrageous ice cream-cake combo alongside a raclette-ramen mashup.

episodes.name: Flavor Expedition
episodes.overview:
Salao Tapas & Bar (Caguas, P.R.) - Fat Cats (Cleveland, Ohio) - Haldi Chowk 35 Indian Bistro (Middletown, N.J.)

This trip, Guy's embarking on a worldwide journey of flavor: In Caguas, Puerto Rico, a tapas-and-more joint puttin' out international bites like churrasco steak and ropa vieja dumplings. In Cleveland, a funky bar servin' next-level dishes with Filipino flair. And in suburban Jersey, an Indian spot cookin' up real deal recipes like tandoori chicken and over-the-top samosas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Covered and Smothered
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri pops into a Jewish deli in Palm Springs, CA, to reminisce about pastrami and brisket. Then, it's double trouble with Kid Rock in Clarkston, MI, and a look back at not one but two of Kid's favorite hometown restaurants.

episodes.name: Surf and Savory
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's grabbing a little surf, turf and flavors from the earth. In Puerto Rico, a local gem is serving off-the-hook pork trifongo and shrimp empanadas. Plus, Guy finds a mushroom po' boy in Somerville, NJ, and outrageous octopus in Cleveland.

episodes.name: From Chicken to Chiles
episodes.overview:
Chúla (La Quinta, Calif.) • Good Company (Cleveland, Ohio) • The Chubby Pickle (Highlands, N.J.)

This trip, Guy's findin' all kinds of unexpected flavor. In the Cali desert, a creative chef puttin' a new spin on familiar recipes, like her Mom's chilaquiles and a crazy Monte Cristo. In Cleveland, an Iron Chef tags along to a joint runnin' sandwiches off the rails, including one that's a mouthful in more ways than one! And in New Jersey, a funky sports bar with an unforgettable name ampin' up bar bites like Korean wings and pork tacos.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Classic Plates New Tastes
episodes.overview: On this road trip, Guy Fieri's finding new takes on classic favs. First up in Palm Desert, Calif., Guy pops into a place servin' avocado fries and a burger with an Italian accent. Then, soul food -- like pigs' feet and St. Louis-style ribs -- gets a Jersey twist in Atlantic City, N.J. And in Lansing, Mich., a barbecue joint puts their own take on bruschetta.

episodes.name: Cruisin Coast to Coast
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's digging into flavor coast to coast. In Indio, Calif., he's hittin' up a taco joint going above and beyond with their torta ahogada and a quesadilla-taco-au jus mashup. In Sea Bright, N.J., a legit Thai spot is piling up the pork and dynamite dumplings. And a funky food truck in Bridgewater Township, N.J., is loadin' up monster sandwiches.

episodes.name: Stellar Sandwiches and Big-Time Burgers
episodes.overview:
East Side Banh Mi (Nashville, Tenn.) • Gastro Grind Burgers (Palm Desert, Calif.) • The Real Italian Deli (Palm Desert, Calif.)

On this trip, Guy's unhingin' his jaw for off-the-hook sandwiches and out-of-bounds burgers. in Nashville, a Vietnamese spot makin' a bomb bánh mì and mind-blowin' steak and rice bowls. In the Cali desert, a husband-wife joint grindin' all their own meats for standard, deluxe, and outrageous hoity-toity fancy-pants burgers.  And stayin' in Palm Desert, a market-deli pilin' up Italian porchetta on scratch-made focaccia.

episodes.name: Cheese and Meat
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's gettin' cheesy and meaty, starting in South Bound Brook, N.J., where a meat market with an unforgettable chef is stacking up their spin on the sloppy joe and baking a fully stuffed bread. In Nashville, a taco joint is pilin' up a carne asada bowl and nachos with hot local flavor. Plus, there's a down-home spot serving craft beer, a dynamite dip and the bomb barbecue pork mac.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Fried to Sides
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's throwin' everything in the fryer! His first stop is an O.G. Triple D in Knoxville, Tenn., where the pizza, onion rings and fried chicken come straight to your car. Then, crunchy crab cakes are gettin' all spiced up in Somers Point, N.J., and a popular pub in Blue Ash, Ohio, had to make more room for their crispy pig tails and humongous hot dogs.

episodes.name: From Chicken to Cheesesteak
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's diggin' into chicken and some crazy creations. In Palm Springs, Calif., a crepe spot is all about the savory with barbecue bird and cheesesteak fillings, while a funky joint is cookin' up real deal Mexican pollo and chicharrones. In Nashville, an Egyptian food truck is firing up hot wings and their falafel waffle specialty.

episodes.name: Burger, Bird and Meaty Italian
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diving into a meaty smorgasbord. In Nashville, a funky neighborhood joint is serving up loaded carne fries and a skyscraper burger, and in New Smyrna Beach, Fla., a rockin' chef is cooking up real deal gnocchi and Grandma's hands-on pizza recipe. Plus, a spot with an out-of-this-world atmosphere is going huge with monster pork chops and an Italian meat extravaganza.

episodes.name: Stuffed, Smoked and Wrapped
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri is pickin' up what Flavortown is puttin' down. In Nashville, a funky neighborhood joint is loading up the tots and adding green chile crunch to their signature wrap. And in Daytona Beach, Fla., a local gem is servin' up off-the-hook seafood and smokin' up amazing alligator ribs. Plus, at the beach, a breezy spot is all about Venezuelan specialties, like piled-up plantain goodness and stuffed chicken arepas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Kaleidoscope
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri looks for culinary creations you can really sink your teeth into, including a New Hampshire catering truck full of beef tips, shrimp and dirty bird wings. Then, there's rockin' pierogis in Ohio and homemade gnocchi at a New Jersey eatery.

episodes.name: Eastern Southern
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's heading east to get a taste of the South. A real deal smokehouse in New Hampshire is putting their own spin on meatloaf, a funky North Carolina joint is spicin' up their shrimp and a historic Florida spot is making a standout seafood stew.

episodes.name: Rolled and Holed
episodes.overview:
Big Dave’s Bagels & Deli (North Conway, N.H.) • Third Wave Café & Wine Bar (New Smyrna Beach, Fla.) • Floyd’s 1921 (Morehead City, N.C.)

This trip, Guy's rollin’ out for a little "holey" moley. In New Hampshire, a Jersey-style joint  puttin' out bomb bagels and unique sweets. Right on the beach in Florida, a fun chef goin' prime time with pastrami ribs and wood-fired pizza. And in North Carolina, a funky spot addin’ a Southern spin to egg rolls and elevatin’ shrimp and grits.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Soups, Stews and Seafood
episodes.overview: Host Guy Fieri travels across America in search of the best diners, drive-ins and dives. He visits classic "greasy spoon" restaurants and talks to staff and customers about the food. Episodes often feature eateries linked by a common theme, such as burgers or comfort food.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Sausage to Sweet
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's got sweet and savory. First up in Pembroke, N.C., he stops by a never-seen-before treat truck to try some knock-out candy apples. Then, an old school diner in Jersey City may have gotten a new name, but the pancakes are still the same. Down the road in Brigantine, N.J., a tried-and-true butcher shop is still grinding and stuffing sausage.

episodes.name: Beef and Bird
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's loading up the meat with bomb beef and bird. In North Conway, N.H., a funky joint is putting Thai into their tacos and punching up their piccata. In Emerald Isle, N.C., a local gem is firing up monster barbecue. Then in Taos, a traditional spot is serving up real deal New Mexican specialties.

episodes.name: Not-Your-Everyday, All Day
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's diggin' into not-your-everyday dishes, all day long. In Taos, N.M., there's a sweet, stacked-up breakfast and a unique pot pie twist, plus cheffed-up Mexican recipes you won't find on a typical menu. Then, skate legend Tony Hawk is along for the ride in San Diego, grabbin' crazy creative vegan cooking.

episodes.name: Culinary Adventure
episodes.overview:
Tuétana Taquería / Mar Rustico (San Diego, Calif.) • Shawarma Guys (San Diego, Calif.) • Donabe Asian Kitchen (Taos, N.M.)

This trip, Guy's jumpin' into a full culinary adventure. In Old Town San Diego, with a two-for-one spot servin' Baja-style seafood and rich bone marrow tacos.  Stayin' in San Diego, a funky Middle Eastern food truck puttin' out next-level shawarma rated best in the U.S.A. And in New Mexico, a pan-Asian joint pullin' out the all stops with curry noodles and a bison Reuben bánh mì.

episodes.name: Revved Up
episodes.overview: If there’s one thing that’s synonymous with DDD, it's Guy Fieri's Rojo Red '68 Camaro. This car has been on his road trip around the country for years, and she is tired. Guy and his buddies at VP Speed Shop are retooling another '68 Camaro to be an identical twin sister that even Guy won't be able to tell apart. When he stops in for check-ins, he'll bring some of his favorite dishes from local places around the area. Plus, we'll look back on how the Camaro became Guy's sidekick as we revisit some of its best gags, celebrity encounters and food-centric shenanigans.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Burgers, Bowls and Bangers
episodes.overview: In a bowl or on a bun, this trip's got it all! First up, Guy pops into a poke truck he found at the Ferndale County Fair for some island-inspired flavors. Then in Hackensack, N.J., a diner is still serving sliders and steak sandwiches you can eat by the truckload. Plus, a popular Palm Desert, Calif., spot has savory and sweet breakfast options to satisfy any palate, including frosted pastries and a banger benny.

episodes.name: Thai, Pie and Fries
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diving into Thai food, pie and some hearty fries. In San Diego, an amazing Asian spot is servin' phenomenal fried fish and righteous ribs. Plus, in Arroyo Seco, N.M., a New Zealand food truck is making mouthwatering meat pies and a modern comfort joint is cooking up a mushroom masterpiece and loaded bison chili fries.

episodes.name: West Coast Wonders
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's cruisin' California for some West Coast wonders. In Healdsburg, a rooftop oasis is firing up pork belly pizza and creating a charcuterie cornucopia. In San Diego, a funky joint is dishing out a real deal taste of New Orleans, and a scratch breakfast/lunch spot is going over-the-top with sweet and savory.

episodes.name: Smoker, Stove & Stewer
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's checkin' out all kinds of culinary. In Las Vegas, a BBQ food truck is smokin' up monster sandwiches, and in Santa Barbara, Calif., a comfort spot is putting out primo pot pie and shrimp curry. Plus, a Mediterranean joint is knockin' it out of the park with beef skewers and tandoori chicken.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Chick'in Out
episodes.overview: From chicken to chickpeas, this road trip's got it all! First up in Santa Fe, N.M., Guy Fieri checks in on an African joint to taste their extra special oxtail and a downhome stew that'll warm you right up. Then, a café in New Jersey is still pressing paninis and stuffing sandwiches in two locations and growing. Finally, a Brooklyn spot is servin' traditional Southern sides in Super Bowl portions with enough mac and cheese, fried pickles and collards to feed the whole team.

episodes.name: Interesting Italian
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diggin' into all kinds of Italian. In Santa Barbara, Calif., Dennis Miller is riding shotgun for a taste of prime-time pizza and amazing arancini. In Las Vegas, a vegan joint is puttin' their spin on an Italian "meat" sandwich, plus a funky pizzeria is stuffing chicken parm into a spectacular stromboli.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Crab Cakes to Curry
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's crossing the country for off-the-hook culinary creations! In Santa Fe, N.M., Guy goes bananas for a banana curry. Then in Las Vegas, a trio representing both coasts has tripled their real estate all thanks to pineapple on their pizza. Plus, they've got a new kind of pie getting rave reviews. Finally, clams and crab cakes in Leeds Point, N.J., are creating all kinds of buzz.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Mac Daddy Meat
episodes.overview: It's a full-blown meat-fest on this road trip! First up, Guy Fieri stops to check out a BBQ joint in Las Vegas that's doin' burnt ends and meatloaf in a totally different way. Then in Belmar, New Jersey, a Mexi-Cali must-stop is stuffin' street tacos like you’d find South of the Border. Just across the state in Rocky Hill is burgers and fries you can't find anywhere else!

episodes.name: All-Over Flavor
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's bathing in flavorful finds. In Santa Barbara, Calif., he takes Marc Summers to check out fried rice served in a bowl and in a burrito. Then, he's off to Las Vegas with Hunter for real deal Jamaican. We're talkin' island-inspired festival, jerk chicken and escovitch fish. Plus in Florida, the most un-Boca Boca restaurant is dishing out lobster meatballs and pork cheek empanadas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: All Wrapped Up
episodes.overview: From coast to coast, Guy Fieri's wrapping up all kinds of grub. First up in Vegas, a crepe shop is folding up everything from pork to peaches. Then in Santa Barbara, California, there's killer carnitas and green chile verde that hasn't changed, while in Robbinsville, New Jersey, real deal Italian dishes like prosciutto bread and chicken parm are served straight out of the deli case.

episodes.name: Chicken and Ribs
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's flyin' with chicken and so much more. In Santa Barbara, California, a butcher-restaurant combo is saucing up their chicken tacos and going fried on a stellar sandwich. In Delray Beach, Florida, an homage to mom includes a mouthwatering meaty pasta and off-the-hook seafood stew. Then in Las Vegas, a wild chef is going over the top with his gorgeous Thai creations.

episodes.name: Meat and Sweet
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's pilin' up the meat along with a little sweet. In Santa Barbara, California, a hidden gem is puttin' out funky fusion like fried chicken bao buns and Korean paella. In Boynton Beach, Florida, a bomb butcher is creating elevated porchetta and scratch-made hot dogs. In Boca Raton, Florida, a food truck is stacking up a carnivore's dream and cooking brownie cheesecake right into a jar.

episodes.name: Mexican, Mediterranean and Mofongo
episodes.overview:
Hellenic Republic (Coral Springs, Fla.) • Letty’s de Letecia’s Cocina (Las Vegas, Nev.) • La Cosinita Latina (West Palm Beach, Fla.)

This trip, Guy's grabbin’ an international assortment of flavor. First up, a funky Florida spot puttin’ their Mediterranean spin on lamb burgers and fried shrimp. In Las Vegas, an O.G. Mexican joint servin’ up the-bomb birria tacos, magnificent mole and a wild take on margaritas. And in West Palm Beach, a familiar face at a local gem dishin’ out primo Puerto Rican specialties like a lobster mofongo.

episodes.name: A World of Meat
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's digging into meaty mashups from all over the world. In Boise, Idaho, a Russian joint is servin' up lights-out lamb and out-of-this-world dumplings. Plus, a Pakistani spot is cooking authentic dishes like flavorful goat and righteous rice. In Ocala, Fla., a barbecue pro is puttin' his delicious spin on smoky ribs, brisket mac and cheese-stuffed sausage.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: All Sorts of Sandwiches
episodes.overview: On this trip down memory lane, Guy Fieri's eating all sorts of sandwiches, from fried to "pied." First up, in Boise, Idaho, an old school drive-in is deep-dunking their Monte Cristos. In Atlantic City, pork rolls and patties are all wrapped up in pizza dough. Finally, a pizza joint in Las Vegas is stuffin', seedin' and saucin' East Coast-inspired eats.

episodes.name: Pick-Me-Ups
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's picking up handfuls of flavor. In Boise, Idaho, a real deal empanada emporium and a stick-to-your-ribs spot are both servin' up off-the-hook burgers and sandwiches. Then, a funky joint in Savannah is puttin' out wood-fired pizza and bagels that are all over the map.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Biscuits to Briskets
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's tasting food from coast to coast and across the pond. First up, Guy's eating Irish-inspired egg rolls in Atlantic Beach, Florida. Then, there's bacon jam and mile-high meatloaf from the 18th hole in Vincentown, N.J., and an all-American breakfast with an English twist in Ventura, California.

episodes.name: Seafood, Spice & Soul
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's grabbing seaside snacks, global spice and Southern soul. On Tybee Island, Ga., a beachy joint is going gourmet with their hot dogs and fresh seafood, while in Savannah, a real deal soul food spot is rolling out an oxtail twist and down-home peach cobbler. Then in Boise, Idaho, a café run by sisters is serving up a taste of Afghanistan with a heartwarming mission.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Dishes Done Right
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's hittin' all the flavours, from barbecue to banh mi. He enjoys rib tips under the Hollywood stars in Los Angeles, gets an Italian element on his jerk chicken in Ohio and checks out a business-busting Vietnamese-BBQ mashup in Michigan.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Pastrami, Patties and Parm
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's going across the country to sample all sorts of savory eats. He catches up on all things BBQ on St. Simons Island, GA, before heading to Los Angeles for chicken parm at an Italian deli and supersized subs loaded with plenty of fried food.

episodes.name: Down South & South of the Border
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's grabbing Southern flavor and south-of-the-border style with a spin. In Tybee Island, Georgia, an old ice cream shop turned restaurant is serving standout seafood and gourmet grilled cheese, while in Savannah, there's culinary comfort cooked up in an old garage. Then in Boise, Idaho, a taco spot gone wild is blowing up the beef and getting creative with carnitas.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Island-Inspired Eats
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's gearing up for vacation mode with Italian and island-inspired eats. First up in Manhattan Beach, Calif., there's both carbonara and Kalua pig comin' out of the same spot. Then just up the 405, Guy's sampling Lao Lao in Los Angeles. Plus, a Jamaican joint in Cincinnati's servin' a brown stew chicken wrap to-go.

episodes.name: Sloppy, Saucy and Stuffed
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diggin' into hearty helpings -- both saucy and stuffed. In Los Angeles, there's El Salvadorian with a twist, like prime-time pupusas and an extra-meaty burger. In Oregon, a food cart in a motel parking lot is serving up authentic Indian. Plus in Pooler, Ga., a Puerto Rican joint is going crazy with a mofongo mashup and their take on a sloppy joe.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Mexi-Cali Meals
episodes.overview: For this trip, Guy Fieri's chowing down on South-of-the-Border bites throughout California. First up, Guy's swinging through Victorville to check in on an O.G. DDD truck stop servin' monster-sized sandwiches and scratch-made salsa. Then in Garden Grove, a generational joint is dishin' out chile verde by the vat, and a Salvadorian spot in Los Angeles may have changed hands, but the top-notch tampiquenas are still the same.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Wrapped, Stacked and Sliced
episodes.overview: On this trip down memory lane, Guy Fieri's wrapping 'em up and stacking 'em high. First up, a Filipino-fusion joint relocated to California's Inland Empire, but their lumpia and spicy pork fries are worth the commute. Then in Santa Monica, an oldie but goodie is still making out-of-bounds burgers, while a staple in Boulder, Colo., is celebrating a century with their college-town classics.

episodes.name: Top-Notch Toppings
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diving into dishes with over-the-top toppings. In Cincinnati, a smokin' spot is piling up a mega pork sandwich and the city's signature chili-pasta mashup. In Bend, Ore., a vegan food trailer is getting creative with righteous rice, veggies and tostadas. Then in Venice, Calif., a real deal pizza stop is puttin' out flavorful flatbread and frying up the pie.

episodes.name: Stuffed, Sandwiched and Souped
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's getting stuffed and sandwiched. In Los Angeles, a taco truck is going big with the birria and putting out tasty tostadas. In Bend, Ore., it's Polish-palooza with lights-out pierogis and a cabbage specialty. Then in Milford, Ohio, an elevated diner is spicing up their chicken sandwich and pairing short rib grilled cheese with kimchi tomato soup.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Ocean Eats and a Chicken Feast
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri's checking out seafood sensations and fryin' up a lot of fowl. First up in Los Angeles, he's tasting a spicy Thai soup and garlic prawns from a GGG alum. Then, Guy's off to Colorado for Italian-inspired crispy cutlets in Colorado Springs and a tower of fried chicken meant for the Mile-High City.

episodes.name: Dumpling-icious
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's diving into dumplings and other righteous recipes from around the world. In Cincinnati, a not-your-everyday Japanese joint is firing up meaty gyozas and a surprising Asian-pasta blend. In Sisters, Ore., a Nepalese spot is showcasing their traditional dumplings alongside a pork belly bao. Then in Los Angeles, a Lebanese-Armenian oasis is putting out stellar shawarma and a righteous regional dumpling dish.

episodes.name: Tasty Time Travel
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's headed on some tasty trips back in time. There's an old schoolhouse in Camp Dennison, Ohio, with a comfort food curriculum like fried chicken and peanut butter pie. Then in Redmond, Ore., a church-turned-restaurant is putting out heavenly pizza and angelic wings, and in Stamford, Conn., a retro joint is dishing out diner classics like matzo ball soup and a taste of Thanksgiving.

episodes.name: From Chicken to Caribbean
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's flyin' from the-bomb bird to island inspiration. In Omaha, a chicken-centric spot is servin' it up fried, spiced and paired with pancakes. In Cincinnati, a hidden gem is firing up real deal Caribbean favorites. Plus, in Redmond, Oregon, an eclectic spot is throwin' a curve into their Cuban sandwich and going over-the-top with chicken and dumplings.

episodes.name: Variety of Flavor
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's hittin' up joints crushin' all kinds of flavor. There's a Malaysian oasis in Cincinnati and a Salvadorian spot in Port Chester, New York, each serving their real deal cultural specialties. Plus, an Omaha family is going Detroit-style with their pizza served straight out of a bus.

episodes.name: Champion Chefs
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's visiting restaurants owned by rockstar chefs who are familiar Food Network faces. In Studio City, Calif., Chef Antonia Lofaso is cooking up out-of-this-world global flavors, from Japanese to Italian. Then in Rapid City, S.D., Chef Justin Warner is serving up righteous ramen and dynamite dumplings.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Chicken, Cheese and Chili Paste
episodes.overview: On this walk down memory lane, Guy Fieri explores a what's what of culinary skills. First up in Orlando, Fla., Guy's checking in on an Italian joint rollin' chicken marsala meatballs. Then, he's smokin' rib tips and fermenting with chili paste in Denver and going wild with grilled cheese in Charlotte, N.C.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Wraps and Rolls
episodes.overview: On this trip, Guy Fieri has an East Coast experience. First up, he stops by a food truck in Orlando, Fla., that's now permanently parked but still rollin' out perfect pastrami and Reuben rolls. Then in Charlotte, N.C., a hot dog haven is branching out of the bun with a Nashville hot chicken sandwich, and an O.G. Triple D alum right down the street is dishing out tacos and crab puppies.

episodes.name: From Chicken to Noodles
episodes.overview:
Il Pastaficio (Greenwich, Conn.) • daybird (Los Angeles, Calif.) • WD Cravings (Omaha, Neb.)

This trip, Guy Fieri's divin' into chicken, noodles and more in-between. In the Cos Cob neighborhood of Greenwich, a husband-and-wife team pasta shop goin' all-in with duck ragu bigoli and a truffle lasagna. Then, in the Virgil Village section of L.A., an all-star culinary cast assembles at a champion chef's joint crankin' out spicy Nashville-Sichuan chicken sandos. And In Omaha, a sweet and savory spot is goin' big with cheese-wheel pasta and decadent desserts.

episodes.name: East, South, West
episodes.overview:
Grigg Street Pizza (Greenwich, Conn.) • The Noble South (Mobile, Ala.) • Sitti's Table Gourmet Market & Café (Cody, Wyo.)

This trip, Guy's crossin' the country and hittin' prime-time pit stops.  In Connecticut, The Great Hambino knows a pizza joint puttin' out real deal pies and off-the-hook Philly cheesesteaks. In Alabama, a Triple D legend shows off a farm-to-table joint cookin' killer crawfish étouffée and chicken-fried quail. And in Wyoming, a Middle Eastern-Mediterranean spot servin' up stellar sandwiches and lights-out lamb flatbread.

episodes.name: Sandwich-Fest
episodes.overview:
Corbo's Southside Deli (Stamford, Conn.) • Kitchen Table (Omaha, Neb.) • Southwood Kitchen (Daphne, Ala.)

This trip, Guy's checkin out stellar sandwiches that stack up. In Connecticut, a real deal deli puttin' out the bomb belly bao and a righteous Reuben. In Omaha, a husband-and-wife team elevatin' meatloaf and a creative whole-bird chicken trifecta. And in Alabama, a spot servin' a dynamite French dip and delicious fall-off-the-bone pork shank.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Fishin' in Flavortown
episodes.overview:
Willie's Pinchos (Orlando, Fla.) • Crazy Burger Cafe & Juice Bar (Narragansett, R.I.) • Edgewood Café (Cranston, R.I.)

On this trip, Guy's goin' fishin' at some Flavortown faves. First up, headin' back to a savory Puerto Rican spot in Orlando still servin' up authentic Caribbean seafood and barbecue. Then, in Cranston, R.I., a joint puttin' out killer cod and little neck clams. And down the coast in Narragansett, a café still goin' strong firin' up next-level burgers.

episodes.name: Meaty to Meatless
episodes.overview:
The Humingbird Way Oyster Bar (Mobile, Ala.) • Modern Love (Omaha, Neb.) • Kouzina Greek Taverna & Bar (Stamford, Conn.)

This trip, Guy's diggin' into dishes that run the gamut from meaty to meatless. In Mobile, a neighborhood joint makin' a righteous rabbit. In Omaha, a modern spot fryin' a mean meatless fried chicken. And in Connecticut, a cozy downtown eatery servin' gangster Greek.

episodes.name: Wrapped, Pied and Fried
episodes.overview:
Block 16 (Omaha, Neb.) • Roosters (Mobile, Ala.) • 307 Pizza (Cody, Wyo.)

Guy's having it wrapped, pied, and fried. In Omaha, Guy takes on a bomb brisket sandwich and duck confit fries. In Mobile, a funky joint serves up craveable carnitas.  And in Cody, Wyoming, a pizza cart is firing up elevated Thai chicken pies.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Smothered and Sauced
episodes.overview:
Se7en Bites (Orlando, Fla.) • Gaul & Co. Malthouse (Philadelphia, Pa.) • Italian Corner (East Providence R.I.)

Guy heads back to popular Triple D spots: first up,  gettin' saucy with a smothered Sloppy Joe in Orlando. In the Port Richmond neighborhood of Philly they're servin' up kielbasa eggrolls and Buffalo Chicken Cheese Sauce-drenched fries. And in East Providence they've added sauced-up spicy gnocchi and a killer pork and pepper sandwich to the menu.

episodes.name: Flavor Explosion
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's diving into a flavor overload! In Alberta, Canada, an Indian joint is servin' up savory street food with flair. In LA, a vegan oasis puts their spin on bangin' Bolognese and elevated lion's mane pizza. And in Mobile, a rockin' food truck dishes out next-level tacos.

episodes.name: Southern, Western and North of the Border
episodes.overview:
Trap Fusion (Memphis, Tenn.) • Pie Zanos (Buffalo, Wyo.) • Heaven Restaurant Market	(Calgary, Alta., Canada)

Guy Fieri's diggin' dishes from across the map. in Memphis, a Southern-Caribbean mashup is servin' oxtail and lamb chops with extra spice. On the Wyoming edge of the Rockies, it's scratch-made Italian that's hittin' all the flavor notes. And, in Calgary, a Venezuelan spot is keepin' it fresh, tasty and gluten-free.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Eats of the Northeast
episodes.overview:
Super Duper Weenie (Fairfield, Conn.) • Stogie Joe's Tavern (Philadelphia, Pa.) • Standard Tap (Philadelphia, Pa.)

Guy Fieri's sampling Northeastern takes on nationwide flavors. First, a funky Connecticut food truck empire with its own brick-and-mortar joint servin' elevated hot dogs and chicken nuggets. Then, a Philly tavern with street cred is crankin' out savory seafood dishes and strombolis overflowin' with salamis and "gabagool".  And around the corner in the City of Brotherly Love, a new American spot is platin' elevated pub grub like bratwurst rarebit and real-deal Italian chorizo mussels.

episodes.name: From Noodle to Strudel
episodes.overview:
Good Fortune Company (Memphis, Tenn.) • Calgary Momo House (Calgary, Alta., Canada) • Bohemian Biergarten (Boulder, Colo.)

Guy Fieri's goin' from strudel to noodle with major deliciousness in between.  In Memphis, a power couple is bringin' big flavor to killer noodles and Rangoon-style crawfish dumplings. Up in Calgary, a next-level Nepalese joint is dishin' out mouthwaterin' chicken and chili. And back in the States, a rustic Boulder bohemian joint is platin' up sweet strudel and savory pancakes.

episodes.name: Hearty Handfuls
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's digging into hearty handfuls of major flavor. First up, a funky joint in Memphis, Tenn., is taking pizza and wings to the next level. Then, in Calgary, Alberta, an authentic Mexican spot is dishing out legit chicharron and tasty tacos, and in St. Simons Island, Ga., it's a taste of Argentina with elevated empanadas and the bomb beef short ribs.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Fresh and Fried
episodes.overview:
Saigon Noodle & Grill (Orlando, Fla.) • Marlowe’s Ribs and Restaurant (Memphis,  Tenn.) • Silk City Diner and Lounge (Philadelphia, Pa.)

This trip, Guy’s catchin’ up with some of his favorite Triple-D spots. First up, a taste of Vietnam in Orlando, where a husband-wife duo are crankin’ out three times the servings of their killer phở than before. Then in Memphis, Graceland meets Flavortown at a joint smokin’  sweet and tangy barbecue and dishin’ dessert fit for The King. And in Philly, an old school diner puttin’ their spin on classics like ham empanadas and cheesesteak egg rolls.

episodes.name: Great Taste, Surprising Place
episodes.overview:
Loaf (Memphis, Tenn.) • Salt & Pepper (Calgary, Alta., Canada) • The Burns Pub and Restaurant  (Broomfield, Colo.)

This trip, Guy’s grabbin’ big flavor from unexpected spots. In Memphis, makin’ culinary masterpieces in a museum. In The Great White North, a Calgary family joint three generations deep cookin’ up South-of-the-border classics. And in Colorado, slingin’ authentic British pub sandwiches, sweets, and spirits at a tiny airport.

episodes.name: Soup, Sandwiches and Seafood
episodes.overview:
Pure Street Food Noodle Bar (Calgary, Alta. Canada) • Porch (St. Simons Island, Ga.)

This trip Guy's headed north and south for some savory dishes. First, a Calgary spot wowin' locals with scratch-made street food like killer phở and a crispy sando with an out-of-bounds, off-the-hook dippin' sauce.  And in coastal Georgia, a joint puttin' its spin on Nashville hot chicken with a side of spicy shrimp.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: From Steak to Seafood
episodes.overview:
Mrs. Potato Restaurant (Orlando, Fla.) • Alcenia's (Memphis, Tenn.) • Evelyn's Drive-In (Tiverton, R.I.)

This trip, Guy's headin' back to some of his favorite surf and turf spots. In Orlando, a Brazilian joint famous for overstuffed potatoes now cookin' up even more South American specialties. In Memphis, revisitin' a from-scratch soul food spot carryin' on Momma's traditions and startin' some of their own.  And on the waters of Rhode Island, a seasonal shack uppin' their game with a lobster BLT and a two-pound fried seafood platter.

episodes.name: Flavor World
episodes.overview:
Fry Bread House (Phoenix, Ariz.) • Rincon Argentino (Boulder, Colo.) • Stick'EM (Memphis, Tenn.)

This trip, Guy's divin' into a world of cultural cuisine featuring indigenous recipes.  In Phoenix, a joint droppin' Native American fry bread and chumuth for tacos and souped-up pozole. In Colorado, a joint dishin' up savory, meaty Argentine specialties like empanadas.  And in Memphis, a funky downtown eatery marinatin' kabobs and lamb shanks with out-of-bounds Ethiopian flavors.

episodes.name: Bird, Belly and Beef
episodes.overview:
Hush Public House (Scottsdale, Ariz.) • Las Tortugas Deli Mexicana (Memphis, Tenn.) • Golden Isles Olive Oil at the Market Place (St. Simons Island, Ga.)

This trip, Guy”s samplin’ elevated beef, pork, and poultry classics around the country. In Scottsdale, an ex-Marine-turned-chef puttin’ his New American spin on Chicago Italian Beef. In Memphis, an authentic father-son Mexican joint servin’ up crispy pork belly and al Pastor tortuga sandos. And in coastal Georgia, an olive oil specialty shop makin’ a mean curry chicken salad and chocolate short ribs.

episodes.name: Smokin' Southern Decadence
episodes.overview:
Low Country Steak (Atlanta, Ga.) • Meat Boss (Mobile, Ala.)

This trip, Guy samplin' some decadent grub across the South. In Atlanta, rollin' into an old friend's next-level steakhouse for some rockin' meats and killer mac & cheese.  And in Alabama, a family BBQ joint usin' some funky homemade equipment to smoke up rib candy burgers and brisket sammies with Alabama white sauce and jalapeño jelly.

episodes.name: French Flavor and Meaty Kabobs
episodes.overview:
Kabob Grill N' Go (Phoenix, Ariz.) • Holy Crêpe!! (Boulder, Colo.) • Julia's Bistro & Bar (San Antonio, Tex.)

This trip, Guy's rollin' out for a mix of French and global cultural classics. In Phoenix, a husband and wife team crankin' their grill into overdrive for unique twists on Armenian and Persian meat on a skewer.  In Colorado, a crêpe haven throwin' down both savory and sweet takes on the folded French classic. And in San Antonio, keepin' with the French flavor at a neighborhood joint turnin' hearty comfort food into haute cuisine.

episodes.name: From the Seas and Overseas
episodes.overview:
Cracovia Polish-American Restaurant & Bar (Westminster, Colo.) • The Jerk Shack (San Antonio, Tex.) • Indigo Coastal Shanty (Brunswick, Ga.)

This trip, Guy’s rollin’ out and reel in’ in seafood and food from overseas. In the Denver suburbs, a Polish joint playin’ perfect pierogi. In San Antonio, a killer Caribbean stop serving’ seasoned shrimp. And in Georgia, a spot takin’ their Southern flair seaside.

episodes.name: From Spicy to Sticky
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's savoring both spicy and sweet eats. In St. Simons Island, Ga., a bomb bakery is plating righteous rum cake and sticky buns. Then, a pizza restaurant in Boulder, Colo., is firing up perfect artisan pies, and a spot in San Antonio, Texas, is channeling traditional Chinese with a dynamite duck dish and pork belly bowl.

episodes.name: Phoenix Food Fans
episodes.overview:
Tim Finnegan's (Glendale, Ariz.) • Bonfire Craft Kitchen & Taphouse (Tempe, Ariz.) • Crujiente Tacos (Phoenix, Ariz.)

This trip, Guy's goin' fanatical for Phoenix-area fare and the 2024 NCAA Men's Final Four. First up, a Glendale spot marryin' Irish pub grub with Southwest style with killer corned beef and cabbage taquitos. In Tempe, a family joint bringin' smoke and spice to wood-fired pizza. And in Phoenix, an award-winnin' neighborhood taqueria redefinin' Mexican street food.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Food Fired Up
episodes.overview:
Audrey Jane's Pizza Garage (Boulder, Colo.) • Republica Empanada (Mesa, Ariz.) • Cozy Corner Restaurant (Memphis, Tenn.)

This trip Guy's headin' back to familiar joints still firin' up classic tastes.  First up, a Boulder pizza spot crankin' out a Spicy Pig pie with homemade sausage and roasted jalapeños.  Then in Mesa, a family-run shop servin' new empanadas including a spin on picadillo tico.  And in Memphis, a classic dive carrying on a family tradition: their secret sweet and spicy 'cue including Cornish hens and thick-cut bologna sandos.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Rockin' Recipes
episodes.overview:
Velencia Luncheria (Norwalk, Conn.) • Aloha Kitchen (Mesa, Ariz.) • Nora Restaurant & Bar (Dallas, Tex.)

This trip Guy's headin' back to some of his faves for great recipes. In Connecticut. a Venezuelan spot crankin' out over-the-top arepas. In Arizona, a Hawaiian outpost servin' up island-inspired pork buns and sweet-n-hot chicken wings. And in Dallas, an Afghan joint grillin' up killer kebabs with a kick.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Diner Dishes
episodes.overview:
Silver Skillet (Atlanta, Ga.) • Magnolia Pancake Haus (San Antonio, Tex.) • Perk Eatery (Scottsdale, Ariz.)

This trip Guy's headin' back to some of his favorite diners. In Atlanta, a joint servin' up Southern comfort with country ham 'n red-eye gravy and a mighty mac and cheese. In San Antonio, a staple dishin' out brisket hash. And in Arizona, a joint platin' up a supreme breakfast burrito.

episodes.name: Fistful of Flavor
episodes.overview: Petra Mediterranean Pizza & Grill (San Luis Obispo, Calif.) • Cavé Bistro (Avon-by-the-Sea, N.J.) • Che Chori (Indianapolis, Ind.)  This trip, Guy's headin' out cross-country, grabbin' fistfuls of flavor. In sunny Cali, a local fave cookin' up killer chicken shawarma pizza and tri-tip pita pockets. On the Jersey Shore, a beach-side bistro slingin' herbaceous octopus and bone marrow burgers for Guy and his impractical joker pal. And in Indy, an Argentine joint firin' up house-made chimichurri chorizo and a out-of-bounds porchetta sando.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: African and Asian Eats
episodes.overview:
Aloy Modern Thai (Boulder, Colo.) •  Curry Corner (Tempe, Ariz.) - Moroccan Bites (San Antonio, Tex.)

This trip Guy's rollin' out for the best African and Asian food. First up, a Colorado spot still servin' up delicious tastes of Thailand. In Arizona, a Pakistani joint spicin' up their spin on home cookin'. And in San Antonio, a Moroccan place that keeps on dishin' out family faves.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Bacon, Burgers, and Pork Butt
episodes.overview:
Buttermilk Kitchen (Atlanta, Ga.) • The Thumb (Scottsdale, Ariz.) • Fred's Texas Cafe (Fort Worth, Tex.)

This trip, Guy's grabbin' seconds of the best bacon, burgers, and smoked meats in between.  In Atlanta, they're servin' up a smoked bacon meatloaf sandwich and mini banana bread loaves drenched in chocolate. In Arizona, a former doctor smokin' competition-quality sliced brisket, ribs, and pork & grits in a gas station. And in Fort Worth, a cowboy chef dishin' out chuckwagon-style food like a lamb chili, chicken-fried steak, and a burger with a BBQ bologna twist.

episodes.name: All Over the Plate
episodes.overview:
Tlaolli (Indianapolis, Ind.) • Skratch Kitchen (Bradley Beach, N.J.) • King Gyros (Whitehall, Ohio)

This trip Guy's checkin' out unique spins on familiar plates.  In the Englewood neighborhood of Indianapolis, a one-time steel worker crankin' out his twist on tamales and birria tacos.  In New Jersey, a former marine biologist goin' funky with clams and into overdrive with chicken Savoy.  And in Ohio, an old taco joint doin' a fast-casual take on Greek cuisine but not skimpin' on the menu with lemon dill-sauced lamb chops and 26 different desserts.

episodes.name: Grand Slam Sammy
episodes.overview:
Seed to Sprout (Avon-by-the-Sea, N.J.) • Sweet Cheeks Q (Boston, Mass.) • Taste! Craft Eatery (San Luis Obispo, Calif.)

This trip, Guy's roundin' the bases for some serious sammies. First, a vegan Jersey joint platin' plant-based perfection. In Boston, a TOC Champ bringin' real-deal barbecue and Southern fare to Beantown. And in Cali, a family spot lettin' folks mix up their own culinary adventure from seventy-six (76!) menu items.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: All Dough’ed Up
episodes.overview:
Skirted Heifer (Colorado Springs, Colo.) • Fat Tummy (San Antonio, Tex.) • Sal’s Gilbert Pizza (Gilbert, Ariz.)

This trip, Guy’s goin’ all in on homemade baked goods. In Colorado, a family-run joint platin’ cheese-skirted burgers on focaccia. In San Antonio, an Argentine empanada spot servin’ up decadent dulce de leche cookies. And in Arizona, a Sicilian place still goin’ strong with their crispy-crust Grandpa pizza pie.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Flavors from Afar
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's checking in with flavors packing a punch! First, a funky Atlanta joint is now a franchise, serving up Korean-Mexican fusion like a pork and kimchi quesadilla and a killer crispy shrimp taco. Then, a Thai spot in Dallas has expanded their menu but is still dishing out authentic flavors with their chicken platter and ground pork bowl. Then in Phoenix, real-deal Italian is going strong with elevated plates like homemade squid ink pasta with shellfish.

episodes.name: Wide World of Chefs
episodes.overview: This trip Guy's goin' nationwide for global tastes:  croquettes, Turkish dumplings and fried chicken.

episodes.name: Home Cooked Flavor
episodes.overview:
Vinal Bakery (East Somerville, Mass.) • High Bank Distillery Co. (Columbus, Ohio) • His Place Eatery (Indianapolis, Ind.)

This trip Guy's headin' out to find some home-made comfort. Outside Boston, a neighborhood place bakin' up scratch-made English muffins for out-of-bounds sandwiches. In Columbus, a whiskey joint elevatin' eats like barbacoa nachos. And in Indianapolis, a soul food spot platin' twists on comfort like a collard green grilled cheese and chicken 'n dumplings.

episodes.name: Burgers, Bone Marrow and Bangladesh
episodes.overview: Step Chld (Minneapolis, Minn.) • Joya's (Columbus, Ohio) • The Quiet Few (East Boston, Mass.)  This trip, Guy's grabbin' big-deal eats. First up: a world-class Minneapolis joint dishin' up eclectic fare like grilled bone marrow with basil sauce and lavender nori shrimp. In Columbus, a Bengali place mashin' up cultures with pork belly fried rice with crispy chicken meatballs. And outside Boston, a hole-in-the-wall whiskey bar servin' up a buffet of booze with and a Hell Yeah burger.

episodes.name: Triple D Nation: Risotto, Rellenos and Red Snapper
episodes.overview: This trip, Guy Fieri's eating his way through risotto, relleno and red snapper. First, a renovated mansion in Atlanta is still plating up not-your-average pub grub like a rockin' rabbit sausage cavatelli and out-of-bounds oyster mushroom risotto. Then, a roadside Mexican joint in Anthem, Ariz., is dishing out scratch-made faves with their killer carnitas and real deal rellenos, while in Arlington, Texas, Jamaican eats are going strong with jammin' jerk chicken and a succulent snapper.

episodes.name: From Vietnamese to Vegan
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's grabbin' grub from Vietnamese to vegan with some major meat in between. There's a Minneapolis Southeast Asian spot cookin' up Balinese chicken thighs and Vietnamese pork belly crepes. A Jersey Shore joint is smokin' up real-deal BBQ stacked into Reuben and chicken sandwiches. And a husband-and-wife duo in Missoula, Mont., is bakin' plant-based, gluten-free faves, like artisan avocado on scratch-made multigrain, plus lights-out lemon-glazed doughnuts.

episodes.name: Meat, Hmong and Mexican
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's diggin' major meat, Mexican and more! First, a meaty mashup in Columbus, Ohio, is slaying it with sandwiches, like their signature cheesesteak and righteous roast. Then, in Minneapolis, a Southeast Asian spot is servin' up craveable faves like lights-out Thai tea pancakes and finger-lickin' crispy chicken. And a family-run Mexican joint in Missoula, Mont., is plating up killer carne asada burritos and prime-time pork ribs with chile verde.

episodes.name: All Over Flavor
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's gettin' into flavors from all over! First up, a Vietnamese spot in Boston is dishing out rockin' rice noodle rolls and a barbecue beef banh mi on fresh-baked baguettes. Next, there's rustic country-style Italian in Missoula, Mont., plating up a legit lamb meatball sub and knockout octopus. And in Minneapolis, a Panamanian chef is cookin' up a taste of the Caribbean with big-deal beef skewers and jammin' jerk chicken.

episodes.name: Dough-Lightful Dishes
episodes.overview: Guy Fieri's diggin' into dishes that all start with great dough. There's a husband-and-wife team bringing legit Mexican eats to Minneapolis with their savory venison sopes, homemade tortillas and over-the-top pork. In Missoula, Mont., a pizza spot is slingin' award-winning artisan pies like meatball verde and savory, sweet sausage and cherry. Plus, a funky joint is cranking out inventive flavor combos while keepin' it vegan, like blueberry-basil doughnuts and a fully loaded cauliflower burrito.
